v8
V8 is Googleâ€™s open source high-performance JavaScript and WebAssembly engine, written in C++. It is used in Chrome and in Node.js, among others. It implements ECMAScript and WebAssembly, and runs on Windows, macOS, and Linux systems that use x64, IA-32, or ARM processors. V8 can be embedded into any C++ application.

31#define EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(name) EmitFnId(k_##name);
32#define EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(name, pc) EmitFnId(k_##name, pc);
33
34#define START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() \
35 { \
36 size_t _current_code_offset = code_.size(); \
37 size_t _current_slots_size = slots_.size(); \
38 DCHECK(!no_nested_emit_instr_handler_guard_); \
39 no_nested_emit_instr_handler_guard_ = true; \
40 stack_.clear_history(); \
41 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) { \
42 handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Small; \
43 } else { \
44 DCHECK_EQ(handler_size_, InstrHandlerSize::Large); \
45 } \
46 while (true) { \
47 current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
48
49#define START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(name) \
50 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() \
51 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(name)
52
53#define START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(name, pc) \
54 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() \
55 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(name, pc)
56
57#define END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() \
58 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode && current_instr_encoding_failed_) { \
59 code_.resize(_current_code_offset); \
60 slots_.resize(_current_slots_size); \
61 stack_.rollback(); \
62 current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false; \
63 handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Large; \
64 continue; \
65 } \
66 break; \
67 } \
68 DCHECK(!current_instr_encoding_failed_); \
69 no_nested_emit_instr_handler_guard_ = false; \
70 }
71
73// Memory64 macros
74
75#define EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER(name, mem64_name, is_memory64) \
76 if (V8_UNLIKELY(is_memory64)) { \
77 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(mem64_name); \
78 } else { \
79 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(name); \
80 }
81
82#define EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(name, mem64_name, is_memory64, pc) \
83 if (V8_UNLIKELY(is_memory64)) { \
84 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(mem64_name, pc); \
85 } else { \
86 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(name, pc); \
87 }

91WasmInterpreter::CodeMap::CodeMap(Isolate* isolate, const WasmModule* module,
92 const uint8_t* module_start, Zone* zone)
93 : zone_(zone),
94 isolate_(isolate),
95 module_(module),
96 interpreter_code_(zone),
97 bytecode_generation_time_(),
98 generated_code_size_(0) {
99 if (module == nullptr) return;
100 interpreter_code_.reserve(module->functions.size());
101 for (const WasmFunction& function : module->functions) {
102 if (function.imported) {
103 DCHECK(!function.code.is_set());
104 AddFunction(&function, nullptr, nullptr);
105 } else {
106 AddFunction(&function, module_start + function.code.offset(),
107 module_start + function.code.end_offset());
108 }
109 }
110}
111
112void WasmInterpreter::CodeMap::Preprocess(uint32_t function_index) {
113 InterpreterCode* code = &interpreter_code_[function_index];
114 DCHECK_EQ(code->function->imported, code->start == nullptr);
115 DCHECK(!code->bytecode && code->start);
116
117 base::TimeTicks start_time = base::TimeTicks::Now();
118
119 // Compute the control targets map and the local declarations.
120 BytecodeIterator it(code->start, code->end, &code->locals, zone_);
121
122 WasmBytecodeGenerator bytecode_generator(function_index, code, module_);
123 code->bytecode = bytecode_generator.GenerateBytecode();
124
125 // Generate histogram sample to measure the time spent generating the
126 // bytecode. Reuse the WasmCompileModuleMicroSeconds.wasm that is currently
127 // obsolete.
128 if (base::TimeTicks::IsHighResolution()) {
129 base::TimeDelta duration = base::TimeTicks::Now() - start_time;
130 bytecode_generation_time_ += duration;
131 int bytecode_generation_time_usecs =
132 static_cast<int>(bytecode_generation_time_.InMicroseconds());
133
134 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) Do not add a sample for each function!
135 isolate_->counters()->wasm_compile_wasm_module_time()->AddSample(
136 bytecode_generation_time_usecs);
137 }
138
139 // Generate histogram sample to measure the bytecode size. Reuse the
140 // V8.WasmModuleCodeSizeMiB (see {NativeModule::SampleCodeSize}).
141 int prev_code_size_mb = generated_code_size_ == 0
142 ? -1
143 : static_cast<int>(generated_code_size_ / MB);
144 generated_code_size_.fetch_add(code->bytecode->GetCodeSize());
145 int code_size_mb = static_cast<int>(generated_code_size_ / MB);
146 if (prev_code_size_mb < code_size_mb) {
147 Histogram* histogram = isolate_->counters()->wasm_module_code_size_mb();
148 histogram->AddSample(code_size_mb);
149 }
150}

156WasmInterpreterThread* WasmInterpreterThreadMap::GetCurrentInterpreterThread(
157 Isolate* isolate) {
158 const int current_thread_id = ThreadId::Current().ToInteger();
159 {
160 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(&mutex_);
161
162 auto it = map_.find(current_thread_id);
163 if (it == map_.end()) {
164 map_[current_thread_id] =
165 std::make_unique<WasmInterpreterThread>(isolate);
166 it = map_.find(current_thread_id);
167 }
168 return it->second.get();
169 }
170}
171
172void WasmInterpreterThreadMap::NotifyIsolateDisposal(Isolate* isolate) {
173 base::SpinningMutexGuard guard(&mutex_);
174
175 auto it = map_.begin();
176 while (it != map_.end()) {
177 WasmInterpreterThread* thread = it->second.get();
178 if (thread->GetIsolate() == isolate) {
179 thread->TerminateExecutionTimers();
180 it = map_.erase(it);
181 } else {
182 ++it;
183 }
184 }
185}

187void FrameState::SetCaughtException(Isolate* isolate,
188 uint32_t catch_block_index,
189 Handle<Object> exception) {
190 if (caught_exceptions_.is_null()) {
191 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(current_function_);
192 uint32_t blocks_count = current_function_->GetBlocksCount();
193 Handle<FixedArray> caught_exceptions =
194 isolate->factory()->NewFixedArrayWithHoles(blocks_count);
195 caught_exceptions_ = isolate->global_handles()->Create(*caught_exceptions);
196 }
197 caught_exceptions_->set(catch_block_index, *exception);
198}
199
200Handle<Object> FrameState::GetCaughtException(
201 Isolate* isolate, uint32_t catch_block_index) const {
202 Handle<Object> exception =
203 handle(caught_exceptions_->get(catch_block_index), isolate);
204 DCHECK(!IsTheHole(*exception));
205 return exception;
206}
207
208void FrameState::DisposeCaughtExceptionsArray(Isolate* isolate) {
209 if (!caught_exceptions_.is_null()) {
210 isolate->global_handles()->Destroy(caught_exceptions_.location());
211 caught_exceptions_ = Handle<FixedArray>::null();
212 }
213}

215WasmExecutionTimer::WasmExecutionTimer(Isolate* isolate,
216 bool track_jitless_wasm)
217 : execute_ratio_histogram_(
218 track_jitless_wasm
219 ? isolate->counters()->wasm_jitless_execution_ratio()
220 : isolate->counters()->wasm_jit_execution_ratio()),
221 slow_wasm_histogram_(
222 track_jitless_wasm
223 ? isolate->counters()->wasm_jitless_execution_too_slow()
224 : isolate->counters()->wasm_jit_execution_too_slow()),
225 window_has_started_(false),
226 next_interval_time_(),
227 start_interval_time_(),
228 window_running_time_(),
229 sample_duration_(base::TimeDelta::FromMilliseconds(std::max(
230 0, v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_histogram_sample_duration.value()))),
231 slow_threshold_(v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_histogram_slow_threshold.value()),
232 slow_threshold_samples_count_(std::max(
233 1, v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_slow_threshold_samples_count.value())),
234 isolate_(isolate) {
235 int cooldown_interval_in_msec = std::max(
236 0, v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_histogram_sample_period.value() -
237 v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_histogram_sample_duration.value());
238 cooldown_interval_ =
239 base::TimeDelta::FromMilliseconds(cooldown_interval_in_msec);
240}
241
242void WasmExecutionTimer::BeginInterval(bool start_timer) {
243 window_has_started_ = true;
244 start_interval_time_ = base::TimeTicks::Now();
245 window_running_time_ = base::TimeDelta();
246 if (start_timer) {
247 window_execute_timer_.Start();
248 }
249}
250
251void WasmExecutionTimer::EndInterval() {
252 window_has_started_ = false;
253 base::TimeTicks now = base::TimeTicks::Now();
254 next_interval_time_ = now + cooldown_interval_;
255 int running_ratio = kMaxPercentValue *
256 window_running_time_.TimesOf(now - start_interval_time_);
257 AddSample(running_ratio);
258}
259
260void WasmExecutionTimer::AddSample(int running_ratio) {
261 DCHECK(v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms);
262
263 execute_ratio_histogram_->AddSample(running_ratio);
264
265 // Emit a Jit[less]WasmExecutionTooSlow sample if the average of the last
266 // {v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_slow_threshold_samples_count} samples is above
267 // {v8_flags.wasm_exec_time_histogram_slow_threshold}.
268 samples_.push_back(running_ratio);
269 if (samples_.size() == slow_threshold_samples_count_) {
270 int sum = 0;
271 for (int sample : samples_) sum += sample;
272 int average = sum / slow_threshold_samples_count_;
273 if (average >= slow_threshold_) {
274 slow_wasm_histogram_->AddSample(average);
275
276 if (isolate_ && !isolate_->context().is_null()) {
277 // Skip this event because not(yet) supported by Chromium.
278
279 // HandleScope scope(isolate_);
280 // v8::metrics::WasmInterpreterSlowExecution event;
281 // event.slow_execution = true;
282 // event.jitless = v8_flags.wasm_jitless;
283 // event.cpu_percentage = average;
284 // v8::metrics::Recorder::ContextId context_id =
285 // isolate_->GetOrRegisterRecorderContextId(
286 // isolate_->native_context());
287 // isolate_->metrics_recorder()->DelayMainThreadEvent(event,
288 // context_id);
289 }
290 }
291
292 samples_.clear();
293 }
294}
295
296void WasmExecutionTimer::StartInternal() {
297 DCHECK(v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms);
298 DCHECK(!window_execute_timer_.IsStarted());
299
300 base::TimeTicks now = base::TimeTicks::Now();
301 if (window_has_started_) {
302 if (now - start_interval_time_ > sample_duration_) {
303 EndInterval();
304 } else {
305 window_execute_timer_.Start();
306 }
307 } else {
308 if (now >= next_interval_time_) {
309 BeginInterval(true);
310 } else {
311 // Ignore this start event.
312 }
313 }
314}
315
316void WasmExecutionTimer::StopInternal() {
317 DCHECK(v8_flags.wasm_enable_exec_time_histograms && v8_flags.slow_histograms);
318
319 base::TimeTicks now = base::TimeTicks::Now();
320 if (window_has_started_) {
321 DCHECK(window_execute_timer_.IsStarted());
322 base::TimeDelta elapsed = window_execute_timer_.Elapsed();
323 window_running_time_ += elapsed;
324 window_execute_timer_.Stop();
325 if (now - start_interval_time_ > sample_duration_) {
326 EndInterval();
327 }
328 } else {
329 if (now >= next_interval_time_) {
330 BeginInterval(false);
331 } else {
332 // Ignore this stop event.
333 }
334 }
335}
336
337void WasmExecutionTimer::Terminate() {
338 if (execute_ratio_histogram_->Enabled()) {
339 if (window_has_started_) {
340 if (window_execute_timer_.IsStarted()) {
341 window_execute_timer_.Stop();
342 }
343 EndInterval();
344 }
345 }
346}

349void NopFinalizer(const v8::WeakCallbackInfo<void>& data) {
350 Address* global_handle_location =
351 reinterpret_cast<Address*>(data.GetParameter());
352 GlobalHandles::Destroy(global_handle_location);
353}
354
355Handle<WasmInstanceObject> MakeWeak(
356 Isolate* isolate, Handle<WasmInstanceObject> instance_object) {
357 Handle<WasmInstanceObject> weak_instance =
358 isolate->global_handles()->Create<WasmInstanceObject>(*instance_object);
359 Address* global_handle_location = weak_instance.location();
360 GlobalHandles::MakeWeak(global_handle_location, global_handle_location,
361 &NopFinalizer, v8::WeakCallbackType::kParameter);
362 return weak_instance;
363}

365std::optional<wasm::ValueType> GetWasmReturnTypeFromSignature(
366 const FunctionSig* wasm_signature) {
367 if (wasm_signature->return_count() == 0) return {};
368
369 DCHECK_EQ(wasm_signature->return_count(), 1);
370 return wasm_signature->GetReturn(0);
371}

375// Build the interpreter call stack for the current activation. For each stack
376// frame we need to calculate the Wasm function index and the original Wasm
377// bytecode location, calculated from the current WasmBytecode offset.
378std::vector<WasmInterpreterStackEntry>
379WasmInterpreterThread::Activation::CaptureStackTrace(
380 const TrapStatus* trap_status) const {
381 std::vector<WasmInterpreterStackEntry> stack_trace;
382 const FrameState* frame_state = &current_frame_state_;
383 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(frame_state);
384
385 if (trap_status) {
386 stack_trace.push_back(WasmInterpreterStackEntry{
387 trap_status->trap_function_index, trap_status->trap_pc});
388 } else {
389 if (frame_state->current_function_) {
390 stack_trace.push_back(WasmInterpreterStackEntry{
391 frame_state->current_function_->GetFunctionIndex(),
392 frame_state->current_bytecode_
393 ? static_cast<int>(
394 frame_state->current_function_->GetPcFromTrapCode(
395 frame_state->current_bytecode_))
396 : 0});
397 }
398 }
399
400 frame_state = frame_state->previous_frame_;
401 while (frame_state && frame_state->current_function_) {
402 stack_trace.insert(
403 stack_trace.begin(),
404 WasmInterpreterStackEntry{
405 frame_state->current_function_->GetFunctionIndex(),
406 frame_state->current_bytecode_
407 ? static_cast<int>(
408 frame_state->current_function_->GetPcFromTrapCode(
409 frame_state->current_bytecode_))
410 : 0});
411 frame_state = frame_state->previous_frame_;
412 }
413
414 // It is possible to have a WasmInterpreterEntryFrame without having a Wasm
415 // current_function_. This can happen if we call from JS a JS function
416 // imported and exported by Wasm. In this case let's add a dummy stack entry.
417 if (stack_trace.empty()) {
418 stack_trace.push_back(WasmInterpreterStackEntry{0, 0});
419 }
420
421 return stack_trace;
422}
423
424int WasmInterpreterThread::Activation::GetFunctionIndex(int index) const {
425 std::vector<int> function_indexes;
426 const FrameState* frame_state = &current_frame_state_;
427 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) - Too slow?
428 while (frame_state->current_function_) {
429 function_indexes.push_back(
430 frame_state->current_function_->GetFunctionIndex());
431 frame_state = frame_state->previous_frame_;
432 }
433
434 if (static_cast<size_t>(index) < function_indexes.size()) {
435 return function_indexes[function_indexes.size() - index - 1];
436 }
437 return -1;
438}

440WasmInterpreterThread::WasmInterpreterThread(Isolate* isolate)
441 : isolate_(isolate),
442 state_(State::STOPPED),
443 trap_reason_(TrapReason::kTrapUnreachable),
444 current_stack_size_(kInitialStackSize),
445 stack_mem_(nullptr),
446 reference_stack_(isolate_->global_handles()->Create(
447 ReadOnlyRoots(isolate_).empty_fixed_array())),
448 current_ref_stack_size_(0),
449 execution_timer_(isolate, true) {
450 PageAllocator* page_allocator = GetPlatformPageAllocator();
451 stack_mem_ = AllocatePages(page_allocator, nullptr, kMaxStackSize,
452 page_allocator->AllocatePageSize(),
453 PageAllocator::kNoAccess);
454 if (!stack_mem_ ||
455 !SetPermissions(page_allocator, stack_mem_, current_stack_size_,
456 PageAllocator::Permission::kReadWrite)) {
457 V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(nullptr,
458 "WasmInterpreterThread::WasmInterpreterThread",
459 "Cannot allocate Wasm interpreter stack");
460 UNREACHABLE();
461 }
462}
463
464WasmInterpreterThread::~WasmInterpreterThread() {
465 GlobalHandles::Destroy(reference_stack_.location());
466 FreePages(GetPlatformPageAllocator(), stack_mem_, kMaxStackSize);
467}
468
469void WasmInterpreterThread::EnsureRefStackSpace(size_t new_size) {
470 if (V8_LIKELY(current_ref_stack_size_ >= new_size)) return;
471 size_t requested_size = base::bits::RoundUpToPowerOfTwo64(new_size);
472 new_size = std::max(size_t{8},
473 std::max(2 * current_ref_stack_size_, requested_size));
474 int grow_by = static_cast<int>(new_size - current_ref_stack_size_);
475 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate_); // Avoid leaking handles.
476 Handle<FixedArray> new_ref_stack =
477 isolate_->factory()->CopyFixedArrayAndGrow(reference_stack_, grow_by);
478 new_ref_stack->FillWithHoles(static_cast<int>(current_ref_stack_size_),
479 static_cast<int>(new_size));
480 isolate_->global_handles()->Destroy(reference_stack_.location());
481 reference_stack_ = isolate_->global_handles()->Create(*new_ref_stack);
482 current_ref_stack_size_ = new_size;
483}
484
485void WasmInterpreterThread::ClearRefStackValues(size_t index, size_t count) {
486 reference_stack_->FillWithHoles(static_cast<int>(index),
487 static_cast<int>(index + count));
488}

490void WasmInterpreterThread::RaiseException(Isolate* isolate,
491 MessageTemplate message) {
492 DCHECK_EQ(WasmInterpreterThread::TRAPPED, state_);
493 if (!isolate->has_exception()) {
494 ClearThreadInWasmScope wasm_flag(isolate);
495 Handle<JSObject> error_obj =
496 isolate->factory()->NewWasmRuntimeError(message);
497 JSObject::AddProperty(isolate, error_obj,
498 isolate->factory()->wasm_uncatchable_symbol(),
499 isolate->factory()->true_value(), NONE);
500 isolate->Throw(*error_obj);
501 }
502}

506 MessageTemplate message) {
507 WasmInterpreterThread* current_thread = GetCurrentInterpreterThread(isolate);
508 current_thread->trap_reason_ = WasmOpcodes::MessageIdToTrapReason(message);
509}

514 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): store in new data member?
515 return current_thread->trap_reason_;

536#if !defined(V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS)

538enum BoundsCheckedHandlersCounter {
539#define ITEM_ENUM_DEFINE(name) name##counter,
540 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(ITEM_ENUM_DEFINE)
541#undef ITEM_ENUM_DEFINE
542 kTotalItems
543};
544
545V8_DECLARE_ONCE(init_instruction_table_once);
546V8_DECLARE_ONCE(init_trap_handlers_once);
547
548// A subset of the Wasm instruction handlers is implemented as ASM builtins, and
549// not with normal C++ functions. This is done only for LoadMem and StoreMem
550// builtins, which can trap for out of bounds accesses.
551// V8 already implements out of bounds trap handling for compiled Wasm code and
552// allocates two large guard pages before and after each Wasm memory region to
553// detect out of bounds memory accesses. Once an access violation exception
554// arises, the V8 exception filter intercepts the exception and checks whether
555// it originates from Wasm code.
556// The Wasm interpreter reuses the same logic, and
557// WasmInterpreter::HandleWasmTrap is called by the SEH exception handler to
558// check whether the access violation was caused by an interpreter instruction
559// handler. It is necessary that these handlers are Wasm builtins for two
560// reasons:
561// 1. We want to know precisely the start and end address of each handler to
562// verify if the AV happened inside one of the Load/Store builtins and can be
563// handled with a Wasm trap.
564// 2. If the exception is handled, we interrupt the execution of
565// TrapMemOutOfBounds, which sets the TRAPPED state and breaks the execution of
566// the chain of instruction handlers with a x64 'ret'. This only works if there
567// is no stack cleanup to do in the handler that caused the failure (no
568// registers to pop from the stack before the 'ret'). Therefore we cannot rely
569// on the compiler, we can only make sure that this is the case if we implement
570// the handlers in assembly.
571
572// Forward declaration
573INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC TrapMemOutOfBounds(
574 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
575 int64_t r0, double fp0);
576
577void InitTrapHandlersOnce(Isolate* isolate) {
578 CHECK_LE(kInstructionCount, kInstructionTableSize);
579
580 ClearThreadInWasmScope wasm_flag(isolate);
581
582 // Overwrites the instruction handlers that access memory and can cause an
583 // out-of-bounds trap with builtin versions that don't have explicit bounds
584 // check but rely on a trap handler to intercept the access violation and
585 // transform it into a trap.
586 EmbeddedData embedded_data = EmbeddedData::FromBlob();
587#define V(name) \
588 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) { \
589 trap_handler::RegisterHandlerData( \
590 reinterpret_cast<Address>(kInstructionTable[k_##name]), \
591 embedded_data.InstructionSizeOf(Builtin::k##name##_s), 0, nullptr); \
592 } \
593 trap_handler::RegisterHandlerData( \
594 reinterpret_cast<Address>( \
595 kInstructionTable[k_##name + kInstructionCount]), \
596 embedded_data.InstructionSizeOf(Builtin::k##name##_l), 0, nullptr);
597 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
598#undef V
599}
600
601void InitInstructionTableOnce(Isolate* isolate) {
602 size_t index = 0;
603#define V(name) \
604 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) { \
605 kInstructionTable[index] = reinterpret_cast<PWasmOp*>( \
606 isolate->builtins()->code(Builtin::k##name##_s)->instruction_start()); \
607 } \
608 kInstructionTable[kInstructionCount + index++] = reinterpret_cast<PWasmOp*>( \
609 isolate->builtins()->code(Builtin::k##name##_l)->instruction_start());
610
611#ifdef __clang__
612#pragma clang diagnostic push
613#pragma clang diagnostic ignored "-Wcast-calling-convention"
614#endif // __clang__
615 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
616#ifdef __clang__
617#pragma clang diagnostic pop
618#endif // __clang__
619#undef V
620
621#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
622 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
623 index = 0;
624#define DEFINE_INSTR_HANDLER(name) kInstructionHandlerNames[index++] = #name;
625 FOREACH_INSTR_HANDLER(DEFINE_INSTR_HANDLER)
626 FOREACH_TRACE_INSTR_HANDLER(DEFINE_INSTR_HANDLER)
627#undef DEFINE_INSTR_HANDLER
628 }
629#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
630}
631#endif // !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
632
633WasmInterpreter::WasmInterpreter(Isolate* isolate, const WasmModule* module,
634 const ModuleWireBytes& wire_bytes,
635 Handle<WasmInstanceObject> instance_object)
636 : zone_(isolate->allocator(), ZONE_NAME),
637 instance_object_(MakeWeak(isolate, instance_object)),
638 module_bytes_(wire_bytes.start(), wire_bytes.end(), &zone_),
639 codemap_(isolate, module, module_bytes_.data(), &zone_) {
640 wasm_runtime_ = std::make_shared<WasmInterpreterRuntime>(
641 module, isolate, instance_object_, &codemap_);
642 module->SetWasmInterpreter(wasm_runtime_);
643
644#if !defined(V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS)
645 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) - For modules that have 64-bit Wasm memory we
646 // need to use explicit bound checks; memory guard pages only work with 32-bit
647 // memories. This could be implemented by allocating a different dispatch
648 // table for each instance (probably in the WasmInterpreterRuntime object) and
649 // patching the entries of Load/Store instructions with bultin handlers only
650 // for instances related to modules that have 32-bit memories. 64-bit memories
651 // are not supported yet by DrumBrake.
652 base::CallOnce(&init_instruction_table_once, &InitInstructionTableOnce,
653 isolate);
654 base::CallOnce(&init_trap_handlers_once, &InitTrapHandlersOnce, isolate);
655
656 trap_handler::SetLandingPad(reinterpret_cast<Address>(TrapMemOutOfBounds));
657#endif // !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
658}
659
660WasmInterpreterThread::State WasmInterpreter::ContinueExecution(
661 WasmInterpreterThread* thread, bool called_from_js) {
662 wasm_runtime_->ContinueExecution(thread, called_from_js);
663 return thread->state();
664}

672constexpr uint32_t kFloat32SignBitMask = uint32_t{1} << 31;
673constexpr uint64_t kFloat64SignBitMask = uint64_t{1} << 63;
674
675#ifdef DRUMBRAKE_ENABLE_PROFILING
676
677static const char* prev_op_name_s = nullptr;
678static std::map<std::pair<const char*, const char*>, uint64_t>*
679 ops_pairs_count_s = nullptr;
680static std::map<const char*, uint64_t>* ops_count_s = nullptr;
681static void ProfileOp(const char* op_name) {
682 if (!ops_pairs_count_s) {
683 ops_pairs_count_s =
684 new std::map<std::pair<const char*, const char*>, uint64_t>();
685 ops_count_s = new std::map<const char*, uint64_t>();
686 }
687 if (prev_op_name_s) {
688 (*ops_pairs_count_s)[{prev_op_name_s, op_name}]++;
689 }
690 (*ops_count_s)[op_name]++;
691 prev_op_name_s = op_name;
692}
693
694template <typename A, typename B>
695std::pair<B, A> flip_pair(const std::pair<A, B>& p) {
696 return std::pair<B, A>(p.second, p.first);
697}
698template <typename A, typename B>
699std::multimap<B, A> flip_map(const std::map<A, B>& src) {
700 std::multimap<B, A> dst;
701 std::transform(src.begin(), src.end(), std::inserter(dst, dst.begin()),
702 flip_pair<A, B>);
703 return dst;
704}
705
706static void PrintOpsCount() {
707 std::multimap<uint64_t, const char*> count_ops_map = flip_map(*ops_count_s);
708 uint64_t total_count = 0;
709 for (auto& pair : count_ops_map) {
710 printf("%10lld, %s\n", pair.first, pair.second);
711 total_count += pair.first;
712 }
713 printf("Total count: %10lld\n\n", total_count);
714
715 std::multimap<uint64_t, std::pair<const char*, const char*>>
716 count_pairs_ops_map = flip_map(*ops_pairs_count_s);
717 for (auto& pair : count_pairs_ops_map) {
718 printf("%10lld, %s -> %s\n", pair.first, pair.second.first,
719 pair.second.second);
720 }
721}
722
723static void PrintAndClearProfilingData() {
724 PrintOpsCount();
725 delete ops_count_s;
726 ops_count_s = nullptr;
727 delete ops_pairs_count_s;
728 ops_pairs_count_s = nullptr;
729}
730
731#define NextOp() \
732 ProfileOp(__FUNCTION__); \
733 MUSTTAIL return kInstructionTable[ReadFnId(code) & kInstructionTableMask]( \
734 code, sp, wasm_runtime, r0, fp0)
735
736#else // DRUMBRAKE_ENABLE_PROFILING
737
738#define NextOp() \
739 MUSTTAIL return kInstructionTable[ReadFnId(code) & kInstructionTableMask]( \
740 code, sp, wasm_runtime, r0, fp0)
741
742#endif // DRUMBRAKE_ENABLE_PROFILING

744static int StructFieldOffset(const StructType* struct_type, int field_index) {
745 return wasm::ObjectAccess::ToTagged(WasmStruct::kHeaderSize +
746 struct_type->field_offset(field_index));
747}

749InstructionHandler s_unwind_code = InstructionHandler::k_s2s_Unwind;
750
751class HandlersBase {
752 public:
753 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Unreachable(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
754 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
755 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
756 MUSTTAIL return HandlersBase::Trap(code, sp, wasm_runtime,
757 TrapReason::kTrapUnreachable, fp0);
758 }
759
760 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC
761 s2s_Unwind(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
762 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, int64_t r0, double fp0) {
763 // Break the chain of calls.
764 }
765
766 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC Trap(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
767 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
768 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
769 TrapReason trap_reason = static_cast<TrapReason>(r0);
770 wasm_runtime->SetTrap(trap_reason, code);
771 MUSTTAIL return s_unwind_func_addr(code, sp, wasm_runtime, trap_reason, .0);
772 }
773
774 static constexpr PWasmOp* s_unwind_func_addr = HandlersBase::s2s_Unwind;
775};
776
777#define TRAP(trap_reason) \
778 MUSTTAIL return HandlersBase::Trap(code, sp, wasm_runtime, trap_reason, fp0);
779
780#define INLINED_TRAP(trap_reason) \
781 wasm_runtime->SetTrap(trap_reason, code); \
782 MUSTTAIL return s_unwind_func_addr(code, sp, wasm_runtime, trap_reason, .0);
783
784template <bool Compressed>
785class Handlers : public HandlersBase {
786 using traits = handler_traits<Compressed>;
787 using slot_offset_t = traits::slot_offset_t;
788 using memory_offset32_t = traits::memory_offset32_t;
789 using memory_offset64_t = traits::memory_offset64_t;
790
791 public:
792 template <typename T>
793 static inline T Read(const uint8_t*& code) {
794 T res = base::ReadUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(code));
795 code += sizeof(T);
796 return res;
797 }
798 template <>
799 slot_offset_t Read<slot_offset_t>(const uint8_t*& code) {
800 slot_offset_t res = base::ReadUnalignedValue<slot_offset_t>(
801 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code));
802#if V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
803 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
804 printf("Read slot_offset_t %d\n", res);
805 }
806#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
807 code += sizeof(slot_offset_t);
808 return res;
809 }
810
811 // Returns the maximum of the two parameters according to JavaScript
812 // semantics.
813 template <typename T>
814 static inline T JSMax(T x, T y) {
815 if (std::isnan(x) || std::isnan(y)) {
816 return std::numeric_limits<T>::quiet_NaN();
817 }
818 if (std::signbit(x) < std::signbit(y)) return x;
819 return x > y ? x : y;
820 }
821
822 // Returns the minimum of the two parameters according to JavaScript
823 // semantics.
824 template <typename T>
825 static inline T JSMin(T x, T y) {
826 if (std::isnan(x) || std::isnan(y)) {
827 return std::numeric_limits<T>::quiet_NaN();
828 }
829 if (std::signbit(x) < std::signbit(y)) return y;
830 return x > y ? y : x;
831 }
832
833 static inline uint8_t* ReadMemoryAddress(uint8_t*& code) {
834 Address res =
835 base::ReadUnalignedValue<Address>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(code));
836 code += sizeof(Address);
837 return reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(res);
838 }
839
840 static inline uint32_t ReadGlobalIndex(const uint8_t*& code) {
841 uint32_t res =
842 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(code));
843 code += sizeof(uint32_t);
844 return res;
845 }
846
847 template <typename T>
848 static inline void push(uint32_t*& sp, const uint8_t*& code,
849 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, T val) {
850 slot_offset_t offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
851 base::WriteUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + offset), val);
852#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
853 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution)
854 wasm_runtime->TracePush<T>(offset * kSlotSize);
855#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
856 }
857
858 template <>
859 inline void push(uint32_t*& sp, const uint8_t*& code,
860 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, WasmRef ref) {
861 slot_offset_t offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
862 uint32_t ref_stack_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
863 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint64_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + offset),
864 kSlotsZapValue);
865 wasm_runtime->StoreWasmRef(ref_stack_index, ref);
866#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
867 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution)
868 wasm_runtime->TracePush<WasmRef>(offset * kSlotSize);
869#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
870 }
871
872 template <typename T>
873 static inline T pop(uint32_t*& sp, const uint8_t*& code,
874 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime) {
875 slot_offset_t offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
876#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
877 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) wasm_runtime->TracePop();
878#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
879 return base::ReadUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + offset));
880 }
881
882 template <>
883 inline WasmRef pop(uint32_t*& sp, const uint8_t*& code,
884 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime) {
885 uint32_t ref_stack_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
886#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
887 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) wasm_runtime->TracePop();
888#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
889 return wasm_runtime->ExtractWasmRef(ref_stack_index);
890 }
891
892 template <typename T>
893 static inline T ExecuteRemS(T lval, T rval) {
894 if (rval == -1) return 0;
895 return lval % rval;
896 }
897
898 template <typename T>
899 static inline T ExecuteRemU(T lval, T rval) {
900 return lval % rval;
901 }

904 // GlobalGet
905
906 template <typename IntT>
907 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2r_GlobalGetI(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
908 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
909 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
910 uint32_t index = ReadGlobalIndex(code);
911 uint8_t* src_addr = wasm_runtime->GetGlobalAddress(index);
912 r0 = base::ReadUnalignedValue<IntT>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(src_addr));
913
914 NextOp();
915 }
916 static auto constexpr s2r_I32GlobalGet = s2r_GlobalGetI<int32_t>;
917 static auto constexpr s2r_I64GlobalGet = s2r_GlobalGetI<int64_t>;
918
919 template <typename FloatT>
920 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2r_GlobalGetF(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
921 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
922 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
923 uint32_t index = ReadGlobalIndex(code);
924 uint8_t* src_addr = wasm_runtime->GetGlobalAddress(index);
925 fp0 = base::ReadUnalignedValue<FloatT>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(src_addr));
926
927 NextOp();
928 }
929 static auto constexpr s2r_F32GlobalGet = s2r_GlobalGetF<float>;
930 static auto constexpr s2r_F64GlobalGet = s2r_GlobalGetF<double>;
931
932 template <typename T>
933 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_GlobalGet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
934 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
935 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
936 uint32_t index = ReadGlobalIndex(code);
937 uint8_t* src_addr = wasm_runtime->GetGlobalAddress(index);
938 push<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime,
939 base::ReadUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(src_addr)));
940
941 NextOp();
942 }
943 static auto constexpr s2s_I32GlobalGet = s2s_GlobalGet<int32_t>;
944 static auto constexpr s2s_I64GlobalGet = s2s_GlobalGet<int64_t>;
945 static auto constexpr s2s_F32GlobalGet = s2s_GlobalGet<float>;
946 static auto constexpr s2s_F64GlobalGet = s2s_GlobalGet<double>;
947 static auto constexpr s2s_S128GlobalGet = s2s_GlobalGet<Simd128>;
948
949 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefGlobalGet(
950 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
951 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
952 uint32_t index = ReadGlobalIndex(code);
953 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, wasm_runtime->GetGlobalRef(index));
954
955 NextOp();
956 }

1009 NextOp();

1055 // LoadMem
1056
1057 template <typename IntT, typename IntU = IntT, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
1058 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
1059 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_LoadMemI(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1060 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1061 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1062 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1063 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
1064 MemIdx index = static_cast<MemIdx>(r0);
1065 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
1066
1067 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1068 effective_index < index ||
1069 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(IntU),
1070 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1071 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1072 }
1073
1074 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
1075
1076 IntU value =
1077 base::ReadUnalignedValue<IntU>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
1078 r0 = static_cast<IntT>(value);
1079
1080 NextOp();
1081 }
1082 static auto constexpr r2r_I32LoadMem8S_Idx64 =
1083 r2r_LoadMemI<int32_t, int8_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1084 static auto constexpr r2r_I32LoadMem8U_Idx64 =
1085 r2r_LoadMemI<int32_t, uint8_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1086 static auto constexpr r2r_I32LoadMem16S_Idx64 =
1087 r2r_LoadMemI<int32_t, int16_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1088 static auto constexpr r2r_I32LoadMem16U_Idx64 =
1089 r2r_LoadMemI<int32_t, uint16_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1090 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem8S_Idx64 =
1091 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, int8_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1092 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem8U_Idx64 =
1093 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, uint8_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1094 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem16S_Idx64 =
1095 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, int16_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1096 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem16U_Idx64 =
1097 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, uint16_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1098 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem32S_Idx64 =
1099 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, int32_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1100 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem32U_Idx64 =
1101 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, uint32_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1102 static auto constexpr r2r_I32LoadMem_Idx64 =
1103 r2r_LoadMemI<int32_t, int32_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1104 static auto constexpr r2r_I64LoadMem_Idx64 =
1105 r2r_LoadMemI<int64_t, int64_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1106
1107 template <typename FloatT, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
1108 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
1109 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_LoadMemF(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1110 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1111 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1112 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1113 MemOffsetT offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
1114 MemIdx index = static_cast<MemIdx>(r0);
1115 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
1116
1117 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1118 effective_index < index ||
1119 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(FloatT),
1120 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1121 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1122 }
1123
1124 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
1125
1126 fp0 = base::ReadUnalignedValue<FloatT>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
1127
1128 NextOp();
1129 }
1130 static auto constexpr r2r_F32LoadMem_Idx64 =
1131 r2r_LoadMemF<float, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1132 static auto constexpr r2r_F64LoadMem_Idx64 =
1133 r2r_LoadMemF<double, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1134
1135 template <typename T, typename U = T, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
1136 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
1137 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_LoadMem(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1138 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1139 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1140 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1141 MemOffsetT offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
1142 MemIdx index = static_cast<MemIdx>(r0);
1143 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
1144
1145 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1146 effective_index < index ||
1147 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(U),
1148 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1149 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1150 }
1151

1322 template <typename T, typename U = T, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
1323 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
1324 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_LoadMem_LocalSet(
1325 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1326 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1327 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1328 MemOffsetT offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
1329 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1330 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
1331
1332 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1333 effective_index < index ||
1334 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(U),
1335 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1336 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1337 }

1339 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
1340
1341 U value = base::ReadUnalignedValue<U>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
1342
1343 slot_offset_t to = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
1344 base::WriteUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to),
1345 static_cast<T>(value));
1346
1347 NextOp();
1348 }

1499 // LoadStoreMem
1500 template <typename T, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
1501 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
1502 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_LoadStoreMem(
1503 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1504 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1505 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1506
1507 MemOffsetT load_offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
1508 uint64_t load_index = r0;
1509 uint64_t effective_load_index = load_offset + load_index;
1510
1511 MemOffsetT store_offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
1512 uint64_t store_index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1513 uint64_t effective_store_index = store_offset + store_index;
1514
1515 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1516 effective_load_index < load_index ||
1517 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_load_index, sizeof(T),
1518 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()) ||
1519 effective_store_index < store_offset ||
1520 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_store_index, sizeof(T),
1521 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1522 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1523 }
1524
1525 uint8_t* load_address = memory_start + effective_load_index;
1526 uint8_t* store_address = memory_start + effective_store_index;
1527
1528 base::WriteUnalignedValue<T>(
1529 reinterpret_cast<Address>(store_address),
1530 base::ReadUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(load_address)));
1531
1532 NextOp();
1533 }
1534 static auto constexpr r2s_I32LoadStoreMem_Idx64 =
1535 r2s_LoadStoreMem<int32_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1536 static auto constexpr r2s_I64LoadStoreMem_Idx64 =
1537 r2s_LoadStoreMem<int64_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1538 static auto constexpr r2s_F32LoadStoreMem_Idx64 =
1539 r2s_LoadStoreMem<float, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
1540 static auto constexpr r2s_F64LoadStoreMem_Idx64 =
1541 r2s_LoadStoreMem<double, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;

1650 // LoadMem_LocalSet
1651
1652 template <typename T, typename U = T>
1653 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet(
1654 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1655 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1656 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1657 memory_offset32_t offset = Read<memory_offset32_t>(code);
1658 uint64_t index = static_cast<uint32_t>(r0);
1659 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
1660
1661 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1662 effective_index < index ||
1663 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(U),
1664 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1665 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1666 }
1667
1668 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
1669
1670 U value = base::ReadUnalignedValue<U>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
1671
1672 slot_offset_t to = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
1673 base::WriteUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to),
1674 static_cast<T>(value));
1675
1676 NextOp();
1677 }
1678 static auto constexpr r2s_I32LoadMem8S_LocalSet =
1679 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int32_t, int8_t>;
1680 static auto constexpr r2s_I32LoadMem8U_LocalSet =
1681 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int32_t, uint8_t>;
1682 static auto constexpr r2s_I32LoadMem16S_LocalSet =
1683 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int32_t, int16_t>;
1684 static auto constexpr r2s_I32LoadMem16U_LocalSet =
1685 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int32_t, uint16_t>;
1686 static auto constexpr r2s_I64LoadMem8S_LocalSet =
1687 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int64_t, int8_t>;
1688 static auto constexpr r2s_I64LoadMem8U_LocalSet =
1689 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int64_t, uint8_t>;
1690 static auto constexpr r2s_I64LoadMem16S_LocalSet =
1691 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int64_t, int16_t>;
1692 static auto constexpr r2s_I64LoadMem16U_LocalSet =
1693 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int64_t, uint16_t>;

1695 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int64_t, int32_t>;
1696 static auto constexpr r2s_I64LoadMem32U_LocalSet =
1697 r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet<int64_t, uint32_t>;

1752 // LocalGet_StoreMem
1753
1754 template <typename T, typename U = T>
1755 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem(
1756 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1757 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1758 slot_offset_t from = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
1759 T value = base::ReadUnalignedValue<T>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + from));
1760
1761 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
1762 memory_offset32_t offset = Read<memory_offset32_t>(code);
1763 uint64_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1764 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
1765
1766 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
1767 effective_index < index ||
1768 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(U),
1769 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
1770 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
1771 }
1772
1773 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
1774
1775 base::WriteUnalignedValue<U>(
1776 reinterpret_cast<Address>(address),
1777 base::ReadUnalignedValue<U>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(&value)));
1778
1779 NextOp();
1780 }
1781 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I32StoreMem8 =
1782 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int32_t, int8_t>;
1783 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I32StoreMem16 =
1784 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int32_t, int16_t>;
1785 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I64StoreMem8 =
1786 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int64_t, int8_t>;
1787 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I64StoreMem16 =
1788 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int64_t, int16_t>;
1789 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I64StoreMem32 =
1790 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int64_t, int32_t>;
1791 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I32StoreMem =
1792 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int32_t>;
1793 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_I64StoreMem =
1794 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<int64_t>;
1795 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_F32StoreMem = s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<float>;
1796 static auto constexpr s2s_LocalGet_F64StoreMem =
1797 s2s_LocalGet_StoreMem<double>;

1814 // Select
1815
1816 template <typename IntT>
1817 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_SelectI(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1818 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1819 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1820 IntT val2 = pop<IntT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1821 IntT val1 = pop<IntT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1822
1823 // r0: condition
1824 r0 = r0 ? val1 : val2;
1825
1826 NextOp();
1827 }
1828 static auto constexpr r2r_I32Select = r2r_SelectI<int32_t>;
1829 static auto constexpr r2r_I64Select = r2r_SelectI<int64_t>;
1830
1831 template <typename FloatT>
1832 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_SelectF(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1833 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1834 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1835 FloatT val2 = pop<FloatT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1836 FloatT val1 = pop<FloatT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1837
1838 // r0: condition
1839 fp0 = r0 ? val1 : val2;
1840
1841 NextOp();
1842 }
1843 static auto constexpr r2r_F32Select = r2r_SelectF<float>;
1844 static auto constexpr r2r_F64Select = r2r_SelectF<double>;
1845
1846 template <typename T>
1847 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_Select(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1848 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1849 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1850 T val2 = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1851 T val1 = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1852
1853 push<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, r0 ? val1 : val2);
1854
1855 NextOp();
1856 }
1857 static auto constexpr r2s_I32Select = r2s_Select<int32_t>;
1858 static auto constexpr r2s_I64Select = r2s_Select<int64_t>;

1860 static auto constexpr r2s_F64Select = r2s_Select<double>;
1861 static auto constexpr r2s_S128Select = r2s_Select<Simd128>;

1863 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_RefSelect(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1864 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1865 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1866 WasmRef val2 = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1867 WasmRef val1 = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1868 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, r0 ? val1 : val2);
1869
1870 NextOp();
1871 }

1873 template <typename IntT>
1874 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2r_SelectI(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
1875 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1876 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1877 int32_t cond = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1878 IntT val2 = pop<IntT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1879 IntT val1 = pop<IntT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1880
1881 r0 = cond ? val1 : val2;
1882
1883 NextOp();
1884 }
1885 static auto constexpr s2r_I32Select = s2r_SelectI<int32_t>;
1886 static auto constexpr s2r_I64Select = s2r_SelectI<int64_t>;

1893 FloatT val2 = pop<FloatT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1894 FloatT val1 = pop<FloatT>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);

1903 template <typename T>

1905 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
1906 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
1907 int32_t cond = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1908 T val2 = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1909 T val1 = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
1910
1911 push<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, cond ? val1 : val2);
1912
1913 NextOp();
1914 }

1933 // Binary arithmetic operators
1934
1935#define FOREACH_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(V) \
1936 V(I32Add, uint32_t, r0, +, I32) \
1937 V(I32Sub, uint32_t, r0, -, I32) \
1938 V(I32Mul, uint32_t, r0, *, I32) \
1939 V(I32And, uint32_t, r0, &, I32) \
1940 V(I32Ior, uint32_t, r0, |, I32) \
1941 V(I32Xor, uint32_t, r0, ^, I32) \
1942 V(I64Add, uint64_t, r0, +, I64) \
1943 V(I64Sub, uint64_t, r0, -, I64) \
1944 V(I64Mul, uint64_t, r0, *, I64) \
1945 V(I64And, uint64_t, r0, &, I64) \
1946 V(I64Ior, uint64_t, r0, |, I64) \
1947 V(I64Xor, uint64_t, r0, ^, I64) \
1948 V(F32Add, float, fp0, +, F32) \
1949 V(F32Sub, float, fp0, -, F32) \
1950 V(F32Mul, float, fp0, *, F32) \
1951 V(F32Div, float, fp0, /, F32) \
1952 V(F64Add, double, fp0, +, F64) \
1953 V(F64Sub, double, fp0, -, F64) \
1954 V(F64Mul, double, fp0, *, F64) \
1955 V(F64Div, double, fp0, /, F64)
1956
1957#define DEFINE_BINOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \
1958 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
1959 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
1960 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
1961 ctype rval = static_cast<ctype>(reg); \
1962 ctype lval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
1963 reg = static_cast<ctype>(lval op rval); \
1964 NextOp(); \
1965 } \
1966 \
1967 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
1968 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
1969 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
1970 ctype rval = static_cast<ctype>(reg); \
1971 ctype lval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
1972 push<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, lval op rval); \
1973 NextOp(); \
1974 } \
1975 \
1976 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2r_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
1977 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
1978 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
1979 ctype rval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
1980 ctype lval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
1981 reg = static_cast<ctype>(lval op rval); \
1982 NextOp(); \
1983 } \
1984 \
1985 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
1986 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
1987 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
1988 ctype rval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
1989 ctype lval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
1990 push<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, lval op rval); \
1991 NextOp(); \
1992 }

2012
2013#define FOREACH_TRAPPING_BINOP(V) \
2014 FOREACH_SIGNED_DIV_BINOP(V) \
2015 FOREACH_UNSIGNED_DIV_BINOP(V) \
2016 FOREACH_REM_BINOP(V)
2017
2018#define DEFINE_BINOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \
2019 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
2020 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
2021 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
2022 ctype rval = static_cast<ctype>(reg); \
2023 ctype lval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
2024 if (rval == 0) { \
2025 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapDivByZero) \
2026 } else if (rval == -1 && lval == std::numeric_limits<ctype>::min()) { \
2027 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapDivUnrepresentable) \
2028 } else { \
2029 reg = static_cast<ctype>(lval op rval); \
2030 } \
2031 NextOp(); \
2032 } \
2033 \
2034 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
2035 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
2036 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
2037 ctype rval = static_cast<ctype>(reg); \

2042 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapDivUnrepresentable) \
2043 } else { \
2044 push<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, lval op rval); \
2045 } \
2046 NextOp(); \
2047 } \

2231 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
2232 ctype rval = static_cast<ctype>(reg); \
2233 ctype lval = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
2234 r0 = (lval op rval) ? 1 : 0; \
2235 NextOp(); \
2236 } \

2299 reinterpret_cast<Address>(&rval)) & \
2300 kFloat64SignBitMask)) \
2301 .get_scalar(), \
2302 F64)

2451 V(F64SConvertI64, int64_t, I64, r0, double, F64, fp0) \

2453 V(F64ConvertF32, float, F32, fp0, double, F64, fp0)

2455#define FOREACH_CONVERT_UNOP(V) \
2456 FOREACH_I64_CONVERT_FROM_FLOAT_UNOP(V) \
2457 FOREACH_I32_CONVERT_FROM_FLOAT_UNOP(V) \
2458 FOREACH_OTHER_CONVERT_UNOP(V)
2459
2460#define DEFINE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \
2461 to_reg) \
2462 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2r_##name(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
2463 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
2464 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
2465 if (!base::IsValueInRangeForNumericType<to_ctype>(from_reg)) { \
2466 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapFloatUnrepresentable) \
2467 } else { \
2468 to_reg = static_cast<to_ctype>(static_cast<from_ctype>(from_reg)); \
2469 } \
2470 NextOp(); \
2471 } \
2472 \

2479 to_ctype val = static_cast<from_ctype>(from_reg); \
2480 push<to_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, val); \
2481 } \
2482 NextOp(); \
2483 } \

2796
2797 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_MemoryGrow(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2798 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2799 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2800 uint32_t delta_pages = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
2801
2802 int32_t result = wasm_runtime->MemoryGrow(delta_pages);
2803
2804 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
2805
2806 NextOp();
2807 }
2808
2809 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Memory64Grow(
2810 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2811 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2812 int64_t result = -1;
2813
2814 uint64_t delta_pages = pop<uint64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
2815
2816 if (delta_pages <= std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
2817 result = wasm_runtime->MemoryGrow(static_cast<uint32_t>(delta_pages));
2818 }
2819
2820 push<int64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
2821
2822 NextOp();
2823 }
2824
2825 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_MemorySize(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2826 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2827 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2828 uint64_t result = wasm_runtime->MemorySize();
2829 push<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, static_cast<uint32_t>(result));
2830
2831 NextOp();
2832 }
2833
2834 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Memory64Size(
2835 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2836 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2837 uint64_t result = wasm_runtime->MemorySize();
2838 push<uint64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
2839
2840 NextOp();
2841 }

2843 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Return(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2844 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2845 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2846 // Break the chain of calls.
2847 Read<int32_t>(code);
2848 }
2849
2850 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Branch(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2851 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2852 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2853 int32_t target_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2854 code += (target_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
2855
2856 NextOp();
2857 }
2858
2859 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_BranchIf(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2860 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2861 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2862 int64_t cond = r0;
2863
2864 int32_t if_true_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2865 if (cond) {
2866 // If condition is true, jump to the target branch.
2867 code += (if_true_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
2868 }
2869
2870 NextOp();
2871 }
2872
2873 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_BranchIf(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2874 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2875 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2876 int32_t cond = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
2877
2878 int32_t if_true_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2879 if (cond) {
2880 // If condition is true, jump to the target branch.
2881 code += (if_true_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
2882 }
2883
2884 NextOp();
2885 }
2886
2887 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_BranchIfWithParams(
2888 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2889 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2890 int64_t cond = r0;
2891
2892 int32_t if_false_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2893 if (!cond) {
2894 // If condition is not true, jump to the false branch.
2895 code += (if_false_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
2896 }
2897
2898 NextOp();
2899 }

2948 }

2950 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Catch(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2951 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2952 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2953 int32_t target_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2954 code += (target_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
2955
2956 NextOp();
2957 }
2958
2959 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CallFunction(
2960 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2961 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2962 uint32_t function_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
2963 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
2964 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
2965 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2966 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
2967#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
2968 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
2969 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
2970 }
2971#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
2972
2973 wasm_runtime->ExecuteFunction(code, function_index, stack_pos,
2974 ref_stack_fp_offset, slot_offset,
2975 return_slot_offset);
2976 NextOp();
2977 }
2978
2979 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ReturnCall(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
2980 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
2981 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
2982 slot_offset_t rets_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
2983 slot_offset_t args_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
2984 uint32_t rets_refs = Read<int32_t>(code);
2985 uint32_t args_refs = Read<int32_t>(code);
2986 uint32_t function_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
2987 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
2988 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
2989 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
2990 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
2991#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
2992 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
2993 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
2994 }
2995#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
2996
2997 // Moves back the stack frame to the caller stack frame.
2998 wasm_runtime->UnwindCurrentStackFrame(sp, slot_offset, rets_size, args_size,
2999 rets_refs, args_refs,
3000 ref_stack_fp_offset);
3001
3002 // Do not call wasm_runtime->ExecuteFunction(), which would add a
3003 // new C++ stack frame.
3004 wasm_runtime->PrepareTailCall(code, function_index, stack_pos,
3005 return_slot_offset);
3006 NextOp();
3007 }

3032 slot_offset_t rets_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);

3056
3057 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CallIndirect(
3058 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3059 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3060 uint32_t entry_index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3061 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3062 uint32_t sig_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3063 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
3064 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3065 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
3066 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
3067#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3068 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
3069 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3070 }
3071#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3072
3073 // This function can trap.
3074 wasm_runtime->ExecuteIndirectCall(code, table_index, sig_index, entry_index,
3075 stack_pos, sp, ref_stack_fp_offset,
3076 slot_offset, return_slot_offset, false);
3077 NextOp();
3078 }
3079
3080 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CallIndirect64(
3081 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3082 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3083 uint64_t entry_index_64 = pop<uint64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3084 if (entry_index_64 > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
3085 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapTableOutOfBounds)
3086 }
3087 uint32_t entry_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(entry_index_64);
3088 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3089 uint32_t sig_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3090 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
3091 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3092 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
3093 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
3094#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3095 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
3096 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3097 }
3098#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3099
3100 // This function can trap.
3101 wasm_runtime->ExecuteIndirectCall(code, table_index, sig_index, entry_index,
3102 stack_pos, sp, ref_stack_fp_offset,
3103 slot_offset, return_slot_offset, false);
3104 NextOp();
3105 }

3107 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ReturnCallIndirect(
3108 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3109 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3110 slot_offset_t rets_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3111 slot_offset_t args_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3112 uint32_t rets_refs = Read<int32_t>(code);
3113 uint32_t args_refs = Read<int32_t>(code);
3114 uint32_t entry_index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3115 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3116 uint32_t sig_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3117 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
3118 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3119 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
3120 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
3121#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3122 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
3123 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3124 }
3125#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3126
3127 // Moves back the stack frame to the caller stack frame.
3128 wasm_runtime->UnwindCurrentStackFrame(sp, slot_offset, rets_size, args_size,
3129 rets_refs, args_refs,
3130 ref_stack_fp_offset);
3131
3132 // This function can trap.
3133 wasm_runtime->ExecuteIndirectCall(code, table_index, sig_index, entry_index,
3134 stack_pos, sp, 0, 0, return_slot_offset,
3135 true);
3136 NextOp();
3137 }

3174
3175 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC r2s_BrTable(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3176 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3177 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3178 uint32_t cond = static_cast<int32_t>(r0);
3179
3180 uint32_t table_length = Read<int32_t>(code);
3181 uint32_t index = cond < table_length ? cond : table_length;
3182
3183 int32_t target_offset = base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(
3184 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code + index * kCodeOffsetSize));
3185 code += (target_offset + index * kCodeOffsetSize);
3186
3187 NextOp();
3188 }
3189
3190 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_BrTable(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3191 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3192 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3193 uint32_t cond = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3194
3195 uint32_t table_length = Read<int32_t>(code);
3196 uint32_t index = cond < table_length ? cond : table_length;
3197
3198 int32_t target_offset = base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(
3199 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code + index * kCodeOffsetSize));
3200 code += (target_offset + index * kCodeOffsetSize);
3201
3202 NextOp();
3203 }
3204
3205 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CopySlotMulti(
3206 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3207 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3208 uint32_t params_count = Read<int32_t>(code);
3209 DCHECK(params_count > 1 && params_count < 32);
3210
3211 uint32_t arg_size_mask = Read<int32_t>(code);
3212
3213 slot_offset_t to = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3214 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < params_count; i++) {
3215 slot_offset_t from = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3216 bool is_64 = arg_size_mask & (1 << i);
3217 if (is_64) {
3218 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint64_t>(
3219 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to),
3220 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint64_t>(
3221 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + from)));
3222
3223#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3224 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
3225 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
3226 wasm_runtime->Trace("COPYSLOT64 %d %d %" PRIx64 "\n", from, to,
3227 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint64_t>(
3228 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to)));
3229 }
3230#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3231
3232 to += sizeof(uint64_t) / sizeof(uint32_t);
3233 } else {
3234 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
3235 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to),
3236 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
3237 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + from)));
3238
3239#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3240 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
3241 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
3242 wasm_runtime->Trace("COPYSLOT32 %d %d %08x\n", from, to,
3243 *reinterpret_cast<int32_t*>(sp + to));
3244 }
3245#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3246
3247 to += sizeof(uint32_t) / sizeof(uint32_t);
3248 }
3249 }
3250
3251 NextOp();
3252 }
3253
3254 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CopySlot_ll(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3255 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,

3264 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + from0)));

3431 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CopySlot32x2(
3432 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3433 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3434 slot_offset_t from = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3435 slot_offset_t to = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3436 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
3437 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to),
3438 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
3439 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + from)));
3440#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3441 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
3442 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
3443 wasm_runtime->Trace("COPYSLOT32 %d %d %08x\n", from, to,
3444 base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(
3445 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to)));
3446 }
3447#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3448
3449 from = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3450 to = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
3451 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
3452 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to),
3453 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
3454 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + from)));
3455#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3456 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
3457 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
3458 wasm_runtime->Trace("COPYSLOT32 %d %d %08x\n", from, to,
3459 base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(
3460 reinterpret_cast<Address>(sp + to)));
3461 }
3462#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
3463
3464 NextOp();
3465 }

3817 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefNull(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3818 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3819 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3820 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
3821 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
3822
3823 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime,
3824 handle(wasm_runtime->GetNullValue(ref_type),
3825 wasm_runtime->GetIsolate()));
3826
3827 NextOp();
3828 }
3829
3830 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefIsNull(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3831 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3832 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3833 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3834 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(ref) ? 1 : 0);
3835
3836 NextOp();
3837 }

3840 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3841 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3842 uint32_t index = Read<int32_t>(code);

3844
3845 NextOp();
3846 }

3848 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefEq(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3849 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3850 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3851 WasmRef lhs = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3852 WasmRef rhs = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3853 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, lhs.is_identical_to(rhs) ? 1 : 0);
3854
3855 NextOp();
3856 }

3858 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_MemoryInit(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3859 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3860 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3861 uint32_t data_segment_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3862 uint64_t size = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3863 uint64_t src = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3864 uint64_t dst = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3865
3866 // This function can trap.
3867 wasm_runtime->MemoryInit(code, data_segment_index, dst, src, size);
3868
3869 NextOp();
3870 }

3947
3948 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_TableGet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3949 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3950 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3951 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3952 uint32_t entry_index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3953
3954 // This function can trap.
3955 WasmRef ref;
3956 if (wasm_runtime->TableGet(code, table_index, entry_index, &ref)) {
3957 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
3958 }
3959
3960 NextOp();
3961 }

3963 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Table64Get(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
3964 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
3965 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
3966 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
3967 uint64_t entry_index_64 = pop<uint64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
3968
3969 if (entry_index_64 > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
3970 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapTableOutOfBounds)
3971 }
3972
3973 uint32_t entry_index = static_cast<uint32_t>(entry_index_64);
3974
3975 // This function can trap.
3976 WasmRef ref;
3977 if (wasm_runtime->TableGet(code, table_index, entry_index, &ref)) {
3978 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
3979 }
3980
3981 NextOp();
3982 }

4080 template <typename IntN, typename IntM, typename IntK>
4081 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Table64CopyImpl(
4082 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4083 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4084 uint32_t dst_table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
4085 uint32_t src_table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
4086 auto size_64 = pop<IntK>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4087 auto src_64 = pop<IntM>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4088 auto dst_64 = pop<IntN>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4089
4090 if (src_64 > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() ||
4091 dst_64 > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max() ||
4092 size_64 > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
4093 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapTableOutOfBounds)
4094 }
4095
4096 uint32_t size = static_cast<uint32_t>(size_64);
4097 uint32_t src = static_cast<uint32_t>(src_64);
4098 uint32_t dst = static_cast<uint32_t>(dst_64);
4099
4100 // This function can trap.
4101 wasm_runtime->TableCopy(code, dst_table_index, src_table_index, dst, src,
4102 size);
4103
4104 NextOp();
4105 }
4106 static auto constexpr s2s_Table64Copy_32_64_32 =
4107 s2s_Table64CopyImpl<uint32_t, uint64_t, uint32_t>;
4108 static auto constexpr s2s_Table64Copy_64_32_32 =
4109 s2s_Table64CopyImpl<uint64_t, uint32_t, uint32_t>;
4110 static auto constexpr s2s_Table64Copy_64_64_64 =
4111 s2s_Table64CopyImpl<uint64_t, uint64_t, uint64_t>;

4113 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_TableGrow(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
4114 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4115 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4116 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
4117 uint32_t delta = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4118 WasmRef value = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4119
4120 uint32_t result = wasm_runtime->TableGrow(table_index, delta, value);
4121 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
4122
4123 NextOp();
4124 }
4125
4126 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Table64Grow(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
4127 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4128 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4129 uint32_t table_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
4130 uint64_t delta_64 = pop<uint64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4131 WasmRef value = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4132
4133 if (delta_64 > std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()) {
4134 push<int64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, -1);
4135 } else {
4136 uint32_t delta = static_cast<uint32_t>(delta_64);
4137 uint32_t result = wasm_runtime->TableGrow(table_index, delta, value);
4138 push<int64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime,
4139 static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<int32_t>(result)));
4140 }
4141
4142 NextOp();
4143 }

4221 // Atomics operators
4222
4223 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_AtomicNotify(
4224 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4225 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4226 int32_t val = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4227
4228 uint64_t offset = Read<memory_offset32_t>(code);
4229 uint64_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4230 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
4231 // Check alignment.
4232 const uint32_t align_mask = sizeof(int32_t) - 1;
4233 if (V8_UNLIKELY((effective_index & align_mask) != 0)) {
4234 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnalignedAccess)
4235 }
4236 // Check bounds.
4237 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
4238 effective_index < index ||
4239 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(uint64_t),
4240 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
4241 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
4242 }
4243
4244 int32_t result = wasm_runtime->AtomicNotify(effective_index, val);
4245 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
4246
4247 NextOp();
4248 }
4249
4250 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_I32AtomicWait(
4251 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4252 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4253 int64_t timeout = pop<int64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4254 int32_t val = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4255
4256 uint64_t offset = Read<memory_offset32_t>(code);
4257 uint64_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4258 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
4259 // Check alignment.
4260 const uint32_t align_mask = sizeof(int32_t) - 1;
4261 if (V8_UNLIKELY((effective_index & align_mask) != 0)) {
4262 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnalignedAccess)
4263 }
4264 // Check bounds.
4265 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
4266 effective_index < index ||
4267 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(uint64_t),
4268 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
4269 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
4270 }
4271 // Check atomics wait allowed.
4272 if (!wasm_runtime->AllowsAtomicsWait()) {
4273 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnreachable)
4274 }
4275
4276 int32_t result = wasm_runtime->I32AtomicWait(effective_index, val, timeout);
4277 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
4278
4279 NextOp();
4280 }

4386
4387#define ATOMIC_BINOP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type, operation) \
4388 template <typename MemIdx, typename MemOffsetT> \
4389 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_##name##I(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4390 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4391 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4392 ctype val = static_cast<ctype>(pop<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime)); \
4393 \
4394 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code); \
4395 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4396 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index; \
4397 /* Check alignment. */ \
4398 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsAligned(effective_index, sizeof(ctype)))) { \
4399 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnalignedAccess) \
4400 } \
4401 /* Check bounds. */ \
4402 if (V8_UNLIKELY( \
4403 effective_index < index || \
4404 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(ctype), \
4405 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) { \
4406 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds) \
4407 } \
4408 static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<ctype>) == sizeof(ctype), \
4409 "Size mismatch for types std::atomic<" #ctype \
4410 ">, and " #ctype); \
4411 \
4412 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart(); \
4413 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index; \
4414 op_ctype result = static_cast<op_ctype>( \
4415 operation(reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<ctype>*>(address), val)); \
4416 push<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result); \
4417 NextOp(); \
4418 } \
4419 static auto constexpr s2s_##name = \
4420 s2s_##name##I<uint32_t, memory_offset32_t>; \
4421 static auto constexpr s2s_##name##_Idx64 = \
4422 s2s_##name##I<uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
4423 FOREACH_ATOMIC_BINOP(ATOMIC_BINOP)
4424#undef ATOMIC_BINOP

4426#define FOREACH_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP(V) \
4427 V(I32AtomicCompareExchange, Uint32, uint32_t, I32, uint32_t, I32) \
4428 V(I32AtomicCompareExchange8U, Uint8, uint8_t, I32, uint32_t, I32) \
4429 V(I32AtomicCompareExchange16U, Uint16, uint16_t, I32, uint32_t, I32) \
4430 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange, Uint64, uint64_t, I64, uint64_t, I64) \
4431 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange8U, Uint8, uint8_t, I32, uint64_t, I64) \
4432 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange16U, Uint16, uint16_t, I32, uint64_t, I64) \
4433 V(I64AtomicCompareExchange32U, Uint32, uint32_t, I32, uint64_t, I64)
4434
4435#define ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type) \
4436 template <typename MemIdx = uint32_t, typename MemOffsetT> \
4437 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_##name##I(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4438 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4439 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4440 ctype new_val = static_cast<ctype>(pop<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime)); \
4441 ctype old_val = static_cast<ctype>(pop<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime)); \
4442 \
4443 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code); \
4444 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4445 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index; \
4446 /* Check alignment. */ \
4447 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsAligned(effective_index, sizeof(ctype)))) { \
4448 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnalignedAccess) \
4449 } \
4450 /* Check bounds. */ \
4451 if (V8_UNLIKELY( \
4452 effective_index < index || \
4453 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(ctype), \
4454 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) { \
4455 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds) \
4456 } \
4457 static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<ctype>) == sizeof(ctype), \
4458 "Size mismatch for types std::atomic<" #ctype \
4459 ">, and " #ctype); \
4460 \
4461 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart(); \
4462 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index; \
4463 \
4464 std::atomic_compare_exchange_strong( \
4465 reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<ctype>*>(address), &old_val, new_val); \
4466 push<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, static_cast<op_ctype>(old_val)); \
4467 NextOp(); \
4468 } \
4469 static auto constexpr s2s_##name = \
4470 s2s_##name##I<uint32_t, memory_offset32_t>; \
4471 static auto constexpr s2s_##name##_Idx64 = \
4472 s2s_##name##I<uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
4473 FOREACH_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP(ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP)
4474#undef ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP

4476#define FOREACH_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(V) \
4477 V(I32AtomicLoad, Uint32, uint32_t, I32, uint32_t, I32) \
4478 V(I32AtomicLoad8U, Uint8, uint8_t, I32, uint32_t, I32) \
4479 V(I32AtomicLoad16U, Uint16, uint16_t, I32, uint32_t, I32) \
4480 V(I64AtomicLoad, Uint64, uint64_t, I64, uint64_t, I64) \
4481 V(I64AtomicLoad8U, Uint8, uint8_t, I32, uint64_t, I64) \
4482 V(I64AtomicLoad16U, Uint16, uint16_t, I32, uint64_t, I64) \
4483 V(I64AtomicLoad32U, Uint32, uint32_t, I32, uint64_t, I64)
4484
4485#define ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type) \
4486 template <typename MemIdx = uint32_t, typename MemOffsetT> \
4487 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_##name##I(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4488 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4489 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4490 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code); \
4491 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4492 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index; \
4493 /* Check alignment. */ \
4494 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsAligned(effective_index, sizeof(ctype)))) { \
4495 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnalignedAccess) \
4496 } \
4497 /* Check bounds. */ \
4498 if (V8_UNLIKELY( \
4499 effective_index < index || \
4500 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(ctype), \
4501 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) { \
4502 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds) \
4503 } \
4504 static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<ctype>) == sizeof(ctype), \
4505 "Size mismatch for types std::atomic<" #ctype \
4506 ">, and " #ctype); \
4507 \
4508 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart(); \
4509 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index; \
4510 \
4511 ctype val = \
4512 std::atomic_load(reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<ctype>*>(address)); \
4513 push<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, static_cast<op_ctype>(val)); \
4514 NextOp(); \
4515 } \
4516 static auto constexpr s2s_##name = \
4517 s2s_##name##I<uint32_t, memory_offset32_t>; \
4518 static auto constexpr s2s_##name##_Idx64 = \
4519 s2s_##name##I<uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
4520 FOREACH_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(ATOMIC_LOAD_OP)
4521#undef ATOMIC_LOAD_OP
