4532#define ATOMIC_STORE_OP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type) \
4533 template <typename MemIdx = uint32_t, typename MemOffsetT> \
4534 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_##name##I(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4535 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4536 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4537 ctype val = static_cast<ctype>(pop<op_ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime)); \
4538 \
4539 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code); \
4540 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4541 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index; \
4542 /* Check alignment. */ \
4543 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsAligned(effective_index, sizeof(ctype)))) { \
4544 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapUnalignedAccess) \
4545 } \
4546 /* Check bounds. */ \
4547 if (V8_UNLIKELY( \
4548 effective_index < index || \
4549 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(ctype), \
4550 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) { \
4551 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds) \
4552 } \
4553 static_assert(sizeof(std::atomic<ctype>) == sizeof(ctype), \
4554 "Size mismatch for types std::atomic<" #ctype \
4555 ">, and " #ctype); \
4556 \
4557 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart(); \
4558 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index; \
4559 \
4560 std::atomic_store(reinterpret_cast<std::atomic<ctype>*>(address), val); \
4561 NextOp(); \
4562 } \
4563 static auto constexpr s2s_##name = \
4564 s2s_##name##I<uint32_t, memory_offset32_t>; \
4565 static auto constexpr s2s_##name##_Idx64 = \
4566 s2s_##name##I<uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
4567 FOREACH_ATOMIC_STORE_OP(ATOMIC_STORE_OP)
4568#undef ATOMIC_STORE_OP

4571 // SIMD instructions.
4572
4573#if V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
4574#define LANE(i, type) ((sizeof(type.val) / sizeof(type.val[0])) - (i)-1)
4575#else
4576#define LANE(i, type) (i)
4577#endif

4579#define SPLAT_CASE(format, stype, valType, op_type, num) \
4580 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##format##Splat( \
4581 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4582 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4583 valType v = pop<valType>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4584 stype s; \
4585 for (int i = 0; i < num; i++) s.val[i] = v; \
4586 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(s)); \
4587 NextOp(); \
4588 }
4589 SPLAT_CASE(F64x2, float64x2, double, F64, 2)
4590 SPLAT_CASE(F32x4, float32x4, float, F32, 4)
4591 SPLAT_CASE(I64x2, int64x2, int64_t, I64, 2)
4592 SPLAT_CASE(I32x4, int32x4, int32_t, I32, 4)
4593 SPLAT_CASE(I16x8, int16x8, int32_t, I32, 8)
4594 SPLAT_CASE(I8x16, int8x16, int32_t, I32, 16)
4595#undef SPLAT_CASE

4597#define EXTRACT_LANE_CASE(format, stype, op_type, name) \
4598 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##format##ExtractLane( \
4599 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4600 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4601 uint16_t lane = Read<int16_t>(code); \
4602 DCHECK_LT(lane, 4); \
4603 Simd128 v = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4604 stype s = v.to_##name(); \
4605 push(sp, code, wasm_runtime, s.val[LANE(lane, s)]); \
4606 NextOp(); \
4607 }
4608 EXTRACT_LANE_CASE(F64x2, float64x2, F64, f64x2)
4609 EXTRACT_LANE_CASE(F32x4, float32x4, F32, f32x4)
4610 EXTRACT_LANE_CASE(I64x2, int64x2, I64, i64x2)
4611 EXTRACT_LANE_CASE(I32x4, int32x4, I32, i32x4)
4612#undef EXTRACT_LANE_CASE
4613
4614// Unsigned extracts require a bit more care. The underlying array in Simd128 is
4615// signed (see wasm-value.h), so when casted to uint32_t it will be signed
4616// extended, e.g. int8_t -> int32_t -> uint32_t. So for unsigned extracts, we
4617// will cast it int8_t -> uint8_t -> uint32_t. We add the DCHECK to ensure that
4618// if the array type changes, we know to change this function.
4619#define EXTRACT_LANE_EXTEND_CASE(format, stype, name, sign, extended_type) \
4620 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##format##ExtractLane##sign( \
4621 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4622 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4623 uint16_t lane = Read<int16_t>(code); \
4624 DCHECK_LT(lane, 16); \
4625 Simd128 s = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4626 stype ss = s.to_##name(); \
4627 auto res = ss.val[LANE(lane, ss)]; \
4628 DCHECK(std::is_signed<decltype(res)>::value); \
4629 if (std::is_unsigned<extended_type>::value) { \
4630 using unsigned_type = std::make_unsigned<decltype(res)>::type; \
4631 push(sp, code, wasm_runtime, \
4632 static_cast<extended_type>(static_cast<unsigned_type>(res))); \
4633 } else { \
4634 push(sp, code, wasm_runtime, static_cast<extended_type>(res)); \
4635 } \
4636 NextOp(); \
4637 }
4638 EXTRACT_LANE_EXTEND_CASE(I16x8, int16x8, i16x8, S, int32_t)
4639 EXTRACT_LANE_EXTEND_CASE(I16x8, int16x8, i16x8, U, uint32_t)
4640 EXTRACT_LANE_EXTEND_CASE(I8x16, int8x16, i8x16, S, int32_t)
4641 EXTRACT_LANE_EXTEND_CASE(I8x16, int8x16, i8x16, U, uint32_t)
4642#undef EXTRACT_LANE_EXTEND_CASE
4643
4644#define BINOP_CASE(op, name, stype, count, expr) \
4645 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4646 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4647 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4648 stype s2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4649 stype s1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4650 stype res; \
4651 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
4652 auto a = s1.val[LANE(i, s1)]; \
4653 auto b = s2.val[LANE(i, s2)]; \
4654 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = expr; \
4655 } \
4656 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res)); \
4657 NextOp(); \
4658 }

4730#define UNOP_CASE(op, name, stype, count, expr) \
4731 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4732 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4733 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4734 stype s = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4735 stype res; \
4736 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
4737 auto a = s.val[LANE(i, s)]; \
4738 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = expr; \
4739 } \
4740 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res)); \
4741 NextOp(); \
4742 }

4766 UNOP_CASE(I8x16Abs, i8x16, int8x16, 16, std::abs(a))
4767 UNOP_CASE(I8x16Popcnt, i8x16, int8x16, 16,
4768 base::bits::CountPopulation<uint8_t>(a))

4771#define BITMASK_CASE(op, name, stype, count) \
4772 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4773 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4774 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4775 stype s = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4776 int32_t res = 0; \
4777 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
4778 bool sign = std::signbit(static_cast<double>(s.val[LANE(i, s)])); \
4779 res |= (sign << i); \
4780 } \
4781 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, res); \
4782 NextOp(); \
4783 }
4784 BITMASK_CASE(I8x16BitMask, i8x16, int8x16, 16)
4785 BITMASK_CASE(I16x8BitMask, i16x8, int16x8, 8)
4786 BITMASK_CASE(I32x4BitMask, i32x4, int32x4, 4)
4787 BITMASK_CASE(I64x2BitMask, i64x2, int64x2, 2)
4788#undef BITMASK_CASE

4790#define CMPOP_CASE(op, name, stype, out_stype, count, expr) \
4791 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4792 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4793 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4794 stype s2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4795 stype s1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4796 out_stype res; \
4797 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
4798 auto a = s1.val[LANE(i, s1)]; \
4799 auto b = s2.val[LANE(i, s2)]; \
4800 auto result = expr; \
4801 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = result ? -1 : 0; \
4802 } \
4803 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res)); \
4804 NextOp(); \
4805 }

4869#define REPLACE_LANE_CASE(format, name, stype, ctype, op_type) \
4870 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##format##ReplaceLane( \
4871 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4872 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4873 uint16_t lane = Read<int16_t>(code); \
4874 DCHECK_LT(lane, 16); \
4875 ctype new_val = pop<ctype>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4876 Simd128 simd_val = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4877 stype s = simd_val.to_##name(); \
4878 s.val[LANE(lane, s)] = new_val; \
4879 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(s)); \
4880 NextOp(); \
4881 }
4882 REPLACE_LANE_CASE(F64x2, f64x2, float64x2, double, F64)
4883 REPLACE_LANE_CASE(F32x4, f32x4, float32x4, float, F32)
4884 REPLACE_LANE_CASE(I64x2, i64x2, int64x2, int64_t, I64)
4885 REPLACE_LANE_CASE(I32x4, i32x4, int32x4, int32_t, I32)
4886 REPLACE_LANE_CASE(I16x8, i16x8, int16x8, int32_t, I32)
4887 REPLACE_LANE_CASE(I8x16, i8x16, int8x16, int32_t, I32)
4888#undef REPLACE_LANE_CASE

4890 template <typename MemIdx, typename MemOffsetT>
4891 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdS128LoadMemI(
4892 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4893 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4894 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
4895 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
4896
4897 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4898 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
4899
4900 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
4901 effective_index < index ||
4902 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(Simd128),
4903 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
4904 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
4905 }
4906
4907 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
4908 Simd128 s =
4909 base::ReadUnalignedValue<Simd128>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
4910 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(s));
4911
4912 NextOp();
4913 }
4914 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128LoadMem =
4915 s2s_SimdS128LoadMemI<uint32_t, memory_offset32_t>;
4916 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128LoadMem_Idx64 =
4917 s2s_SimdS128LoadMemI<uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
4918
4919 template <typename MemIdx, typename MemOffsetT>
4920 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdS128StoreMemI(
4921 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4922 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4923 Simd128 val = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4924
4925 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
4926 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
4927
4928 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
4929 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
4930
4931 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
4932 effective_index < index ||
4933 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(Simd128),
4934 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
4935 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
4936 }
4937
4938 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
4939 base::WriteUnalignedValue<Simd128>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address), val);
4940
4941 NextOp();
4942 }
4943 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128StoreMem =
4944 s2s_SimdS128StoreMemI<uint32_t, memory_offset32_t>;
4945 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128StoreMem_Idx64 =
4946 s2s_SimdS128StoreMemI<uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;

4948#define SHIFT_CASE(op, name, stype, count, expr) \
4949 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
4950 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
4951 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
4952 uint32_t shift = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime); \
4953 stype s = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
4954 stype res; \
4955 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
4956 auto a = s.val[LANE(i, s)]; \
4957 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = expr; \
4958 } \
4959 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res)); \
4960 NextOp(); \
4961 }
4962 SHIFT_CASE(I64x2Shl, i64x2, int64x2, 2,

4964 SHIFT_CASE(I64x2ShrS, i64x2, int64x2, 2, a >> (shift % 64))

4966 static_cast<uint64_t>(a) >> (shift % 64))

4968 static_cast<uint32_t>(a) << (shift % 32))
4969 SHIFT_CASE(I32x4ShrS, i32x4, int32x4, 4, a >> (shift % 32))
4970 SHIFT_CASE(I32x4ShrU, i32x4, int32x4, 4,
4971 static_cast<uint32_t>(a) >> (shift % 32))
4972 SHIFT_CASE(I16x8Shl, i16x8, int16x8, 8,
4973 static_cast<uint16_t>(a) << (shift % 16))
4974 SHIFT_CASE(I16x8ShrS, i16x8, int16x8, 8, a >> (shift % 16))
4975 SHIFT_CASE(I16x8ShrU, i16x8, int16x8, 8,
4976 static_cast<uint16_t>(a) >> (shift % 16))
4977 SHIFT_CASE(I8x16Shl, i8x16, int8x16, 16,
4978 static_cast<uint8_t>(a) << (shift % 8))
4979 SHIFT_CASE(I8x16ShrS, i8x16, int8x16, 16, a >> (shift % 8))

4984 template <typename s_type, typename d_type, typename narrow, typename wide,
4985 uint32_t start>
4986 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdExtMul(
4987 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
4988 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
4989 s_type s2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).template to<s_type>();
4990 s_type s1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).template to<s_type>();
4991 auto end = start + (kSimd128Size / sizeof(wide));
4992 d_type res;
4993 uint32_t i = start;
4994 for (size_t dst = 0; i < end; ++i, ++dst) {
4995 // Need static_cast for unsigned narrow types.
4996 res.val[LANE(dst, res)] =
4997 MultiplyLong<wide>(static_cast<narrow>(s1.val[LANE(start, s1)]),
4998 static_cast<narrow>(s2.val[LANE(start, s2)]));
4999 }
5000 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5001 NextOp();
5002 }
5003 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI16x8ExtMulLowI8x16S =
5004 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int8x16, int16x8, int8_t, int16_t, 0>;
5005 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI16x8ExtMulHighI8x16S =
5006 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int8x16, int16x8, int8_t, int16_t, 8>;
5007 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI16x8ExtMulLowI8x16U =
5008 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int8x16, int16x8, uint8_t, uint16_t, 0>;
5009 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI16x8ExtMulHighI8x16U =
5010 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int8x16, int16x8, uint8_t, uint16_t, 8>;
5011 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI32x4ExtMulLowI16x8S =
5012 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int16x8, int32x4, int16_t, int32_t, 0>;
5013 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI32x4ExtMulHighI16x8S =
5014 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int16x8, int32x4, int16_t, int32_t, 4>;
5015 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI32x4ExtMulLowI16x8U =
5016 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int16x8, int32x4, uint16_t, uint32_t, 0>;
5017 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI32x4ExtMulHighI16x8U =
5018 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int16x8, int32x4, uint16_t, uint32_t, 4>;
5019 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI64x2ExtMulLowI32x4S =
5020 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int32x4, int64x2, int32_t, int64_t, 0>;
5021 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI64x2ExtMulHighI32x4S =
5022 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int32x4, int64x2, int32_t, int64_t, 2>;
5023 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI64x2ExtMulLowI32x4U =
5024 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int32x4, int64x2, uint32_t, uint64_t, 0>;
5025 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI64x2ExtMulHighI32x4U =
5026 s2s_DoSimdExtMul<int32x4, int64x2, uint32_t, uint64_t, 2>;
5027#undef EXT_MUL_CASE

5092#define PACK_CASE(op, src_type, name, dst_type, count, dst_ctype) \
5093 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \

5095 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
5096 src_type s2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
5097 src_type s1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
5098 dst_type res; \
5099 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
5100 int64_t v = i < count / 2 ? s1.val[LANE(i, s1)] \
5101 : s2.val[LANE(i - count / 2, s2)]; \
5102 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = base::saturated_cast<dst_ctype>(v); \
5103 } \
5104 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res)); \
5105 NextOp(); \
5106 }
5107 PACK_CASE(I16x8SConvertI32x4, int32x4, i32x4, int16x8, 8, int16_t)
5108 PACK_CASE(I16x8UConvertI32x4, int32x4, i32x4, int16x8, 8, uint16_t)
5109 PACK_CASE(I8x16SConvertI16x8, int16x8, i16x8, int8x16, 16, int8_t)
5110 PACK_CASE(I8x16UConvertI16x8, int16x8, i16x8, int8x16, 16, uint8_t)
5111#undef PACK_CASE
5112
5113 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdSelect(
5114 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5115 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5116 int32x4 bool_val = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i32x4();
5117 int32x4 v2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i32x4();
5118 int32x4 v1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i32x4();
5119 int32x4 res;
5120 for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
5121 res.val[LANE(i, res)] =
5122 v2.val[LANE(i, v2)] ^ ((v1.val[LANE(i, v1)] ^ v2.val[LANE(i, v2)]) &
5123 bool_val.val[LANE(i, bool_val)]);
5124 }
5125 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5126 NextOp();
5127 }
5128 // Do these 5 instructions really have the same implementation?
5129 static constexpr auto s2s_SimdI8x16RelaxedLaneSelect = s2s_DoSimdSelect;
5130 static constexpr auto s2s_SimdI16x8RelaxedLaneSelect = s2s_DoSimdSelect;
5131 static constexpr auto s2s_SimdI32x4RelaxedLaneSelect = s2s_DoSimdSelect;
5132 static constexpr auto s2s_SimdI64x2RelaxedLaneSelect = s2s_DoSimdSelect;
5133 static constexpr auto s2s_SimdS128Select = s2s_DoSimdSelect;
5134
5135 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdI32x4DotI16x8S(
5136 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5137 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5138 int16x8 v2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i16x8();
5139 int16x8 v1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i16x8();
5140 int32x4 res;
5141 for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5142 int32_t lo = (v1.val[LANE(i * 2, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 2, v2)]);
5143 int32_t hi = (v1.val[LANE(i * 2 + 1, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 2 + 1, v2)]);
5144 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = base::AddWithWraparound(lo, hi);
5145 }
5146 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5147 NextOp();
5148 }
5149
5150 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdI16x8DotI8x16I7x16S(
5151 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5152 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5153 int8x16 v2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5154 int8x16 v1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5155 int16x8 res;
5156 for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
5157 int16_t lo = (v1.val[LANE(i * 2, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 2, v2)]);
5158 int16_t hi = (v1.val[LANE(i * 2 + 1, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 2 + 1, v2)]);
5159 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = base::AddWithWraparound(lo, hi);
5160 }
5161 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5162 NextOp();
5163 }
5164
5165 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdI32x4DotI8x16I7x16AddS(
5166 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5167 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5168 int32x4 v3 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i32x4();
5169 int8x16 v2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5170 int8x16 v1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5171 int32x4 res;
5172 for (size_t i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
5173 int32_t a = (v1.val[LANE(i * 4, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 4, v2)]);
5174 int32_t b = (v1.val[LANE(i * 4 + 1, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 4 + 1, v2)]);
5175 int32_t c = (v1.val[LANE(i * 4 + 2, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 4 + 2, v2)]);
5176 int32_t d = (v1.val[LANE(i * 4 + 3, v1)] * v2.val[LANE(i * 4 + 3, v2)]);
5177 int32_t acc = v3.val[LANE(i, v3)];
5178 // a + b + c + d should not wrap
5179 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = base::AddWithWraparound(a + b + c + d, acc);
5180 }
5181 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5182 NextOp();
5183 }
5184
5185 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdI8x16Swizzle(
5186 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5187 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5188 int8x16 v2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5189 int8x16 v1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5190 int8x16 res;
5191 for (size_t i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; ++i) {
5192 int lane = v2.val[LANE(i, v2)];
5193 res.val[LANE(i, res)] =
5194 lane < kSimd128Size && lane >= 0 ? v1.val[LANE(lane, v1)] : 0;
5195 }
5196 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5197 NextOp();
5198 }
5199 static constexpr auto s2s_SimdI8x16RelaxedSwizzle = s2s_SimdI8x16Swizzle;
5200
5201 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdI8x16Shuffle(
5202 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5203 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5204 int8x16 value = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5205 int8x16 v2 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5206 int8x16 v1 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i8x16();
5207 int8x16 res;
5208 for (size_t i = 0; i < kSimd128Size; ++i) {
5209 int lane = value.val[i];
5210 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = lane < kSimd128Size
5211 ? v1.val[LANE(lane, v1)]
5212 : v2.val[LANE(lane - kSimd128Size, v2)];
5213 }
5214 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5215 NextOp();
5216 }

5218 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_SimdV128AnyTrue(
5219 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5220 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5221 int32x4 s = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i32x4();
5222 bool res = s.val[LANE(0, s)] | s.val[LANE(1, s)] | s.val[LANE(2, s)] |
5223 s.val[LANE(3, s)];
5224 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, res);
5225 NextOp();
5226 }

5228#define REDUCTION_CASE(op, name, stype, count) \
5229 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
5230 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
5231 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
5232 stype s = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
5233 bool res = true; \
5234 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; ++i) { \
5235 res = res & static_cast<bool>(s.val[LANE(i, s)]); \
5236 } \
5237 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, res); \
5238 NextOp(); \
5239 }
5240 REDUCTION_CASE(I64x2AllTrue, i64x2, int64x2, 2)
5241 REDUCTION_CASE(I32x4AllTrue, i32x4, int32x4, 4)
5242 REDUCTION_CASE(I16x8AllTrue, i16x8, int16x8, 8)
5243 REDUCTION_CASE(I8x16AllTrue, i8x16, int8x16, 16)
5244#undef REDUCTION_CASE
5245
5246#define QFM_CASE(op, name, stype, count, operation) \
5247 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Simd##op(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, \
5248 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, \
5249 int64_t r0, double fp0) { \
5250 stype c = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
5251 stype b = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
5252 stype a = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_##name(); \
5253 stype res; \
5254 for (size_t i = 0; i < count; i++) { \
5255 res.val[LANE(i, res)] = \
5256 operation(a.val[LANE(i, a)] * b.val[LANE(i, b)]) + \
5257 c.val[LANE(i, c)]; \
5258 } \
5259 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res)); \
5260 NextOp(); \
5261 }
5262 QFM_CASE(F32x4Qfma, f32x4, float32x4, 4, +)
5263 QFM_CASE(F32x4Qfms, f32x4, float32x4, 4, -)
5264 QFM_CASE(F64x2Qfma, f64x2, float64x2, 2, +)
5265 QFM_CASE(F64x2Qfms, f64x2, float64x2, 2, -)
5266#undef QFM_CASE

5268 template <typename s_type, typename load_type>
5269 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdLoadSplat(
5270 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5271 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5272 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
5273 uint64_t offset = Read<memory_offset32_t>(code);
5274
5275 uint64_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5276 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
5277
5278 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5279 effective_index < index ||
5280 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(load_type),
5281 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
5282 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
5283 }
5284
5285 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
5286 load_type v =
5287 base::ReadUnalignedValue<load_type>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
5288 s_type s;
5289 for (size_t i = 0; i < arraysize(s.val); i++) {
5290 s.val[LANE(i, s)] = v;
5291 }
5292 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(s));
5293
5294 NextOp();
5295 }
5296 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load8Splat =
5297 s2s_DoSimdLoadSplat<int8x16, int8_t>;
5298 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load16Splat =
5299 s2s_DoSimdLoadSplat<int16x8, int16_t>;
5300 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load32Splat =
5301 s2s_DoSimdLoadSplat<int32x4, int32_t>;
5302 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load64Splat =
5303 s2s_DoSimdLoadSplat<int64x2, int64_t>;
5304
5305 template <typename s_type, typename wide_type, typename narrow_type>
5306 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend(
5307 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5308 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5309 static_assert(sizeof(wide_type) == sizeof(narrow_type) * 2,
5310 "size mismatch for wide and narrow types");
5311 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
5312 uint64_t offset = Read<memory_offset32_t>(code);
5313
5314 uint64_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5315 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
5316
5317 // Load 8 bytes and sign/zero extend to 16 bytes.
5318 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5319 effective_index < index ||
5320 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(uint64_t),
5321 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
5322 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
5323 }
5324
5325 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
5326 uint64_t v =
5327 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint64_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
5328 constexpr int lanes = kSimd128Size / sizeof(wide_type);
5329 s_type s;
5330 for (int i = 0; i < lanes; i++) {
5331 uint8_t shift = i * (sizeof(narrow_type) * 8);
5332 narrow_type el = static_cast<narrow_type>(v >> shift);
5333 s.val[LANE(i, s)] = static_cast<wide_type>(el);
5334 }
5335 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(s));
5336
5337 NextOp();
5338 }
5339 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load8x8S =
5340 s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend<int16x8, int16_t, int8_t>;
5341 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load8x8U =
5342 s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend<int16x8, uint16_t, uint8_t>;
5343 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load16x4S =
5344 s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend<int32x4, int32_t, int16_t>;
5345 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load16x4U =
5346 s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend<int32x4, uint32_t, uint16_t>;
5347 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load32x2S =
5348 s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend<int64x2, int64_t, int32_t>;
5349 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load32x2U =
5350 s2s_DoSimdLoadExtend<int64x2, uint64_t, uint32_t>;
5351
5352 template <typename s_type, typename load_type>
5353 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdLoadZeroExtend(
5354 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5355 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5356 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
5357 uint64_t offset = Read<uint64_t>(code);
5358
5359 uint64_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5360 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
5361
5362 // Load a single 32-bit or 64-bit element into the lowest bits of a v128
5363 // vector, and initialize all other bits of the v128 vector to zero.
5364 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5365 effective_index < index ||
5366 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(load_type),
5367 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
5368 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
5369 }
5370
5371 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
5372 load_type v =
5373 base::ReadUnalignedValue<load_type>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
5374 s_type s;
5375 // All lanes are 0.
5376 for (size_t i = 0; i < arraysize(s.val); i++) {
5377 s.val[LANE(i, s)] = 0;
5378 }
5379 // Lane 0 is set to the loaded value.
5380 s.val[LANE(0, s)] = v;
5381 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(s));
5382
5383 NextOp();
5384 }
5385 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load32Zero =
5386 s2s_DoSimdLoadZeroExtend<int32x4, uint32_t>;
5387 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load64Zero =
5388 s2s_DoSimdLoadZeroExtend<int64x2, uint64_t>;
5389
5390 template <typename s_type, typename memory_type, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
5391 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
5392 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdLoadLane(
5393 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5394 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5395 s_type value = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).template to<s_type>();
5396
5397 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
5398 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
5399
5400 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5401 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
5402
5403 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5404 effective_index < index ||
5405 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(memory_type),
5406 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
5407 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
5408 }
5409
5410 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
5411 memory_type loaded = base::ReadUnalignedValue<memory_type>(
5412 reinterpret_cast<Address>(address));
5413 uint16_t lane = Read<uint16_t>(code);
5414 value.val[LANE(lane, value)] = loaded;
5415 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(value));
5416
5417 NextOp();
5418 }
5419 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load8Lane =
5420 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int8x16, int8_t>;
5421 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load16Lane =
5422 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int16x8, int16_t>;
5423 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load32Lane =
5424 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int32x4, int32_t>;
5425 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load64Lane =
5426 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int64x2, uint64_t>;
5427 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load8Lane_Idx64 =
5428 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int8x16, int8_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
5429 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load16Lane_Idx64 =
5430 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int16x8, int16_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
5431 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load32Lane_Idx64 =
5432 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int32x4, int32_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
5433 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Load64Lane_Idx64 =
5434 s2s_DoSimdLoadLane<int64x2, int64_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;

5436 template <typename s_type, typename memory_type, typename MemIdx = uint32_t,
5437 typename MemOffsetT = memory_offset32_t>
5438 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdStoreLane(
5439 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5440 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5441 // Extract a single lane, push it onto the stack, then store the lane.
5442 s_type value = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).template to<s_type>();
5443
5444 uint8_t* memory_start = wasm_runtime->GetMemoryStart();
5445 uint64_t offset = Read<MemOffsetT>(code);
5446
5447 uint64_t index = pop<MemIdx>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5448 uint64_t effective_index = offset + index;
5449
5450 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
5451 effective_index < index ||
5452 !base::IsInBounds<uint64_t>(effective_index, sizeof(memory_type),
5453 wasm_runtime->GetMemorySize()))) {
5454 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapMemOutOfBounds)
5455 }
5456 uint8_t* address = memory_start + effective_index;
5457
5458 uint16_t lane = Read<uint16_t>(code);
5459 memory_type res = value.val[LANE(lane, value)];
5460 base::WriteUnalignedValue<memory_type>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(address),
5461 res);
5462
5463 NextOp();
5464 }
5465 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store8Lane =
5466 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int8x16, int8_t>;
5467 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store16Lane =
5468 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int16x8, int16_t>;
5469 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store32Lane =
5470 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int32x4, int32_t>;
5471 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store64Lane =
5472 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int64x2, uint64_t>;
5473 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store8Lane_Idx64 =
5474 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int8x16, int8_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
5475 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store16Lane_Idx64 =
5476 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int16x8, int16_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
5477 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store32Lane_Idx64 =
5478 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int32x4, int32_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;
5479 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdS128Store64Lane_Idx64 =
5480 s2s_DoSimdStoreLane<int64x2, int64_t, uint64_t, memory_offset64_t>;

5482 template <typename DstSimdType, typename SrcSimdType, typename Wide,
5483 typename Narrow>
5484 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_DoSimdExtAddPairwise(
5485 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5486 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5487 constexpr int lanes = kSimd128Size / sizeof(DstSimdType::val[0]);
5488 auto v = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).template to<SrcSimdType>();
5489 DstSimdType res;
5490 for (int i = 0; i < lanes; ++i) {
5491 res.val[LANE(i, res)] =
5492 AddLong<Wide>(static_cast<Narrow>(v.val[LANE(i * 2, v)]),
5493 static_cast<Narrow>(v.val[LANE(i * 2 + 1, v)]));
5494 }
5495 push<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, Simd128(res));
5496
5497 NextOp();
5498 }
5499 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI32x4ExtAddPairwiseI16x8S =
5500 s2s_DoSimdExtAddPairwise<int32x4, int16x8, int32_t, int16_t>;
5501 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI32x4ExtAddPairwiseI16x8U =
5502 s2s_DoSimdExtAddPairwise<int32x4, int16x8, uint32_t, uint16_t>;
5503 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI16x8ExtAddPairwiseI8x16S =
5504 s2s_DoSimdExtAddPairwise<int16x8, int8x16, int16_t, int8_t>;
5505 static auto constexpr s2s_SimdI16x8ExtAddPairwiseI8x16U =
5506 s2s_DoSimdExtAddPairwise<int16x8, int8x16, uint16_t, uint8_t>;
5507
5509
5510 // Allocate, initialize and throw a new exception. The exception values are
5511 // being popped off the operand stack.
5512 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Throw(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
5513 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5514 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5515 Isolate* isolate = wasm_runtime->GetIsolate();
5516 {
5517 HandleScope handle_scope(isolate); // Avoid leaking handles.
5518
5519 uint32_t tag_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
5520
5521 Handle<WasmExceptionPackage> exception_object =
5522 wasm_runtime->CreateWasmExceptionPackage(tag_index);
5523 Handle<FixedArray> encoded_values = Cast<FixedArray>(
5524 WasmExceptionPackage::GetExceptionValues(isolate, exception_object));
5525
5526 // Encode the exception values on the operand stack into the exception
5527 // package allocated above.
5528 const WasmTagSig* sig = wasm_runtime->GetWasmTag(tag_index).sig;
5529 uint32_t encoded_index = 0;
5530 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
5531 switch (sig->GetParam(index).kind()) {
5532 case kI32: {
5533 uint32_t u32 = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5534 EncodeI32ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index, u32);
5535 break;
5536 }
5537 case kF32: {
5538 float f32 = pop<float>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5539 EncodeI32ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index,
5540 *reinterpret_cast<uint32_t*>(&f32));
5541 break;
5542 }
5543 case kI64: {
5544 uint64_t u64 = pop<uint64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5545 EncodeI64ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index, u64);
5546 break;
5547 }
5548 case kF64: {
5549 double f64 = pop<double>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5550 EncodeI64ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index,
5551 *reinterpret_cast<uint64_t*>(&f64));
5552 break;
5553 }
5554 case kS128: {
5555 int32x4 s128 = pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime).to_i32x4();
5556 EncodeI32ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index,
5557 s128.val[0]);
5558 EncodeI32ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index,
5559 s128.val[1]);
5560 EncodeI32ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index,
5561 s128.val[2]);
5562 EncodeI32ExceptionValue(encoded_values, &encoded_index,
5563 s128.val[3]);
5564 break;
5565 }
5566 case kRef:
5567 case kRefNull: {
5568 Handle<Object> ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5569 if (IsWasmNull(*ref, isolate)) {
5570 ref = handle(ReadOnlyRoots(isolate).null_value(), isolate);
5571 }
5572 encoded_values->set(encoded_index++, *ref);
5573 break;
5574 }
5575 default:
5576 UNREACHABLE();
5577 }
5578 }
5579
5580 wasm_runtime->ThrowException(code, sp, *exception_object);
5581 }
5582 NextOp();
5583 }
5584
5585 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_Rethrow(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
5586 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5587 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5588 uint32_t catch_block_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
5589 wasm_runtime->RethrowException(code, sp, catch_block_index);
5590
5591 NextOp();
5592 }
5593
5595 // GC instruction handlers.
5596
5597 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_BranchOnNull(
5598 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5599 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5600 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): Implement peek<T>?
5601 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5602
5603 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
5604 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
5605
5606 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
5607
5608 int32_t if_null_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
5609 if (wasm_runtime->IsNullTypecheck(ref, ref_type)) {
5610 // If condition is true (ref is null), jump to the target branch.
5611 code += (if_null_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
5612 }
5613
5614 NextOp();
5615 }
5616
5617 /*
5618 * Notice that in s2s_BranchOnNullWithParams the branch happens when the
5619 * condition is false, not true, as follows:
5620 *
5621 * > s2s_BranchOnNullWithParams
5622 * pop - ref
5623 * i32: ref value_tye
5624 * push - ref
5625 * branch_offset (if NOT NULL) ----+
5626 * > s2s_CopySlot |
5627 * .... |
5628 * > s2s_Branch (gets here if NULL) |
5629 * branch_offset |
5630 * > (next instruction) <---------------+
5631 */
5632 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_BranchOnNullWithParams(
5633 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5634 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5635 // TO(paolosev@microsoft.com): Implement peek<T>?
5636 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5637
5638 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
5639 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
5640
5641 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
5642
5643 int32_t if_null_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
5644 if (!wasm_runtime->IsNullTypecheck(ref, ref_type)) {
5645 // If condition is false (ref is not null), jump to the false branch.
5646 code += (if_null_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
5647 }
5648
5649 NextOp();
5650 }

5691
5692 static bool DoRefCast(WasmRef ref, ValueType ref_type, HeapType target_type,
5693 bool null_succeeds,
5694 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime) {
5695 if (target_type.is_index()) {
5696 Handle<Map> rtt = wasm_runtime->RttCanon(target_type.ref_index().index);
5697 return wasm_runtime->SubtypeCheck(ref, ref_type, rtt,
5698 ValueType::Rtt(target_type.ref_index()),
5699 null_succeeds);
5700 } else {
5701 switch (target_type.representation()) {
5702 case HeapType::kEq:
5703 return wasm_runtime->RefIsEq(ref, ref_type, null_succeeds);
5704 case HeapType::kI31:
5705 return wasm_runtime->RefIsI31(ref, ref_type, null_succeeds);
5706 case HeapType::kStruct:
5707 return wasm_runtime->RefIsStruct(ref, ref_type, null_succeeds);
5708 case HeapType::kArray:
5709 return wasm_runtime->RefIsArray(ref, ref_type, null_succeeds);
5710 case HeapType::kString:
5711 return wasm_runtime->RefIsString(ref, ref_type, null_succeeds);
5712 case HeapType::kNone:
5713 case HeapType::kNoExtern:
5714 case HeapType::kNoFunc:
5715 DCHECK(null_succeeds);
5716 return wasm_runtime->IsNullTypecheck(ref, ref_type);
5717 case HeapType::kAny:
5718 // Any may never need a cast as it is either implicitly convertible or
5719 // never convertible for any given type.
5720 default:
5721 UNREACHABLE();
5722 }
5723 }
5724 }
5725
5726 /*
5727 * Notice that in s2s_BranchOnCast the branch happens when the condition is
5728 * false, not true, as follows:
5729 *
5730 * > s2s_BranchOnCast
5731 * i32: null_succeeds
5732 * i32: target_type HeapType representation
5733 * pop - ref
5734 * i32: ref value_tye
5735 * push - ref
5736 * branch_offset (if CAST FAILS) --------+
5737 * > s2s_CopySlot |
5738 * .... |
5739 * > s2s_Branch (gets here if CAST SUCCEEDS) |
5740 * branch_offset |
5741 * > (next instruction) <--------------------+
5742 */
5743 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_BranchOnCast(
5744 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5745 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5746 bool null_succeeds = Read<int32_t>(code);
5747 HeapType target_type(
5748 ModuleTypeIndex({static_cast<uint32_t>(Read<int32_t>(code))}));
5749
5750 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5751 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
5752 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
5753 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
5754 int32_t no_branch_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
5755
5756 if (!DoRefCast(ref, ref_type, target_type, null_succeeds, wasm_runtime)) {
5757 // If condition is not true, jump to the 'false' branch.
5758 code += (no_branch_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
5759 }
5760
5761 NextOp();
5762 }
5763
5764 /*
5765 * Notice that in s2s_BranchOnCastFail the branch happens when the condition
5766 * is false, not true, as follows:
5767 *
5768 * > s2s_BranchOnCastFail
5769 * i32: null_succeeds
5770 * i32: target_type HeapType representation
5771 * pop - ref
5772 * i32: ref value_tye
5773 * push - ref
5774 * branch_offset (if CAST SUCCEEDS) --+
5775 * > s2s_CopySlot |
5776 * .... |
5777 * > s2s_Branch (gets here if CAST FAILS) |
5778 * branch_offset |
5779 * > (next instruction) <-----------------+
5780 */
5781 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_BranchOnCastFail(
5782 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5783 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5784 bool null_succeeds = Read<int32_t>(code);
5785 HeapType target_type(
5786 ModuleTypeIndex({static_cast<uint32_t>(Read<int32_t>(code))}));
5787
5788 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5789 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
5790 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
5791 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
5792 int32_t branch_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
5793
5794 if (DoRefCast(ref, ref_type, target_type, null_succeeds, wasm_runtime)) {
5795 // If condition is true, jump to the 'true' branch.
5796 code += (branch_offset - kCodeOffsetSize);
5797 }
5798
5799 NextOp();
5800 }
5801
5802 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_CallRef(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
5803 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5804 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5805 WasmRef func_ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5806 uint32_t sig_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
5807 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
5808 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
5809 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
5810 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
5811#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
5812 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
5813 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
5814 }
5815#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
5816
5817 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(func_ref))) {
5818 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
5819 }
5820
5821 // This can trap.
5822 wasm_runtime->ExecuteCallRef(code, func_ref, sig_index, stack_pos, sp,
5823 ref_stack_fp_offset, slot_offset,
5824 return_slot_offset, false);
5825 NextOp();
5826 }
5827
5828 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ReturnCallRef(
5829 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5830 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5831 slot_offset_t rets_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
5832 slot_offset_t args_size = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
5833 uint32_t rets_refs = Read<int32_t>(code);
5834 uint32_t args_refs = Read<int32_t>(code);
5835
5836 WasmRef func_ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5837 uint32_t sig_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
5838 uint32_t stack_pos = Read<int32_t>(code);
5839 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
5840 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
5841 slot_offset_t return_slot_offset = 0;
5842#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
5843 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
5844 return_slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
5845 }
5846#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
5847
5848 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(func_ref))) {
5849 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
5850 }
5851
5852 // Moves back the stack frame to the caller stack frame.
5853 wasm_runtime->UnwindCurrentStackFrame(sp, slot_offset, rets_size, args_size,
5854 rets_refs, args_refs,
5855 ref_stack_fp_offset);
5856
5857 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) - This calls adds a new C++ stack frame,
5858 // which is not ideal in a tail-call.
5859 wasm_runtime->ExecuteCallRef(code, func_ref, sig_index, stack_pos, sp, 0, 0,
5860 return_slot_offset, true);
5861
5862 NextOp();
5863 }
5864
5865 static void StoreRefIntoMemory(Tagged<HeapObject> host, Address dst_addr,
5866 uint32_t offset, Tagged<Object> value,
5867 WriteBarrierMode mode) {
5868 DCHECK_EQ(dst_addr, host.ptr() + offset - kHeapObjectTag);
5869
5870 // Only stores the lower 32-bit.
5871 base::WriteUnalignedValue<Tagged_t>(
5872 dst_addr, V8HeapCompressionScheme::CompressObject(value.ptr()));
5873
5874 // Need to generate a GC write barrier.
5875 CONDITIONAL_WRITE_BARRIER(host, offset, value, mode);
5876 }
5877
5878 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_StructNew(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
5879 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5880 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5881 uint32_t index = Read<int32_t>(code);
5882 std::pair<Handle<WasmStruct>, const StructType*> struct_new_result =
5883 wasm_runtime->StructNewUninitialized(index);
5884 Handle<HeapObject> struct_obj = struct_new_result.first;
5885 const StructType* struct_type = struct_new_result.second;
5886
5887 {
5888 // The new struct is uninitialized, which means GC might fail until
5889 // initialization.
5890 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
5891
5892 for (uint32_t i = struct_type->field_count(); i > 0;) {
5893 i--;
5894 int field_offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, i);
5895 Address field_addr = (*struct_obj).ptr() + field_offset;
5896
5897 ValueKind kind = struct_type->field(i).kind();
5898 switch (kind) {
5899 case kI8:
5900 *reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(field_addr) =
5901 pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5902 break;
5903 case kI16:
5904 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int16_t>(
5905 field_addr, pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
5906 break;
5907 case kI32:
5908 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int32_t>(
5909 field_addr, pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
5910 break;
5911 case kI64:
5912 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int64_t>(
5913 field_addr, pop<int64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
5914 break;
5915 case kF32:
5916 base::WriteUnalignedValue<float>(
5917 field_addr, pop<float>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
5918 break;
5919 case kF64:
5920 base::WriteUnalignedValue<double>(
5921 field_addr, pop<double>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
5922 break;
5923 case kS128:
5924 base::WriteUnalignedValue<Simd128>(
5925 field_addr, pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
5926 break;
5927 case kRef:
5928 case kRefNull: {
5929 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
5930 StoreRefIntoMemory(
5931 *struct_obj, field_addr,
5932 field_offset + kHeapObjectTag, // field_offset is offset into
5933 // tagged object.
5934 *ref, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5935 break;
5936 }
5937 default:
5938 UNREACHABLE();
5939 }
5940 }
5941 }
5942
5943 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, struct_obj);
5944
5945 NextOp();
5946 }
5947
5948 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_StructNewDefault(
5949 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
5950 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
5951 uint32_t index = Read<int32_t>(code);
5952 std::pair<Handle<WasmStruct>, const StructType*> struct_new_result =
5953 wasm_runtime->StructNewUninitialized(index);
5954 Handle<HeapObject> struct_obj = struct_new_result.first;
5955 const StructType* struct_type = struct_new_result.second;
5956
5957 {
5958 // The new struct is uninitialized, which means GC might fail until
5959 // initialization.
5960 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
5961
5962 for (uint32_t i = struct_type->field_count(); i > 0;) {
5963 i--;
5964 int field_offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, i);
5965 Address field_addr = (*struct_obj).ptr() + field_offset;
5966
5967 const ValueType value_type = struct_type->field(i);
5968 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
5969 switch (kind) {
5970 case kI8:
5971 *reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(field_addr) = int8_t{};
5972 break;
5973 case kI16:
5974 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int16_t>(field_addr, int16_t{});
5975 break;
5976 case kI32:
5977 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int32_t>(field_addr, int32_t{});
5978 break;
5979 case kI64:
5980 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int64_t>(field_addr, int64_t{});
5981 break;
5982 case kF32:
5983 base::WriteUnalignedValue<float>(field_addr, float{});
5984 break;
5985 case kF64:
5986 base::WriteUnalignedValue<double>(field_addr, double{});
5987 break;
5988 case kS128:
5989 base::WriteUnalignedValue<Simd128>(field_addr, Simd128{});
5990 break;
5991 case kRef:
5992 case kRefNull:
5993 StoreRefIntoMemory(
5994 *struct_obj, field_addr,
5995 field_offset + kHeapObjectTag, // field_offset is offset into
5996 // tagged object.
5997 wasm_runtime->GetNullValue(value_type), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
5998 break;
5999 default:
6000 UNREACHABLE();
6001 }
6002 }
6003 }
6004
6005 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, struct_obj);
6006
6007 NextOp();
6008 }
6009
6010 template <typename T, typename U = T>
6011 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_StructGet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6012 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6013 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6014 WasmRef struct_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6015
6016 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(struct_obj))) {
6017 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6018 }
6019 int offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
6020 Address field_addr = (*struct_obj).ptr() + offset;
6021 push<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, base::ReadUnalignedValue<U>(field_addr));
6022
6023 NextOp();
6024 }
6025 static auto constexpr s2s_I8SStructGet = s2s_StructGet<int32_t, int8_t>;
6026 static auto constexpr s2s_I8UStructGet = s2s_StructGet<uint32_t, uint8_t>;
6027 static auto constexpr s2s_I16SStructGet = s2s_StructGet<int32_t, int16_t>;
6028 static auto constexpr s2s_I16UStructGet = s2s_StructGet<uint32_t, uint16_t>;
6029 static auto constexpr s2s_I32StructGet = s2s_StructGet<int32_t>;
6030 static auto constexpr s2s_I64StructGet = s2s_StructGet<int64_t>;
6031 static auto constexpr s2s_F32StructGet = s2s_StructGet<float>;
6032 static auto constexpr s2s_F64StructGet = s2s_StructGet<double>;
6033 static auto constexpr s2s_S128StructGet = s2s_StructGet<Simd128>;
6034
6035 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefStructGet(
6036 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6037 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6038 WasmRef struct_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6039 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(struct_obj))) {
6040 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6041 }
6042 int offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
6043 Address field_addr = (*struct_obj).ptr() + offset;
6044 // DrumBrake expects pointer compression.
6045 Tagged_t ref_tagged = base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(field_addr);
6046 Isolate* isolate = wasm_runtime->GetIsolate();
6047 Tagged<Object> ref_uncompressed(
6048 V8HeapCompressionScheme::DecompressTagged(isolate, ref_tagged));
6049 WasmRef ref_handle = handle(ref_uncompressed, isolate);
6050 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref_handle);
6051
6052 NextOp();
6053 }
6054
6055 template <typename T, typename U = T>
6056 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_StructSet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6057 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6058 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6059 int offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
6060 T value = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6061 WasmRef struct_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6062 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(struct_obj))) {
6063 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6064 }
6065 Address field_addr = (*struct_obj).ptr() + offset;
6066 base::WriteUnalignedValue<U>(field_addr, value);
6067
6068 NextOp();
6069 }
6070 static auto constexpr s2s_I8StructSet = s2s_StructSet<int32_t, int8_t>;
6071 static auto constexpr s2s_I16StructSet = s2s_StructSet<int32_t, int16_t>;
6072 static auto constexpr s2s_I32StructSet = s2s_StructSet<int32_t>;
6073 static auto constexpr s2s_I64StructSet = s2s_StructSet<int64_t>;
6074 static auto constexpr s2s_F32StructSet = s2s_StructSet<float>;
6075 static auto constexpr s2s_F64StructSet = s2s_StructSet<double>;
6076 static auto constexpr s2s_S128StructSet = s2s_StructSet<Simd128>;
6077
6078 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefStructSet(
6079 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6080 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6081 int field_offset = Read<int32_t>(code);
6082 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6083 WasmRef struct_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6084 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(struct_obj))) {
6085 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6086 }
6087 Address field_addr = (*struct_obj).ptr() + field_offset;
6088 StoreRefIntoMemory(
6089 Cast<HeapObject>(*struct_obj), field_addr,
6090 field_offset +
6091 kHeapObjectTag, // field_offset is offset into tagged object.
6092 *ref, UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
6093
6094 NextOp();
6095 }
6096
6097 template <typename T, typename U = T>
6098 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayNew(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6099 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6100 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6101 const uint32_t array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6102 const uint32_t elem_count = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6103 const T value = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6104
6105 std::pair<Handle<WasmArray>, const ArrayType*> array_new_result =
6106 wasm_runtime->ArrayNewUninitialized(elem_count, array_index);
6107 Handle<WasmArray> array = array_new_result.first;
6108 if (V8_UNLIKELY(array.is_null())) {
6109 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayTooLarge)
6110 }
6111
6112 {
6113 // The new array is uninitialized, which means GC might fail until
6114 // initialization.
6115 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
6116
6117 const ArrayType* array_type = array_new_result.second;
6118 const ValueKind kind = array_type->element_type().kind();
6119 const uint32_t element_size = value_kind_size(kind);
6120 DCHECK_EQ(element_size, sizeof(U));
6121
6122 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(0);
6123 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elem_count; i++) {
6124 base::WriteUnalignedValue<U>(element_addr, value);
6125 element_addr += element_size;
6126 }
6127 }
6128
6129 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, array);
6130
6131 NextOp();
6132 }
6133 static auto constexpr s2s_I8ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<int32_t, int8_t>;
6134 static auto constexpr s2s_I16ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<int32_t, int16_t>;
6135 static auto constexpr s2s_I32ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<int32_t>;
6136 static auto constexpr s2s_I64ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<int64_t>;
6137 static auto constexpr s2s_F32ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<float>;
6138 static auto constexpr s2s_F64ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<double>;
6139 static auto constexpr s2s_S128ArrayNew = s2s_ArrayNew<Simd128>;
6140
6141 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefArrayNew(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6142 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6143 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6144 const uint32_t array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6145 const uint32_t elem_count = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6146 const WasmRef value = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6147
6148 std::pair<Handle<WasmArray>, const ArrayType*> array_new_result =
6149 wasm_runtime->ArrayNewUninitialized(elem_count, array_index);
6150 Handle<WasmArray> array = array_new_result.first;
6151 if (V8_UNLIKELY(array.is_null())) {
6152 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayTooLarge)
6153 }
6154
6155#if DEBUG
6156 const ArrayType* array_type = array_new_result.second;
6157 DCHECK_EQ(value_kind_size(array_type->element_type().kind()),
6158 sizeof(Tagged_t));
6159#endif
6160
6161 {
6162 // The new array is uninitialized, which means GC might fail until
6163 // initialization.
6164 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
6165
6166 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(0);
6167 uint32_t element_offset = array->element_offset(0);
6168 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elem_count; i++) {
6169 StoreRefIntoMemory(Cast<HeapObject>(*array), element_addr,
6170 element_offset, *value, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
6171 element_addr += sizeof(Tagged_t);
6172 element_offset += sizeof(Tagged_t);
6173 }
6174 }
6175
6176 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, array);
6177
6178 NextOp();
6179 }
6180
6181 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayNewFixed(
6182 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6183 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6184 const uint32_t array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6185 const uint32_t elem_count = Read<int32_t>(code);
6186
6187 std::pair<Handle<WasmArray>, const ArrayType*> array_new_result =
6188 wasm_runtime->ArrayNewUninitialized(elem_count, array_index);
6189 Handle<WasmArray> array = array_new_result.first;
6190 if (V8_UNLIKELY(array.is_null())) {
6191 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayTooLarge)
6192 }
6193
6194 {
6195 // The new array is uninitialized, which means GC might fail until
6196 // initialization.
6197 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
6198
6199 if (elem_count > 0) {
6200 const ArrayType* array_type = array_new_result.second;
6201 const ValueKind kind = array_type->element_type().kind();
6202 const uint32_t element_size = value_kind_size(kind);
6203
6204 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(elem_count - 1);
6205 uint32_t element_offset = array->element_offset(elem_count - 1);
6206 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elem_count; i++) {
6207 switch (kind) {
6208 case kI8:
6209 *reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(element_addr) =
6210 pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6211 break;
6212 case kI16:
6213 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int16_t>(
6214 element_addr, pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
6215 break;
6216 case kI32:
6217 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int32_t>(
6218 element_addr, pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
6219 break;
6220 case kI64:
6221 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int64_t>(
6222 element_addr, pop<int64_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
6223 break;
6224 case kF32:
6225 base::WriteUnalignedValue<float>(
6226 element_addr, pop<float>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
6227 break;
6228 case kF64:
6229 base::WriteUnalignedValue<double>(
6230 element_addr, pop<double>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
6231 break;
6232 case kS128:
6233 base::WriteUnalignedValue<Simd128>(
6234 element_addr, pop<Simd128>(sp, code, wasm_runtime));
6235 break;
6236 case kRef:
6237 case kRefNull: {
6238 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6239 StoreRefIntoMemory(Cast<HeapObject>(*array), element_addr,
6240 element_offset, *ref, SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
6241 break;
6242 }
6243 default:
6244 UNREACHABLE();
6245 }
6246 element_addr -= element_size;
6247 element_offset -= element_size;
6248 }
6249 }
6250 }
6251
6252 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, array);
6253
6254 NextOp();
6255 }
6256
6257 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC
6258 s2s_ArrayNewDefault(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6259 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime, int64_t r0,
6260 double fp0) {
6261 const uint32_t array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6262 const uint32_t elem_count = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6263
6264 std::pair<Handle<WasmArray>, const ArrayType*> array_new_result =
6265 wasm_runtime->ArrayNewUninitialized(elem_count, array_index);
6266 Handle<WasmArray> array = array_new_result.first;
6267 if (V8_UNLIKELY(array.is_null())) {
6268 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayTooLarge)
6269 }
6270
6271 {
6272 // The new array is uninitialized, which means GC might fail until
6273 // initialization.
6274 DisallowHeapAllocation no_gc;
6275
6276 const ArrayType* array_type = array_new_result.second;
6277 const ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type();
6278 const ValueKind kind = element_type.kind();
6279 const uint32_t element_size = value_kind_size(kind);
6280
6281 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(0);
6282 uint32_t element_offset = array->element_offset(0);
6283 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < elem_count; i++) {
6284 switch (kind) {
6285 case kI8:
6286 *reinterpret_cast<int8_t*>(element_addr) = int8_t{};
6287 break;
6288 case kI16:
6289 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int16_t>(element_addr, int16_t{});
6290 break;
6291 case kI32:
6292 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int32_t>(element_addr, int32_t{});
6293 break;
6294 case kI64:
6295 base::WriteUnalignedValue<int64_t>(element_addr, int64_t{});
6296 break;
6297 case kF32:
6298 base::WriteUnalignedValue<float>(element_addr, float{});
6299 break;
6300 case kF64:
6301 base::WriteUnalignedValue<double>(element_addr, double{});
6302 break;
6303 case kS128:
6304 base::WriteUnalignedValue<Simd128>(element_addr, Simd128{});
6305 break;
6306 case kRef:
6307 case kRefNull:
6308 StoreRefIntoMemory(
6309 Cast<HeapObject>(*array), element_addr, element_offset,
6310 wasm_runtime->GetNullValue(element_type), SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER);
6311 break;
6312 default:
6313 UNREACHABLE();
6314 }
6315 element_addr += element_size;
6316 element_offset += element_size;
6317 }
6318 }
6319
6320 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, array);
6321
6322 NextOp();
6323 }
6324
6325 template <TrapReason OutOfBoundsError>
6326 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayNewSegment(
6327 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6328 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6329 const uint32_t array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6330 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): already validated?
6331 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(array_index))) {
6332 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6333 }
6334
6335 const uint32_t data_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6336 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): already validated?
6337 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(data_index))) {
6338 TRAP(OutOfBoundsError)
6339 }
6340
6341 uint32_t length = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6342 uint32_t offset = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6343 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(offset))) {
6344 TRAP(OutOfBoundsError)
6345 }
6346 if (V8_UNLIKELY(length >= static_cast<uint32_t>(WasmArray::MaxLength(
6347 wasm_runtime->GetArrayType(array_index))))) {
6348 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayTooLarge)
6349 }
6350
6351 WasmRef result = wasm_runtime->WasmArrayNewSegment(array_index, data_index,
6352 offset, length);
6353 if (V8_UNLIKELY(result.is_null())) {
6354 wasm::TrapReason reason = WasmInterpreterThread::GetRuntimeLastWasmError(
6355 wasm_runtime->GetIsolate());
6356 INLINED_TRAP(reason)
6357 }
6358 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
6359
6360 NextOp();
6361 }
6362 // The instructions array.new_data and array.new_elem have the same
6363 // implementation after validation. The only difference is that
6364 // array.init_elem is used with arrays that contain elements of reference
6365 // types, and array.init_data with arrays that contain elements of numeric
6366 // types.
6367 static auto constexpr s2s_ArrayNewData =
6368 s2s_ArrayNewSegment<kTrapDataSegmentOutOfBounds>;
6369 static auto constexpr s2s_ArrayNewElem =
6370 s2s_ArrayNewSegment<kTrapElementSegmentOutOfBounds>;
6371
6372 template <bool init_data>
6373 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayInitSegment(
6374 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6375 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6376 const uint32_t array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6377 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): already validated?
6378 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(array_index))) {
6379 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6380 }
6381
6382 const uint32_t data_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6383 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): already validated?
6384 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(data_index))) {
6385 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapElementSegmentOutOfBounds)
6386 }
6387
6388 uint32_t size = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6389 uint32_t src_offset = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6390 uint32_t dest_offset = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6391 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(size)) || !Smi::IsValid(dest_offset)) {
6392 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6393 }
6394 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(src_offset))) {
6395 TrapReason reason = init_data
6396 ? TrapReason::kTrapDataSegmentOutOfBounds
6397 : TrapReason::kTrapElementSegmentOutOfBounds;
6398 INLINED_TRAP(reason);
6399 }
6400
6401 WasmRef array = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6402 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array))) {
6403 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6404 }
6405
6406 bool ok = wasm_runtime->WasmArrayInitSegment(data_index, array, dest_offset,
6407 src_offset, size);
6408 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!ok)) {
6409 TrapReason reason = WasmInterpreterThread::GetRuntimeLastWasmError(
6410 wasm_runtime->GetIsolate());
6411 INLINED_TRAP(reason)
6412 }
6413
6414 NextOp();
6415 }
6416 // The instructions array.init_data and array.init_elem have the same
6417 // implementation after validation. The only difference is that
6418 // array.init_elem is used with arrays that contain elements of reference
6419 // types, and array.init_data with arrays that contain elements of numeric
6420 // types.
6421 static auto constexpr s2s_ArrayInitData = s2s_ArrayInitSegment<true>;
6422 static auto constexpr s2s_ArrayInitElem = s2s_ArrayInitSegment<false>;
6423
6424 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayLen(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6425 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6426 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6427 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6428 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6429 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6430 }
6431 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6432
6433 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6434 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, array->length());
6435
6436 NextOp();
6437 }
6438
6439 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayCopy(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6440 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6441 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6442 const uint32_t dest_array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6443 const uint32_t src_array_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6444 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): already validated?
6445 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(dest_array_index) ||
6446 !Smi::IsValid(src_array_index))) {
6447 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6448 }
6449
6450 uint32_t size = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6451 uint32_t src_offset = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6452 WasmRef src_array = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6453 uint32_t dest_offset = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6454 WasmRef dest_array = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6455
6456 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!Smi::IsValid(size) || !Smi::IsValid(src_offset) ||
6457 !Smi::IsValid(dest_offset))) {
6458 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6459 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(dest_array))) {
6460 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6461 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(dest_offset + size >
6462 Cast<WasmArray>(*dest_array)->length())) {
6463 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6464 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(src_array))) {
6465 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6466 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(src_offset + size >
6467 Cast<WasmArray>(*src_array)->length())) {
6468 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6469 }
6470
6471 bool ok = true;
6472 if (size > 0) {
6473 ok = wasm_runtime->WasmArrayCopy(dest_array, dest_offset, src_array,
6474 src_offset, size);
6475 }
6476
6477 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!ok)) {
6478 wasm::TrapReason reason = WasmInterpreterThread::GetRuntimeLastWasmError(
6479 wasm_runtime->GetIsolate());
6480 INLINED_TRAP(reason)
6481 }
6482
6483 NextOp();
6484 }
6485
6486 template <typename T, typename U = T>
6487 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayGet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6488 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6489 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6490 uint32_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6491 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6492 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6493 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6494 }
6495 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6496
6497 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6498 if (V8_UNLIKELY(index >= array->length())) {
6499 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6500 }
6501
6502 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(index);
6503 push<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, base::ReadUnalignedValue<U>(element_addr));
6504
6505 NextOp();
6506 }
6507 static auto constexpr s2s_I8SArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<int32_t, int8_t>;
6508 static auto constexpr s2s_I8UArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<uint32_t, uint8_t>;
6509 static auto constexpr s2s_I16SArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<int32_t, int16_t>;
6510 static auto constexpr s2s_I16UArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<uint32_t, uint16_t>;
6511 static auto constexpr s2s_I32ArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<int32_t>;
6512 static auto constexpr s2s_I64ArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<int64_t>;
6513 static auto constexpr s2s_F32ArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<float>;
6514 static auto constexpr s2s_F64ArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<double>;
6515 static auto constexpr s2s_S128ArrayGet = s2s_ArrayGet<Simd128>;
6516
6517 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefArrayGet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6518 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6519 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6520 uint32_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6521 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6522 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6523 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6524 }
6525 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6526
6527 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6528 if (V8_UNLIKELY(index >= array->length())) {
6529 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6530 }
6531
6532 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime,
6533 wasm_runtime->GetWasmArrayRefElement(array, index));
6534
6535 NextOp();
6536 }

6538 template <typename T, typename U = T>
6539 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArraySet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6540 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6541 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6542 const T value = pop<T>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6543 const uint32_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6544 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6545 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6546 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6547 }
6548 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6549
6550 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6551 if (V8_UNLIKELY(index >= array->length())) {
6552 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6553 }
6554
6555 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(index);
6556 base::WriteUnalignedValue<U>(element_addr, value);
6557
6558 NextOp();
6559 }
6560 static auto constexpr s2s_I8ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<int32_t, int8_t>;
6561 static auto constexpr s2s_I16ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<int32_t, int16_t>;
6562 static auto constexpr s2s_I32ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<int32_t>;
6563 static auto constexpr s2s_I64ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<int64_t>;
6564 static auto constexpr s2s_F32ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<float>;
6565 static auto constexpr s2s_F64ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<double>;
6566 static auto constexpr s2s_S128ArraySet = s2s_ArraySet<Simd128>;
6567
6568 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefArraySet(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6569 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6570 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6571 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6572 const uint32_t index = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6573 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6574 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6575 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6576 }
6577 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6578
6579 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6580 if (V8_UNLIKELY(index >= array->length())) {
6581 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6582 }
6583
6584 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(index);
6585 uint32_t element_offset = array->element_offset(index);
6586 StoreRefIntoMemory(array, element_addr, element_offset, *ref,
6587 UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
6588
6589 NextOp();
6590 }
6591
6592 template <typename T, typename U = T>
6593 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ArrayFill(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6594 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6595 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6596 uint32_t size = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6597 T value = pop<U>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6598 uint32_t offset = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6599
6600 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6601 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6602 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6603 }
6604 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6605
6606 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6607 if (V8_UNLIKELY(static_cast<uint64_t>(offset) + size > array->length())) {
6608 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6609 }
6610
6611 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(offset);
6612 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < size; i++) {
6613 base::WriteUnalignedValue<T>(element_addr, value);
6614 element_addr += sizeof(T);
6615 }
6616
6617 NextOp();
6618 }
6619 static auto constexpr s2s_I8ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<int8_t, int32_t>;
6620 static auto constexpr s2s_I16ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<int16_t, int32_t>;
6621 static auto constexpr s2s_I32ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<int32_t>;
6622 static auto constexpr s2s_I64ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<int64_t>;
6623 static auto constexpr s2s_F32ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<float>;
6624 static auto constexpr s2s_F64ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<double>;
6625 static auto constexpr s2s_S128ArrayFill = s2s_ArrayFill<Simd128>;
6626
6627 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefArrayFill(
6628 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6629 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6630 // DrumBrake currently only works with pointer compression.
6631 static_assert(COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL);
6632
6633 uint32_t size = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6634 WasmRef value = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6635 Tagged<Object> tagged_value = *value;
6636 uint32_t offset = pop<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6637
6638 WasmRef array_obj = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6639 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(array_obj))) {
6640 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6641 }
6642 DCHECK(IsWasmArray(*array_obj));
6643
6644 Tagged<WasmArray> array = Cast<WasmArray>(*array_obj);
6645 if (V8_UNLIKELY(static_cast<uint64_t>(offset) + size > array->length())) {
6646 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapArrayOutOfBounds)
6647 }
6648
6649 Address element_addr = array->ElementAddress(offset);
6650 uint32_t element_offset = array->element_offset(offset);
6651 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < size; i++) {
6652 StoreRefIntoMemory(array, element_addr, element_offset, tagged_value,
6653 UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
6654 element_addr += kTaggedSize;
6655 element_offset += kTaggedSize;
6656 }
6657
6658 NextOp();
6659 }
6660
6661 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefI31(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6662 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6663 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6664 uint32_t value = pop<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6665
6666 // Truncate high bit.
6667 Tagged<Smi> smi(Internals::IntToSmi(value & 0x7fffffff));
6668 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime,
6669 handle(smi, wasm_runtime->GetIsolate()));
6670
6671 NextOp();
6672 }
6673
6674 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_I31GetS(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6675 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6676 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6677 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6678 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(ref))) {
6679 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6680 }
6681 DCHECK(IsSmi(*ref));
6682 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, i::Smi::ToInt(*ref));
6683
6684 NextOp();
6685 }
6686
6687 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_I31GetU(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6688 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6689 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6690 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6691 if (V8_UNLIKELY(wasm_runtime->IsRefNull(ref))) {
6692 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapNullDereference)
6693 }
6694 DCHECK(IsSmi(*ref));
6695 push<uint32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime,
6696 0x7fffffff & static_cast<uint32_t>(i::Smi::ToInt(*ref)));
6697
6698 NextOp();
6699 }
6700
6701 template <bool null_succeeds>
6702 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC RefCast(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6703 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6704 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6705 HeapType target_type(
6706 ModuleTypeIndex({static_cast<uint32_t>(Read<int32_t>(code))}));
6707
6708 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6709
6710 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
6711 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
6712
6713 if (!DoRefCast(ref, ref_type, target_type, null_succeeds, wasm_runtime)) {
6714 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapIllegalCast)
6715 }
6716
6717 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
6718
6719 NextOp();
6720 }
6721 static auto constexpr s2s_RefCast = RefCast<false>;
6722 static auto constexpr s2s_RefCastNull = RefCast<true>;
6723
6724 template <bool null_succeeds>
6725 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC RefTest(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6726 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6727 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6728 HeapType target_type(
6729 ModuleTypeIndex({static_cast<uint32_t>(Read<int32_t>(code))}));
6730
6731 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6732
6733 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
6734 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
6735
6736 bool cast_succeeds =
6737 DoRefCast(ref, ref_type, target_type, null_succeeds, wasm_runtime);
6738 push<int32_t>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, cast_succeeds ? 1 : 0);
6739
6740 NextOp();
6741 }
6742 static auto constexpr s2s_RefTest = RefTest<false>;
6743 static auto constexpr s2s_RefTestNull = RefTest<true>;
6744
6745 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_AssertNullTypecheck(
6746 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6747 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6748 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6749
6750 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
6751 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
6752 if (!wasm_runtime->IsNullTypecheck(ref, ref_type)) {
6753 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapIllegalCast)
6754 }
6755 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
6756
6757 NextOp();
6758 }

6760 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_AssertNotNullTypecheck(
6761 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6762 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6763 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6764
6765 const uint32_t ref_bitfield = Read<int32_t>(code);
6766 ValueType ref_type = ValueType::FromRawBitField(ref_bitfield);
6767 if (wasm_runtime->IsNullTypecheck(ref, ref_type)) {
6768 TRAP(TrapReason::kTrapIllegalCast)
6769 }
6770 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
6771
6772 NextOp();
6773 }

6808 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_RefAsNonNull(
6809 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,

6819
6820 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_AnyConvertExtern(
6821 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6822 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6823 WasmRef extern_ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6824 // Pass 0 as canonical type index; see implementation of builtin
6825 // WasmAnyConvertExtern.
6826 WasmRef result = wasm_runtime->WasmJSToWasmObject(
6827 extern_ref, kWasmAnyRef, 0 /* canonical type index */);
6828 if (V8_UNLIKELY(result.is_null())) {
6829 wasm::TrapReason reason = WasmInterpreterThread::GetRuntimeLastWasmError(
6830 wasm_runtime->GetIsolate());
6831 INLINED_TRAP(reason)
6832 }
6833 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, result);
6834
6835 NextOp();
6836 }
6837
6838 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_ExternConvertAny(
6839 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6840 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6841 WasmRef ref = pop<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime);
6842
6843 if (wasm_runtime->IsNullTypecheck(ref, kWasmAnyRef)) {
6844 ref = handle(wasm_runtime->GetNullValue(kWasmExternRef),
6845 wasm_runtime->GetIsolate());
6846 }
6847 push<WasmRef>(sp, code, wasm_runtime, ref);
6848
6849 NextOp();
6850 }

6853
6854 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC s2s_TraceInstruction(
6855 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6856 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6857 uint32_t pc = Read<int32_t>(code);
6858 uint32_t opcode = Read<int32_t>(code);
6859 uint32_t reg_mode = Read<int32_t>(code);
6860
6861 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
6862 wasm_runtime->Trace(
6863 "@%-3u: %-24s: ", pc,
6864 wasm::WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(opcode)));
6865 wasm_runtime->PrintStack(sp, static_cast<RegMode>(reg_mode), r0, fp0);
6866 }
6867
6868 NextOp();
6869 }
6870
6871 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC trace_UpdateStack(
6872 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6873 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6874 uint32_t stack_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6875 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
6876 wasm_runtime->TraceUpdate(stack_index, slot_offset);
6877
6878 NextOp();
6879 }
