6881 template <typename T>
6882 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC trace_PushConstSlot(
6883 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6884 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6885 slot_offset_t slot_offset = Read<slot_offset_t>(code);
6886 wasm_runtime->TracePush<T>(slot_offset);
6887
6888 NextOp();
6889 }
6890 static auto constexpr trace_PushConstI32Slot = trace_PushConstSlot<int32_t>;
6891 static auto constexpr trace_PushConstI64Slot = trace_PushConstSlot<int64_t>;
6892 static auto constexpr trace_PushConstF32Slot = trace_PushConstSlot<float>;
6893 static auto constexpr trace_PushConstF64Slot = trace_PushConstSlot<double>;
6894 static auto constexpr trace_PushConstS128Slot = trace_PushConstSlot<Simd128>;
6895 static auto constexpr trace_PushConstRefSlot = trace_PushConstSlot<WasmRef>;
6896
6897 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC trace_PushCopySlot(
6898 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6899 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6900 uint32_t stack_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6901
6902 wasm_runtime->TracePushCopy(stack_index);
6903
6904 NextOp();
6905 }
6906
6907 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC trace_PopSlot(const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp,
6908 WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6909 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6910 wasm_runtime->TracePop();
6911
6912 NextOp();
6913 }
6914
6915 INSTRUCTION_HANDLER_FUNC trace_SetSlotType(
6916 const uint8_t* code, uint32_t* sp, WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6917 int64_t r0, double fp0) {
6918 uint32_t stack_index = Read<int32_t>(code);
6919 uint32_t type = Read<int32_t>(code);
6920 wasm_runtime->TraceSetSlotType(stack_index, type);
6921
6922 NextOp();
6923 }

6926}; // class Handlers<Compressed>

6928#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
6929
6930void WasmBytecodeGenerator::TracePushConstSlot(uint32_t slot_index) {
6931 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
6932 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
6933 switch (slots_[slot_index].kind()) {
6934 case kI32:
6935 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(trace_PushConstI32Slot);
6936 break;
6937 case kI64:
6938 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(trace_PushConstI64Slot);
6939 break;
6940 case kF32:
6941 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(trace_PushConstF32Slot);
6942 break;
6943 case kF64:
6944 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(trace_PushConstF64Slot);
6945 break;
6946 case kS128:
6947 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(trace_PushConstS128Slot);
6948 break;
6949 case kRef:
6950 case kRefNull:
6951 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(trace_PushConstRefSlot);
6952 break;
6953 default:
6954 UNREACHABLE();
6955 }
6956 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[slot_index].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
6957 }
6958 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
6959 }
6960}
6961
6962void WasmBytecodeGenerator::TracePushCopySlot(uint32_t from_stack_index) {
6963 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
6964 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_PushCopySlot) {
6965 EmitI32Const(from_stack_index);
6966 }
6967 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
6968 }
6969}
6970
6971void WasmBytecodeGenerator::TraceSetSlotType(uint32_t stack_index,
6972 ValueType type) {
6973 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
6974 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_SetSlotType) {
6975 EmitI32Const(stack_index);
6976 EmitRefValueType(type.raw_bit_field());
6977 }
6978 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
6979 }
6980}
6981
6982void ShadowStack::Print(WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
6983 const uint32_t* sp, size_t start_params,
6984 size_t start_locals, size_t start_stack,
6985 RegMode reg_mode, int64_t r0, double fp0) const {
6986 for (size_t i = 0; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
6987 char slot_kind = i < start_locals - start_params ? 'p'
6988 : i < start_stack - start_params ? 'l'
6989 : 's';
6990 const uint8_t* addr =
6991 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(sp) + stack_[i].slot_offset_;
6992 stack_[i].Print(wasm_runtime, start_params + i, slot_kind, addr);
6993 }
6994
6995 switch (reg_mode) {
6996 case RegMode::kI32Reg:
6997 ShadowStack::Slot::Print(wasm_runtime, kWasmI32,
6998 start_params + stack_.size(), 'R',
6999 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&r0));
7000 break;
7001 case RegMode::kI64Reg:
7002 ShadowStack::Slot::Print(wasm_runtime, kWasmI64,
7003 start_params + stack_.size(), 'R',
7004 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&r0));
7005 break;
7006 case RegMode::kF32Reg: {
7007 float f = static_cast<float>(fp0);
7008 ShadowStack::Slot::Print(wasm_runtime, kWasmF32,
7009 start_params + stack_.size(), 'R',
7010 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&f));
7011 } break;
7012 case RegMode::kF64Reg:
7013 ShadowStack::Slot::Print(wasm_runtime, kWasmF64,
7014 start_params + stack_.size(), 'R',
7015 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(&fp0));
7016 break;
7017 default:
7018 break;
7019 }
7020
7021 wasm_runtime->Trace("\n");
7022}
7023
7024// static
7025void ShadowStack::Slot::Print(WasmInterpreterRuntime* wasm_runtime,
7026 ValueType type, size_t index, char kind,
7027 const uint8_t* addr) {
7028 switch (type.kind()) {
7029 case kI32:
7030 wasm_runtime->Trace(
7031 "%c%zu:i32:%d ", kind, index,
7032 base::ReadUnalignedValue<int32_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr)));
7033 break;
7034 case kI64:
7035 wasm_runtime->Trace(
7036 "%c%zu:i64:%" PRId64, kind, index,
7037 base::ReadUnalignedValue<int64_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr)));
7038 break;
7039 case kF32: {
7040 float f =
7041 base::ReadUnalignedValue<float>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr));
7042 wasm_runtime->Trace("%c%zu:f32:%f ", kind, index, static_cast<double>(f));
7043 } break;
7044 case kF64:
7045 wasm_runtime->Trace(
7046 "%c%zu:f64:%f ", kind, index,
7047 base::ReadUnalignedValue<double>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr)));
7048 break;
7049 case kS128: {
7050 // This defaults to tracing all S128 values as i32x4 values for now,
7051 // when there is more state to know what type of values are on the
7052 // stack, the right format should be printed here.
7053 int32x4 s;
7054 s.val[0] =
7055 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr));
7056 s.val[1] = base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
7057 reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr + 4));
7058 s.val[2] = base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
7059 reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr + 8));
7060 s.val[3] = base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
7061 reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr + 12));
7062 wasm_runtime->Trace("%c%zu:s128:%08x,%08x,%08x,%08x ", kind, index,
7063 s.val[0], s.val[1], s.val[2], s.val[3]);
7064 break;
7065 }
7066 case kRef:
7067 case kRefNull:
7068 DCHECK_EQ(sizeof(uint64_t), sizeof(WasmRef));
7069 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): Extract actual ref value from the
7070 // thread's reference_stack_.
7071 wasm_runtime->Trace(
7072 "%c%zu:ref:%" PRIx64, kind, index,
7073 base::ReadUnalignedValue<uint64_t>(reinterpret_cast<Address>(addr)));
7074 break;
7075 default:
7076 UNREACHABLE();
7077 }
7078}

7080char const* kInstructionHandlerNames[kInstructionTableSize];
7081
7082#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7083
7084PWasmOp* kInstructionTable[kInstructionTableSize] = {
7085
7086// 1. Add "small" (compressed) instruction handlers.
7087
7088#if !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
7089// For this case, this table will be initialized in
7090// InitInstructionTableOnce.
7091#define V(_) nullptr,
7092 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7093#undef V
7094
7095#else // !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
7096#define V(name) Handlers<true>::name,
7097 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7098 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_DUPLICATED_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7099#undef V
7100
7101#endif // !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
7102
7103#define V(name) Handlers<true>::name,
7104 FOREACH_NO_BOUNDSCHECK_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7105#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7106 FOREACH_TRACE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7107#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7108#undef V
7109
7110// 2. Add "large" instruction handlers.
7111
7112#if !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
7113// For this case, this table will be initialized in
7114// InitInstructionTableOnce.
7115#define V(_) nullptr,
7116 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7117#undef V
7118
7119#else // !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
7120#define V(name) Handlers<false>::name,
7121 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7122 FOREACH_LOAD_STORE_DUPLICATED_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7123#undef V
7124
7125#endif // !V8_DRUMBRAKE_BOUNDS_CHECKS
7126
7127#define V(name) Handlers<false>::name,
7128 FOREACH_NO_BOUNDSCHECK_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7129#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7130 FOREACH_TRACE_INSTR_HANDLER(V)
7131#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7132#undef V
7133};
7134
7137
7138const WasmEHData::TryBlock* WasmEHData::GetTryBlock(
7139 CodeOffset code_offset) const {
7140 const auto& catch_it = code_trycatch_map_.find(code_offset);
7141 if (catch_it == code_trycatch_map_.end()) return nullptr;
7142 BlockIndex try_block_index = catch_it->second;
7143
7144 const auto& try_it = try_blocks_.find(try_block_index);
7145 DCHECK_NE(try_it, try_blocks_.end());
7146 const WasmEHData::TryBlock* try_block = &try_it->second;
7147 if (try_block->IsTryDelegate()) {
7148 try_block = GetDelegateTryBlock(try_block);
7149 }
7150 return try_block;
7151}
7152
7153const WasmEHData::TryBlock* WasmEHData::GetParentTryBlock(
7154 const WasmEHData::TryBlock* try_block) const {
7155 const auto& try_it =
7156 try_blocks_.find(try_block->parent_or_matching_try_block);
7157 return try_it != try_blocks_.end() ? &try_it->second : nullptr;
7158}
7159
7160const WasmEHData::TryBlock* WasmEHData::GetDelegateTryBlock(
7161 const WasmEHData::TryBlock* try_block) const {
7162 DCHECK_GE(try_block->delegate_try_index, 0);
7163 if (try_block->delegate_try_index == WasmEHData::kDelegateToCallerIndex) {
7164 return nullptr;
7165 }
7166 const auto& try_it = try_blocks_.find(try_block->delegate_try_index);
7167 DCHECK_NE(try_it, try_blocks_.end());
7168 return &try_it->second;
7169}
7170
7171size_t WasmEHData::GetEndInstructionOffsetFor(
7172 WasmEHData::BlockIndex catch_block_index) const {
7173 int try_block_index = GetTryBranchOf(catch_block_index);
7174 DCHECK_GE(try_block_index, 0);
7175
7176 const auto& it = try_blocks_.find(try_block_index);
7177 DCHECK_NE(it, try_blocks_.end());
7178 return it->second.end_instruction_code_offset;
7179}
7180
7181WasmEHData::ExceptionPayloadSlotOffsets
7182WasmEHData::GetExceptionPayloadStartSlotOffsets(
7183 WasmEHData::BlockIndex catch_block_index) const {
7184 const auto& it = catch_blocks_.find(catch_block_index);
7185 DCHECK_NE(it, catch_blocks_.end());
7186 return {it->second.first_param_slot_offset,
7187 it->second.first_param_ref_stack_index};
7188}
7189
7190WasmEHData::BlockIndex WasmEHData::GetTryBranchOf(
7191 WasmEHData::BlockIndex catch_block_index) const {
7192 const auto& it = catch_blocks_.find(catch_block_index);
7193 if (it == catch_blocks_.end()) return -1;
7194 return it->second.try_block_index;
7195}
7196
7197void WasmEHDataGenerator::AddTryBlock(
7198 BlockIndex try_block_index, BlockIndex parent_or_matching_try_block_index,
7199 BlockIndex ancestor_try_block_index) {
7200 DCHECK_EQ(try_blocks_.find(try_block_index), try_blocks_.end());
7201 try_blocks_.insert(
7202 {try_block_index,
7203 TryBlock{parent_or_matching_try_block_index, ancestor_try_block_index}});
7204 current_try_block_index_ = try_block_index;
7205}
7206
7207void WasmEHDataGenerator::AddCatchBlock(BlockIndex catch_block_index,
7208 int tag_index,
7209 uint32_t first_param_slot_offset,
7210 uint32_t first_param_ref_stack_index,
7211 CodeOffset code_offset) {
7212 DCHECK_EQ(catch_blocks_.find(catch_block_index), catch_blocks_.end());
7213 catch_blocks_.insert(
7214 {catch_block_index,
7215 CatchBlock{current_try_block_index_, first_param_slot_offset,
7216 first_param_ref_stack_index}});
7217
7218 auto it = try_blocks_.find(current_try_block_index_);
7219 DCHECK_NE(it, try_blocks_.end());
7220 it->second.catch_handlers.emplace_back(
7221 CatchHandler{catch_block_index, tag_index, code_offset});
7222}
7223
7224void WasmEHDataGenerator::AddDelegatedBlock(
7225 BlockIndex delegate_try_block_index) {
7226 auto it = try_blocks_.find(current_try_block_index_);
7227 DCHECK_NE(it, try_blocks_.end());
7228 TryBlock& try_block = it->second;
7229 DCHECK(try_block.catch_handlers.empty());
7230 try_block.SetDelegated(delegate_try_block_index);
7231}
7232
7233WasmEHData::BlockIndex WasmEHDataGenerator::EndTryCatchBlocks(
7234 WasmEHData::BlockIndex block_index, CodeOffset code_offset) {
7235 WasmEHData::BlockIndex try_block_index = GetTryBranchOf(block_index);
7236 if (try_block_index < 0) {
7237 // No catch/catch_all blocks.
7238 try_block_index = block_index;
7239 }
7240
7241 const auto& try_it = try_blocks_.find(try_block_index);
7242 DCHECK_NE(try_it, try_blocks_.end());
7243 try_it->second.end_instruction_code_offset = code_offset;
7244 current_try_block_index_ = try_it->second.parent_or_matching_try_block;
7245 return try_block_index;
7246}
7247
7248void WasmEHDataGenerator::RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(
7249 WasmOpcode opcode, CodeOffset code_offset) {
7250 if (current_try_block_index_ < 0) {
7251 return; // Not inside a try block.
7252 }
7253
7254 BlockIndex try_block_index = current_try_block_index_;
7255 const auto& try_it = try_blocks_.find(current_try_block_index_);
7256 DCHECK_NE(try_it, try_blocks_.end());
7257 const TryBlock& try_block = try_it->second;
7258
7259 bool inside_catch_handler = !try_block.catch_handlers.empty();
7260 if (inside_catch_handler) {
7261 // If we are throwing from inside a catch block, the exception should only
7262 // be caught by the catch handler of an ancestor try block.
7263 try_block_index = try_block.ancestor_try_index;
7264 if (try_block_index < 0) return;
7265 }
7266
7267 code_trycatch_map_[code_offset] = try_block_index;
7268}
7269
7270WasmBytecode::WasmBytecode(int func_index, const uint8_t* code_data,
7271 size_t code_length, uint32_t stack_frame_size,
7272 const FunctionSig* signature,
7273 const InterpreterCode* interpreter_code,
7274 size_t blocks_count, const uint8_t* const_slots_data,
7275 size_t const_slots_length, uint32_t ref_slots_count,
7276 const WasmEHData&& eh_data,
7277 const std::map<CodeOffset, pc_t>&& code_pc_map)
7278 : code_(code_data, code_data + code_length),
7279 code_bytes_(code_.data()),
7280 signature_(signature),
7281 interpreter_code_(interpreter_code),
7282 const_slots_values_(const_slots_data,
7283 const_slots_data + const_slots_length),
7284 func_index_(func_index),
7285 blocks_count_(static_cast<uint32_t>(blocks_count)),
7286 args_count_(static_cast<uint32_t>(signature_->parameter_count())),
7287 args_slots_size_(ArgsSizeInSlots(signature_)),
7288 return_count_(static_cast<uint32_t>(signature_->return_count())),
7289 rets_slots_size_(RetsSizeInSlots(signature_)),
7290 locals_count_(
7291 static_cast<uint32_t>(interpreter_code_->locals.num_locals)),
7292 locals_slots_size_(LocalsSizeInSlots(interpreter_code_)),
7293 total_frame_size_in_bytes_(stack_frame_size * kSlotSize +
7294 args_slots_size_ * kSlotSize +
7295 rets_slots_size_ * kSlotSize),
7296 ref_args_count_(RefArgsCount(signature_)),
7297 ref_rets_count_(RefRetsCount(signature_)),
7298 ref_locals_count_(RefLocalsCount(interpreter_code)),
7299 ref_slots_count_(ref_slots_count),
7300 eh_data_(eh_data),
7301 code_pc_map_(code_pc_map) {}
7302
7303pc_t WasmBytecode::GetPcFromTrapCode(const uint8_t* current_code) const {
7304 DCHECK_GE(current_code, code_bytes_);
7305 size_t code_offset = current_code - code_bytes_;
7306
7307 auto it = code_pc_map_.lower_bound(code_offset);
7308 if (it == code_pc_map_.begin()) return 0;
7309 it--;
7310
7311 return it->second;
7312}

7314// static
7315size_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::total_bytecode_size_ = 0;
7316// static
7317size_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::emitted_short_slot_offset_count_ = 0;
7318// static
7319size_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::emitted_short_memory_offset_count_ = 0;
7320
7321WasmBytecodeGenerator::WasmBytecodeGenerator(uint32_t function_index,
7322 InterpreterCode* wasm_code,
7323 const WasmModule* module)
7324 : const_slot_offset_(0),
7325 slot_offset_(0),
7326 ref_slots_count_(0),
7327 function_index_(function_index),
7328 wasm_code_(wasm_code),
7329 args_count_(0),
7330 args_slots_size_(0),
7331 return_count_(0),
7332 rets_slots_size_(0),
7333 locals_count_(0),
7334 current_block_index_(-1),
7335 is_instruction_reachable_(true),
7336 unreachable_block_count_(0),
7337#ifdef DEBUG
7338 was_current_instruction_reachable_(true),
7339#endif // DEBUG
7340 module_(module),
7341 last_instr_offset_(kInvalidCodeOffset),
7342 handler_size_(InstrHandlerSize::Large),
7343 current_instr_encoding_failed_(false)
7344#ifdef DEBUG
7345 ,
7346 no_nested_emit_instr_handler_guard_(false)
7347#endif // DEBUG
7348{
7349 DCHECK(v8_flags.wasm_jitless);
7350
7351 // Multiple memories not supported.
7352 DCHECK_LE(module->memories.size(), 1);
7353
7354 size_t wasm_code_size = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
7355 code_.reserve(wasm_code_size * 6);
7356 slots_.reserve(wasm_code_size / 2);
7357 stack_.reserve(wasm_code_size / 4);
7358 blocks_.reserve(wasm_code_size / 8);
7359
7360 const FunctionSig* sig = module_->functions[function_index].sig;
7361 args_count_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->parameter_count());
7362 args_slots_size_ = WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig);
7363 return_count_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->return_count());
7364 rets_slots_size_ = WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig);
7365 locals_count_ = static_cast<uint32_t>(wasm_code->locals.num_locals);
7366
7367 is_memory64_ = IsMemory64();
7368 if (is_memory64_) {
7369 int_mem_push_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I64Push;
7370 int_mem_pop_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I64Pop;
7371 } else {
7372 int_mem_push_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I32Push;
7373 int_mem_pop_ = &WasmBytecodeGenerator::I32Pop;
7374 }
7375}
7376
7377size_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::Simd128Hash::operator()(
7378 const Simd128& s128) const {
7379 static_assert(sizeof(size_t) == sizeof(uint64_t));
7380 const int64x2 s = s128.to_i64x2();
7381 return s.val[0] ^ s.val[1];
7382}
7383
7384// Look if the slot that hold the value at {stack_index} is being shared with
7385// other slots. This can happen if there are multiple load.get operations that
7386// copy from the same local.
7387bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::HasSharedSlot(uint32_t stack_index) const {
7388 // Only consider stack entries added in the current block.
7389 // We don't need to consider ancestor blocks because if a block has a
7390 // non-empty signature we always pass arguments and results into separate
7391 // slots, emitting CopySlot operations.
7392 uint32_t start_slot_index = blocks_[current_block_index_].stack_size_;
7393
7394 for (uint32_t i = start_slot_index; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
7395 if (stack_[i] == stack_[stack_index]) {
7396 return true;
7397 }
7398 }
7399 return false;
7400}
7401
7402// Look if the slot that hold the value at {stack_index} is being shared with
7403// other slots. This can happen if there are multiple load.get operations that
7404// copy from the same local. In this case when we modify the value of the slot
7405// with a local.set or local.tee we need to first duplicate the slot to make
7406// sure that the old value is preserved in the other shared slots.
7407bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::FindSharedSlot(uint32_t stack_index,
7408 uint32_t* new_slot_index) {
7409 *new_slot_index = UINT_MAX;
7410 ValueType value_type = slots_[stack_[stack_index]].value_type;
7411 if (value_type.is_reference()) return false;
7412
7413 // Only consider stack entries added in the current block.
7414 // We don't need to consider ancestor blocks because if a block has a
7415 // non-empty signature we always pass arguments and results into separate
7416 // slots, emitting CopySlot operations.
7417 uint32_t start_slot_index = blocks_[current_block_index_].stack_size_;
7418
7419 for (uint32_t i = start_slot_index; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
7420 if (stack_[i] == stack_[stack_index]) {
7421 // Allocate new slot to preserve the old value of a shared slot.
7422 *new_slot_index = CreateSlot(value_type);
7423 break;
7424 }
7425 }
7426
7427 if (*new_slot_index == UINT_MAX) return false;
7428
7429 // If there was a collision and we allocated a new slot to preserve the old
7430 // value, we need to do two things to keep the state up to date:
7431 // 1. For each shared slot, we update the stack value to refer to the new
7432 // slot. This track the change at bytecode generation time.
7433 // 2. We return {true} to indicate that the slot was shared and the caller
7434 // should emit a 's2s_PreserveCopySlot...' instruction to copy the old slot
7435 // value into the new slot, at runtime.
7436
7437 // This loop works because stack_index is always greater or equal to the index
7438 // of args/globals.
7439 DCHECK_GT(start_slot_index, stack_index);
7440 for (uint32_t i = start_slot_index; i < stack_.size(); i++) {
7441 if (stack_[i] == stack_[stack_index]) {
7442 // Copy value into the new slot.
7443 UpdateStack(i, *new_slot_index);
7444#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7445 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
7446 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
7447 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7448 EmitStackIndex(i);
7449 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[*new_slot_index].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
7450 printf("Preserve UpdateStack: [%d] = %d\n", i,
7451 slots_[*new_slot_index].slot_offset);
7452 }
7453 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7454 }
7455#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7456 }
7457 }
7458
7459 return true;
7460}
7461
7462void WasmBytecodeGenerator::EmitCopySlot(ValueType value_type,
7463 uint32_t from_slot_index,
7464 uint32_t to_slot_index,
7465 bool copy_from_reg) {
7466 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
7467 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
7468 switch (kind) {
7469 case kI32:
7470 if (copy_from_reg) {
7471 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyR0ToSlot32);
7472 } else {
7473 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot32);
7474 }
7475 break;
7476 case kI64:
7477 if (copy_from_reg) {
7478 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyR0ToSlot64);
7479 } else {
7480 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot64);
7481 }
7482 break;
7483 case kF32:
7484 if (copy_from_reg) {
7485 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyFp0ToSlot32);
7486 } else {
7487 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot32);
7488 }
7489 break;
7490 case kF64:
7491 if (copy_from_reg) {
7492 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_CopyFp0ToSlot64);
7493 } else {
7494 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot64);
7495 }
7496 break;
7497 case kS128:
7498 DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7499 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlot128);
7500 break;
7501 case kRef:
7502 case kRefNull:
7503 DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7504 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_CopySlotRef);
7505 break;
7506 default:
7507 UNREACHABLE();
7508 }
7509
7510 if (kind == kRefNull || kind == kRef) {
7511 DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7512 EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[from_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7513 EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[to_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7514 } else {
7515 if (!copy_from_reg) {
7516 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset);
7517 }
7518 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset);
7519 }
7520 }
7521 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7522
7523#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7524 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_bytecode_generator &&
7525 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
7526 printf("emit CopySlot: %d(%d) -> %d(%d)\n", from_slot_index,
7527 slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset, to_slot_index,
7528 slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset);
7529 }
7530#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7531}
7532
7533// When a Wasm function starts the values for the function args and locals are
7534// already present in the Wasm stack. The stack entries for args and locals
7535// can be directly accessed with {local.get} and modified with {local.set} and
7536// {local.tee}, but they can never be popped, they are always present until
7537// the function returns.
7538// During the execution of the function other values are then pushed/popped
7539// into/from the stack, but these other entries are only accessible indirectly
7540// as operands/results of operations, not directly with local.get/set
7541// instructions.
7542//
7543// DrumBrake implements a "args/locals propagation" optimization that allows the
7544// stack slots for "local" stack entries to be shared with other stack entries
7545// (using the {stack_} and {slots_} arrays), in order to avoid emitting calls to
7546// 'local.get' instruction handlers.
7547
7548// When an arg/local value is modified, and its slot is shared with other
7549// entries in the stack, we need to preserve the old value of the stack entry in
7550// a new slot.
7551void WasmBytecodeGenerator::CopyToSlot(ValueType value_type,
7552 uint32_t from_slot_index,
7553 uint32_t to_stack_index,
7554 bool copy_from_reg) {
7555 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
7556 uint32_t to_slot_index = stack_[to_stack_index];
7557 DCHECK(copy_from_reg || CheckEqualKind(kind, slots_[from_slot_index].kind()));
7558 DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(slots_[to_slot_index].kind(), kind));
7559
7560 uint32_t new_slot_index;
7561 // If the slot is shared {FindSharedSlot} creates a new slot and makes all the
7562 // 'non-locals' stack entries that shared the old slot point to this new slot.
7563 // We need to emit a {PreserveCopySlot} instruction to dynamically copy the
7564 // old value into the new slot.
7565 if (FindSharedSlot(to_stack_index, &new_slot_index)) {
7566 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
7567 switch (kind) {
7568 case kI32:
7569 if (copy_from_reg) {
7570 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyR0ToSlot32);
7571 } else {
7572 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot32);
7573 }
7574 break;
7575 case kI64:
7576 if (copy_from_reg) {
7577 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyR0ToSlot64);
7578 } else {
7579 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot64);
7580 }
7581 break;
7582 case kF32:
7583 if (copy_from_reg) {
7584 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyFp0ToSlot32);
7585 } else {
7586 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot32);
7587 }
7588 break;
7589 case kF64:
7590 if (copy_from_reg) {
7591 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_PreserveCopyFp0ToSlot64);
7592 } else {
7593 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot64);
7594 }
7595 break;
7596 case kS128:
7597 DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7598 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_PreserveCopySlot128);
7599 break;
7600 case kRef:
7601 case kRefNull:
7602 default:
7603 UNREACHABLE();
7604 }
7605
7606 if (kind == kRefNull || kind == kRef) {
7607 DCHECK(!copy_from_reg);
7608 EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[from_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7609 EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[to_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7610 EmitRefStackIndex(slots_[new_slot_index].ref_stack_index);
7611 } else {
7612 if (!copy_from_reg) {
7613 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset);
7614 }
7615 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset);
7616 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[new_slot_index].slot_offset);
7617 }
7618
7619#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7620 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution &&
7621 v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution_verbose) {
7622 printf("emit s2s_PreserveCopySlot: %d %d %d\n",
7623 slots_[from_slot_index].slot_offset,
7624 slots_[to_slot_index].slot_offset,
7625 slots_[new_slot_index].slot_offset);
7626 }
7627#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7628 }
7629 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7630 } else {
7631 EmitCopySlot(value_type, from_slot_index, to_slot_index, copy_from_reg);
7632 }
7633}
7634
7635// Used for 'local.tee' and 'local.set' instructions.
7636void WasmBytecodeGenerator::CopyToSlotAndPop(ValueType value_type,
7637 uint32_t to_stack_index,
7638 bool is_tee, bool copy_from_reg) {
7639 DCHECK(!stack_.empty());
7640 DCHECK_LT(to_stack_index, stack_.size() - (copy_from_reg ? 0 : 1));
7641
7642 // LocalGet uses a "copy-on-write" mechanism: the arg/local value is not
7643 // copied and instead the stack entry references the same slot. When the
7644 // arg/local value is modified, we need to preserve the old value of the stack
7645 // entry in a new slot.
7646 CopyToSlot(value_type, stack_.back(), to_stack_index, copy_from_reg);
7647
7648 if (!is_tee && !copy_from_reg) {
7649 PopSlot();
7650
7651#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7652 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7653 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_PopSlot) {}
7654 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7655 }
7656#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7657 }
7658}
7659
7660// This function is called when we enter a new 'block', 'loop' or 'if' block
7661// statement. Checks whether any of the 'non-locals' stack entries share a slot
7662// with an arg/local stack entry. In that case stop make sure the local stack
7663// entry will get its own slot. This is necessary because at runtime we could
7664// jump at the block after having modified the local value in some other code
7665// path.
7666// TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com) - Understand why this is not required only for
7667// 'loop' blocks.
7668void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PreserveArgsAndLocals() {
7669 uint32_t num_args_and_locals = args_count_ + locals_count_;
7670
7671 // If there are only args/locals entries in the stack, nothing to do.
7672 if (num_args_and_locals >= stack_size()) return;
7673
7674 for (uint32_t local_index = 0; local_index < num_args_and_locals;
7675 ++local_index) {
7676 uint32_t new_slot_index;
7677 if (FindSharedSlot(local_index, &new_slot_index)) {
7678 ValueType value_type = slots_[stack_[local_index]].value_type;
7679 EmitCopySlot(value_type, stack_[local_index], new_slot_index);
7680 }
7681 }
7682}
7683
7684uint32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::ReserveBlockSlots(
7685 uint8_t opcode, const WasmInstruction::Optional::Block& block_data,
7686 size_t* rets_slots_count, size_t* params_slots_count) {
7687 uint32_t first_slot_index = 0;
7688 *rets_slots_count = 0;
7689 *params_slots_count = 0;
7690 bool first_slot_found = false;
7691 const ValueType value_type = block_data.value_type();
7692 if (value_type == kWasmBottom) {
7693 const FunctionSig* sig = module_->signature(block_data.sig_index);
7694 *rets_slots_count = sig->return_count();
7695 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < *rets_slots_count; i++) {
7696 uint32_t slot_index = CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(i));
7697 if (!first_slot_found) {
7698 first_slot_index = slot_index;
7699 first_slot_found = true;
7700 }
7701 }
7702 *params_slots_count = sig->parameter_count();
7703 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < *params_slots_count; i++) {
7704 uint32_t slot_index = CreateSlot(sig->GetParam(i));
7705 if (!first_slot_found) {
7706 first_slot_index = slot_index;
7707 first_slot_found = true;
7708 }
7709 }
7710 } else if (value_type != kWasmVoid) {
7711 *rets_slots_count = 1;
7712 first_slot_index = CreateSlot(value_type);
7713 }
7714 return first_slot_index;
7715}
7716
7717void WasmBytecodeGenerator::StoreBlockParamsIntoSlots(
7718 uint32_t target_block_index, bool update_stack) {
7719 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
7720 blocks_[target_block_index];
7721 DCHECK_EQ(target_block_data.opcode_, kExprLoop);
7722
7723 uint32_t params_count = ParamsCount(target_block_data);
7724 uint32_t rets_count = ReturnsCount(target_block_data);
7725 uint32_t first_param_slot_index =
7726 target_block_data.first_block_index_ + rets_count;
7727 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < params_count; i++) {
7728 uint32_t from_slot_index =
7729 stack_[stack_top_index() - (params_count - 1) + i];
7730 uint32_t to_slot_index = first_param_slot_index + i;
7731 if (from_slot_index != to_slot_index) {
7732 EmitCopySlot(GetParamType(target_block_data, i), from_slot_index,
7733 to_slot_index);
7734 if (update_stack) {
7735 DCHECK_EQ(GetParamType(target_block_data, i),
7736 slots_[first_param_slot_index + i].value_type);
7737 DCHECK_EQ(GetParamType(target_block_data, i),
7738 slots_[first_param_slot_index + i].value_type);
7739 UpdateStack(stack_top_index() - (params_count - 1) + i,
7740 first_param_slot_index + i);
7741
7742#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7743 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7744 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7745 EmitStackIndex(stack_top_index() - (params_count - 1) + i);
7746 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[first_param_slot_index + i].slot_offset *
7747 kSlotSize);
7748 }
7749 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7750 }
7751#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7752 }
7753 }
7754 }
7755}
7756
7757void WasmBytecodeGenerator::StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(
7758 uint32_t target_block_index, WasmOpcode opcode) {
7759 bool is_branch = kExprBr == opcode || kExprBrIf == opcode ||
7760 kExprBrTable == opcode || kExprBrOnNull == opcode ||
7761 kExprBrOnNonNull == opcode || kExprBrOnCast == opcode;
7762 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
7763 blocks_[target_block_index];
7764 bool is_target_loop_block = target_block_data.opcode_ == kExprLoop;
7765 if (is_target_loop_block && is_branch) {
7766 StoreBlockParamsIntoSlots(target_block_index, false);
7767 }
7768
7769 // Ignore params if this is the function main block.
7770 uint32_t params_count =
7771 target_block_index == 0 ? 0 : ParamsCount(target_block_data);
7772 uint32_t rets_count = ReturnsCount(target_block_data);
7773
7774 // There could be valid code where there are not enough elements in the
7775 // stack if some code in unreachable (for example if a 'i32.const 0' is
7776 // followed by a 'br_if' the if branch is never reachable).
7777 uint32_t count = std::min(static_cast<uint32_t>(stack_.size()), rets_count);
7778 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < count; i++) {
7779 uint32_t from_slot_index = stack_[stack_top_index() - (count - 1) + i];
7780 uint32_t to_slot_index = target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i;
7781 if (from_slot_index != to_slot_index) {
7782 EmitCopySlot(GetReturnType(target_block_data, i), from_slot_index,
7783 to_slot_index);
7784 }
7785 }
7786
7787 bool is_else = (kExprElse == opcode);
7788 bool is_return = (kExprReturn == opcode);
7789 bool is_catch = (kExprCatch == opcode || kExprCatchAll == opcode);
7790 if (!is_branch && !is_return && !is_else && !is_catch) {
7791 uint32_t new_stack_height =
7792 target_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + rets_count;
7793 DCHECK(new_stack_height <= stack_.size() ||
7794 !was_current_instruction_reachable_);
7795 stack_.resize(new_stack_height);
7796
7797 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < rets_count; i++) {
7798 DCHECK_EQ(GetReturnType(target_block_data, i),
7799 slots_[target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i].value_type);
7800 DCHECK_EQ(GetReturnType(target_block_data, i),
7801 slots_[target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i].value_type);
7802 UpdateStack(target_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i,
7803 target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i);
7804
7805#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7806 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7807 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7808 EmitStackIndex(target_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i);
7809 EmitSlotOffset(
7810 slots_[target_block_data.first_block_index_ + i].slot_offset *
7811 kSlotSize);
7812 }
7813 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7814 }
7815#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7816 }
7817 }
7818}
7819
7820void WasmBytecodeGenerator::RestoreIfElseParams(uint32_t if_block_index) {
7821 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& if_block_data =
7822 blocks_[if_block_index];
7823 DCHECK_EQ(if_block_data.opcode_, kExprIf);
7824
7825 stack_.resize(blocks_[if_block_index].stack_size_);
7826 uint32_t params_count = if_block_index == 0 ? 0 : ParamsCount(if_block_data);
7827 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < params_count; i++) {
7828 UpdateStack(if_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i,
7829 if_block_data.GetParam(i), GetParamType(if_block_data, i));
7830#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7831 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
7832 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(trace_UpdateStack) {
7833 EmitStackIndex(if_block_data.stack_size_ - params_count + i);
7834 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[if_block_data.GetParam(i)].slot_offset *
7835 kSlotSize);
7836 }
7837 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7838 }
7839#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
7840 }
7841}
7842
7843uint32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::ScanConstInstructions() const {
7844 Decoder decoder(wasm_code_->start, wasm_code_->end);
7845 uint32_t const_slots_size = 0;
7846 pc_t pc = wasm_code_->locals.encoded_size;
7847 pc_t limit = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
7848 while (pc < limit) {
7849 uint32_t opcode = wasm_code_->start[pc];
7850 if (opcode == kExprI32Const || opcode == kExprF32Const) {
7851 const_slots_size += sizeof(uint32_t) / kSlotSize;
7852 } else if (opcode == kExprI64Const || opcode == kExprF64Const) {
7853 const_slots_size += sizeof(uint64_t) / kSlotSize;
7854 } else if (opcode == kSimdPrefix) {
7855 auto [opcode_index, opcode_len] =
7856 decoder.read_u32v<Decoder::FullValidationTag>(
7857 wasm_code_->start + pc + 1, "prefixed opcode index");
7858 opcode = (kSimdPrefix << 8) | opcode_index;
7859 if (opcode == kExprS128Const || opcode == kExprI8x16Shuffle) {
7860 const_slots_size += sizeof(Simd128) / kSlotSize;
7861 }
7862 }
7863 pc++;
7864 }
7865 return const_slots_size;
7866}
7867
7868int32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::EndBlock(WasmOpcode opcode) {
7869 WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& block_data = blocks_[current_block_index_];
7870 bool is_try_catch =
7871 block_data.IsTry() || block_data.IsCatch() || block_data.IsCatchAll();
7872
7873 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(current_block_index_, opcode);
7874
7875 block_data.end_code_offset_ = CurrentCodePos();
7876 if (opcode == kExprEnd && block_data.IsElse()) {
7877 DCHECK_GT(block_data.if_else_block_index_, 0);
7878 blocks_[block_data.if_else_block_index_].end_code_offset_ =
7879 CurrentCodePos();
7880 }
7881
7882 if (!is_try_catch) {
7883 current_block_index_ = blocks_[current_block_index_].parent_block_index_;
7884 }
7885
7886 if (is_try_catch && (opcode == kExprEnd || opcode == kExprDelegate)) {
7887 int32_t try_block_index =
7888 eh_data_.EndTryCatchBlocks(current_block_index_, CurrentCodePos());
7889 DCHECK_GE(try_block_index, 0);
7890 current_block_index_ = blocks_[try_block_index].parent_block_index_;
7891 }
7892
7893 last_instr_offset_ = kInvalidCodeOffset;
7894
7895 return current_block_index_;
7896}
7897
7898void WasmBytecodeGenerator::Return() {
7899 if (current_block_index_ >= 0) {
7900 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(0, kExprReturn);
7901 }
7902
7903 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(s2s_Return) {
7904 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data = blocks_[0];
7905 uint32_t final_stack_size =
7906 target_block_data.stack_size_ + ReturnsCount(target_block_data);
7907 EmitStackIndex(final_stack_size);
7908 }
7909 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
7910}
7911
7912WasmInstruction WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeInstruction(pc_t pc,
7913 Decoder& decoder) {
7914 pc_t limit = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
7915 if (pc >= limit) return WasmInstruction();
7916
7917 int len = 1;
7918 uint8_t orig = wasm_code_->start[pc];
7919 WasmOpcode opcode = static_cast<WasmOpcode>(orig);
7920 if (WasmOpcodes::IsPrefixOpcode(opcode)) {
7921 uint32_t prefixed_opcode_length;
7922 std::tie(opcode, prefixed_opcode_length) =
7923 decoder.read_prefixed_opcode<Decoder::NoValidationTag>(
7924 wasm_code_->at(pc));
7925 // skip breakpoint by switching on original code.
7926 len = prefixed_opcode_length;
7927 }
7928
7929 WasmInstruction::Optional optional;
7930 switch (orig) {
7931 case kExprUnreachable:
7932 break;
7933 case kExprNop:
7934 break;
7935 case kExprBlock:
7936 case kExprLoop:
7937 case kExprIf:
7938 case kExprTry: {
7939 BlockTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &decoder,
7940 wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), Decoder::kNoValidation);
7941 if (imm.sig_index.valid()) {
7942 // The block has at least one argument or at least two results, its
7943 // signature is identified by sig_index.
7944 optional.block.sig_index = imm.sig_index;
7945 optional.block.value_type_bitfield = kWasmBottom.raw_bit_field();
7946 } else if (imm.sig.return_count() + imm.sig.parameter_count() == 0) {
7947 // Void signature: no arguments and no results.
7948 optional.block.sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex::Invalid();
7949 optional.block.value_type_bitfield = kWasmVoid.raw_bit_field();
7950 } else {
7951 // No arguments and one result.
7952 optional.block.sig_index = ModuleTypeIndex::Invalid();
7953 std::optional<wasm::ValueType> wasm_return_type =
7954 GetWasmReturnTypeFromSignature(&imm.sig);
7955 DCHECK(wasm_return_type.has_value());
7956 optional.block.value_type_bitfield =
7957 wasm_return_type.value().raw_bit_field();
7958 }
7959 len = 1 + imm.length;
7960 break;
7961 }
7962 case kExprElse:
7963 break;
7964 case kExprCatch: {
7965 TagIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
7966 Decoder::kNoValidation);
7967 optional.index = imm.index;
7968 len = 1 + imm.length;
7969 break;
7970 }
7971 case kExprCatchAll:
7972 break;
7973 case kExprEnd:
7974 break;
7975 case kExprThrow: {
7976 TagIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
7977 Decoder::kNoValidation);
7978 len = 1 + imm.length;
7979 optional.index = imm.index;
7980 break;
7981 }
7982 case kExprRethrow:
7983 case kExprBr:
7984 case kExprBrIf:
7985 case kExprBrOnNull:
7986 case kExprBrOnNonNull:
7987 case kExprDelegate: {
7988 BranchDepthImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
7989 Decoder::kNoValidation);
7990 len = 1 + imm.length;
7991 optional.depth = imm.depth;
7992 break;
7993 }
7994 case kExprBrTable: {
7995 BranchTableImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
7996 Decoder::kNoValidation);
7997 BranchTableIterator<Decoder::NoValidationTag> iterator(&decoder, imm);
7998 optional.br_table.table_count = imm.table_count;
7999 optional.br_table.labels_index =
8000 static_cast<uint32_t>(br_table_labels_.size());
8001 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= imm.table_count; i++) {
8002 DCHECK(iterator.has_next());
8003 br_table_labels_.emplace_back(iterator.next());
8004 }
8005 len = static_cast<int>(1 + iterator.pc() - imm.start);
8006 break;
8007 }
8008 case kExprReturn:
8009 break;
8010 case kExprCallFunction:
8011 case kExprReturnCall: {
8012 CallFunctionImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8013 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8014 len = 1 + imm.length;
8015 optional.index = imm.index;
8016 break;
8017 }
8018 case kExprCallIndirect:
8019 case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
8020 CallIndirectImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8021 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8022 len = 1 + imm.length;
8023 optional.indirect_call.table_index = imm.table_imm.index;
8024 optional.indirect_call.sig_index = imm.sig_imm.index.index;
8025 break;
8026 }
8027 case kExprDrop:
8028 break;
8029 case kExprSelect:
8030 break;
8031 case kExprSelectWithType: {
8032 SelectTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &decoder,
8033 wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8034 len = 1 + imm.length;
8035 break;
8036 }
8037 case kExprLocalGet: {
8038 IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "local index",
8039 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8040 len = 1 + imm.length;
8041 optional.index = imm.index;
8042 break;
8043 }
8044 case kExprLocalSet: {
8045 IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "local index",
8046 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8047 len = 1 + imm.length;
8048 optional.index = imm.index;
8049 break;
8050 }
8051 case kExprLocalTee: {
8052 IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "local index",
8053 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8054 len = 1 + imm.length;
8055 optional.index = imm.index;
8056 break;
8057 }
8058 case kExprGlobalGet: {
8059 GlobalIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8060 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8061 len = 1 + imm.length;
8062 optional.index = imm.index;
8063 break;
8064 }
8065 case kExprGlobalSet: {
8066 GlobalIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8067 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8068 len = 1 + imm.length;
8069 optional.index = imm.index;
8070 break;
8071 }
8072 case kExprTableGet: {
8073 IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "table index",
8074 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8075 len = 1 + imm.length;
8076 optional.index = imm.index;
8077 break;
8078 }
8079 case kExprTableSet: {
8080 IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "table index",
8081 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8082 len = 1 + imm.length;
8083 optional.index = imm.index;
8084 break;
8085 }
8086
8087#define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
8088 case kExpr##name: { \
8089 MemoryAccessImmediate imm( \
8090 &decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), sizeof(ctype), \
8091 !module_->memories.empty() && module_->memories[0].is_memory64(), \
8092 Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8093 len = 1 + imm.length; \
8094 optional.offset = imm.offset; \
8095 break; \
8096 }
8097 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8S, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
8098 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);
8099 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16S, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
8100 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);
8101 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8S, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
8102 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
8103 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
8104 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
8105 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
8106 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);
8107 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
8108 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
8109 LOAD_CASE(F32LoadMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
8110 LOAD_CASE(F64LoadMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
8111#undef LOAD_CASE
8112
8113#define STORE_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
8114 case kExpr##name: { \
8115 MemoryAccessImmediate imm( \
8116 &decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), sizeof(ctype), \
8117 !module_->memories.empty() && module_->memories[0].is_memory64(), \
8118 Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8119 len = 1 + imm.length; \
8120 optional.offset = imm.offset; \
8121 break; \
8122 }
8123 STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem8, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
8124 STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem16, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
8125 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem8, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
8126 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem16, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
8127 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem32, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
8128 STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
8129 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
8130 STORE_CASE(F32StoreMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
8131 STORE_CASE(F64StoreMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
8132#undef STORE_CASE
8133
8134 case kExprMemorySize: {
8135 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8136 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8137 len = 1 + imm.length;
8138 break;
8139 }
8140 case kExprMemoryGrow: {
8141 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8142 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8143 len = 1 + imm.length;
8144 break;
8145 }
8146 case kExprI32Const: {
8147 ImmI32Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8148 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8149 len = 1 + imm.length;
8150 optional.i32 = imm.value;
8151 break;
8152 }
8153 case kExprI64Const: {
8154 ImmI64Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8155 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8156 len = 1 + imm.length;
8157 optional.i64 = imm.value;
8158 break;
8159 }
8160 case kExprF32Const: {
8161 ImmF32Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8162 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8163 len = 1 + imm.length;
8164 optional.f32 = imm.value;
8165 break;
8166 }
8167 case kExprF64Const: {
8168 ImmF64Immediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8169 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8170 len = 1 + imm.length;
8171 optional.f64 = imm.value;
8172 break;
8173 }
8174
8175#define EXECUTE_BINOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \
8176 case kExpr##name: \
8177 break;
8178
8179 FOREACH_COMPARISON_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8180 FOREACH_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8181 FOREACH_TRAPPING_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8182 FOREACH_MORE_BINOP(EXECUTE_BINOP)
8183#undef EXECUTE_BINOP
8184
8185#define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \
8186 case kExpr##name: \
8187 break;
8188
8189 FOREACH_SIMPLE_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8190#undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8191
8192#define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \
8193 to_reg) \
8194 case kExpr##name: \
8195 break;
8196
8197 FOREACH_ADDITIONAL_CONVERT_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8198 FOREACH_CONVERT_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8199 FOREACH_REINTERPRET_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8200#undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8201
8202#define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, to_ctype, to_type, op) \
8203 case kExpr##name: \
8204 break;
8205
8206 FOREACH_BITS_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8207#undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8208
8209#define EXECUTE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, to_ctype, to_type) \
8210 case kExpr##name: \
8211 break;
8212
8213 FOREACH_EXTENSION_UNOP(EXECUTE_UNOP)
8214#undef EXECUTE_UNOP
8215
8216 case kExprRefNull: {
8217 HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), &decoder,
8218 wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8219 optional.ref_type = imm.type.representation();
8220 len = 1 + imm.length;
8221 break;
8222 }
8223 case kExprRefIsNull:
8224 case kExprRefEq:
8225 case kExprRefAsNonNull: {
8226 len = 1;
8227 break;
8228 }
8229 case kExprRefFunc: {
8230 IndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1), "function index",
8231 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8232 optional.index = imm.index;
8233 len = 1 + imm.length;
8234 break;
8235 }
8236
8237 case kGCPrefix:
8238 DecodeGCOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8239 break;
8240
8241 case kNumericPrefix:
8242 DecodeNumericOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8243 break;
8244
8245 case kAtomicPrefix:
8246 DecodeAtomicOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8247 break;
8248
8249 case kSimdPrefix: {
8250 bool is_valid_simd_op =
8251 DecodeSimdOp(opcode, &optional, &decoder, wasm_code_, pc, &len);
8252 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!is_valid_simd_op)) {
8253 UNREACHABLE();
8254 }
8255 break;
8256 }
8257
8258 case kExprCallRef:
8259 case kExprReturnCallRef: {
8260 SigIndexImmediate imm(&decoder, wasm_code_->at(pc + 1),
8261 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8262 optional.index = imm.index.index;
8263 len = 1 + imm.length;
8264 break;
8265 }
8266
8267 default:
8268 // Not implemented yet
8269 UNREACHABLE();
8270 }
8271
8272 return WasmInstruction{orig, opcode, len, static_cast<uint32_t>(pc),
8273 optional};
8274}
8275
8276void WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeGCOp(WasmOpcode opcode,
8277 WasmInstruction::Optional* optional,
8278 Decoder* decoder, InterpreterCode* code,
8279 pc_t pc, int* const len) {
8280 switch (opcode) {
8281 case kExprStructNew:
8282 case kExprStructNewDefault: {
8283 StructIndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8284 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8285 optional->index = imm.index.index;
8286 *len += imm.length;
8287 break;
8288 }
8289 case kExprStructGet:
8290 case kExprStructGetS:
8291 case kExprStructGetU:
8292 case kExprStructSet: {
8293 FieldImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8294 optional->gc_field_immediate = {imm.struct_imm.index.index,
8295 imm.field_imm.index};
8296 *len += imm.length;
8297 break;
8298 }
8299 case kExprArrayNew:
8300 case kExprArrayNewDefault:
8301 case kExprArrayGet:
8302 case kExprArrayGetS:
8303 case kExprArrayGetU:
8304 case kExprArraySet:
8305 case kExprArrayFill: {
8306 ArrayIndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8307 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8308 optional->index = imm.index.index;
8309 *len += imm.length;
8310 break;
8311 }
8312
8313 case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
8314 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8315 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8316 optional->gc_array_new_fixed.array_index = array_imm.index.index;
8317 *len += array_imm.length;
8318 IndexImmediate data_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "array length",
8319 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8320 optional->gc_array_new_fixed.length = data_imm.index;
8321 *len += data_imm.length;
8322 break;
8323 }
8324
8325 case kExprArrayNewData:
8326 case kExprArrayNewElem:
8327 case kExprArrayInitData:
8328 case kExprArrayInitElem: {
8329 ArrayIndexImmediate array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8330 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8331 optional->gc_array_new_or_init_data.array_index = array_imm.index.index;
8332 *len += array_imm.length;
8333 IndexImmediate data_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "segment index",
8334 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8335 optional->gc_array_new_or_init_data.data_index = data_imm.index;
8336 *len += data_imm.length;
8337 break;
8338 }
8339
8340 case kExprArrayCopy: {
8341 ArrayIndexImmediate dest_array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8342 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8343 optional->gc_array_copy.dest_array_index = dest_array_imm.index.index;
8344 *len += dest_array_imm.length;
8345 ArrayIndexImmediate src_array_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8346 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8347 optional->gc_array_copy.src_array_index = src_array_imm.index.index;
8348 *len += src_array_imm.length;
8349 break;
8350 }
8351
8352 case kExprRefI31:
8353 case kExprI31GetS:
8354 case kExprI31GetU:
8355 case kExprAnyConvertExtern:
8356 case kExprExternConvertAny:
8357 case kExprArrayLen:
8358 break;
8359
8360 case kExprRefCast:
8361 case kExprRefCastNull:
8362 case kExprRefTest:
8363 case kExprRefTestNull: {
8364 HeapTypeImmediate imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
8365 code->at(pc + *len), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8366 optional->gc_heap_type_immediate.length = imm.length;
8367 optional->gc_heap_type_immediate.type_representation =
8368 imm.type.representation();
8369 *len += imm.length;
8370 break;
8371 }
8372
8373 case kExprBrOnCast:
8374 case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
8375 BrOnCastImmediate flags_imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8376 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8377 *len += flags_imm.length;
8378 BranchDepthImmediate branch(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8379 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8380 *len += branch.length;
8381 HeapTypeImmediate source_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
8382 code->at(pc + *len), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8383 *len += source_imm.length;
8384 HeapTypeImmediate target_imm(WasmEnabledFeatures::All(), decoder,
8385 code->at(pc + *len), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8386 *len += target_imm.length;
8387 optional->br_on_cast_data = BranchOnCastData{
8388 branch.depth, flags_imm.flags.src_is_null,
8389 flags_imm.flags.res_is_null, target_imm.type.representation()};
8390 break;
8391 }
8392
8393 default:
8394 FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s", code->start[pc],
8395 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(code->start[pc])));
8396 UNREACHABLE();
8397 }
8398}
8399
8400void WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeNumericOp(WasmOpcode opcode,
8401 WasmInstruction::Optional* optional,
8402 Decoder* decoder,
8403 InterpreterCode* code, pc_t pc,
8404 int* const len) {
8405 switch (opcode) {
8406#define DECODE_UNOP(name, from_ctype, from_type, from_reg, to_ctype, to_type, \
8407 to_reg) \
8408 case kExpr##name: \
8409 break;
8410
8411 FOREACH_TRUNCSAT_UNOP(DECODE_UNOP)
8412#undef DECODE_UNOP
8413
8414 case kExprMemoryInit: {
8415 MemoryInitImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8416 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8417 DCHECK_LT(imm.data_segment.index, module_->num_declared_data_segments);
8418 optional->index = imm.data_segment.index;
8419 *len += imm.length;
8420 break;
8421 }
8422 case kExprDataDrop: {
8423 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "data segment index",
8424 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8425 DCHECK_LT(imm.index, module_->num_declared_data_segments);
8426 optional->index = imm.index;
8427 *len += imm.length;
8428 break;
8429 }
8430 case kExprMemoryCopy: {
8431 MemoryCopyImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8432 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8433 *len += imm.length;
8434 break;
8435 }
8436 case kExprMemoryFill: {
8437 MemoryIndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8438 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8439 *len += imm.length;
8440 break;
8441 }
8442 case kExprTableInit: {
8443 TableInitImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8444 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8445 optional->table_init.table_index = imm.table.index;
8446 optional->table_init.element_segment_index = imm.element_segment.index;
8447 *len += imm.length;
8448 break;
8449 }
8450 case kExprElemDrop: {
8451 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "element segment index",
8452 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8453 optional->index = imm.index;
8454 *len += imm.length;
8455 break;
8456 }
8457 case kExprTableCopy: {
8458 TableCopyImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8459 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8460 optional->table_copy.dst_table_index = imm.table_dst.index;
8461 optional->table_copy.src_table_index = imm.table_src.index;
8462 *len += imm.length;
8463 break;
8464 }
8465 case kExprTableGrow: {
8466 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "table index",
8467 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8468 optional->index = imm.index;
8469 *len += imm.length;
8470 break;
8471 }
8472 case kExprTableSize: {
8473 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "table index",
8474 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8475 optional->index = imm.index;
8476 *len += imm.length;
8477 break;
8478 }
8479 case kExprTableFill: {
8480 IndexImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), "table index",
8481 Decoder::kNoValidation);
8482 optional->index = imm.index;
8483 *len += imm.length;
8484 break;
8485 }
8486 default:
8487 FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s", code->start[pc],
8488 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(code->start[pc])));
8489 UNREACHABLE();
8490 }
8491}
8492
8493void WasmBytecodeGenerator::DecodeAtomicOp(WasmOpcode opcode,
8494 WasmInstruction::Optional* optional,
8495 Decoder* decoder,
8496 InterpreterCode* code, pc_t pc,
8497 int* const len) {
8498 switch (opcode) {
8499 case kExprAtomicNotify:
8500 case kExprI32AtomicWait: {
8501 MachineType memtype = MachineType::Uint32();
8502 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8503 ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()),
8504 IsMemory64(), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8505 optional->offset = imm.offset;
8506 *len += imm.length;
8507 break;
8508 }
8509 case kExprI64AtomicWait: {
8510 MachineType memtype = MachineType::Uint64();
8511 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len),
8512 ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()),
8513 IsMemory64(), Decoder::kNoValidation);
8514 optional->offset = imm.offset;
8515 *len += imm.length;
8516 break;
8517 }
8518 case kExprAtomicFence:
8519 *len += 1;
8520 break;
8521
8522#define ATOMIC_BINOP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type, operation) \
8523 case kExpr##name: { \
8524 MachineType memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
8525 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), \
8526 ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()), \
8527 IsMemory64(), Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8528 optional->offset = imm.offset; \
8529 *len += imm.length; \
8530 break; \
8531 }
8532 FOREACH_ATOMIC_BINOP(ATOMIC_BINOP)
8533#undef ATOMIC_BINOP
8534
8535#define ATOMIC_OP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type) \
8536 case kExpr##name: { \
8537 MachineType memtype = MachineType::Type(); \
8538 MemoryAccessImmediate imm(decoder, code->at(pc + *len), \
8539 ElementSizeLog2Of(memtype.representation()), \
8540 IsMemory64(), Decoder::kNoValidation); \
8541 optional->offset = imm.offset; \
8542 *len += imm.length; \
8543 break; \
8544 }
8545 FOREACH_ATOMIC_COMPARE_EXCHANGE_OP(ATOMIC_OP)
8546 FOREACH_ATOMIC_LOAD_OP(ATOMIC_OP)
8547 FOREACH_ATOMIC_STORE_OP(ATOMIC_OP)
8548#undef ATOMIC_OP
8549
8550 default:
8551 FATAL("Unknown or unimplemented opcode #%d:%s", code->start[pc],
8552 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(code->start[pc])));
8553 UNREACHABLE();
8554 }
8555}

8557const char* GetRegModeString(RegMode reg_mode) {
8558 switch (reg_mode) {
8559 case RegMode::kNoReg:
8560 return "NoReg";
8561 case RegMode::kAnyReg:
8562 return "AnyReg";
8563 case RegMode::kI32Reg:
8564 return "I32Reg";
8565 case RegMode::kI64Reg:
8566 return "I64Reg";
8567 case RegMode::kF32Reg:
8568 return "F32Reg";
8569 case RegMode::kF64Reg:
8570 return "F64Reg";
8571 default:
8572 UNREACHABLE();
8573 }
8574}

8580 case kR2S:
8581 return "R2S";
8582 case kS2R:
8583 return "S2R";
8584 case kS2S:
8585 return "S2S";
8586 default:
8587 UNREACHABLE();
8588 }
8589}

8605// static
8606void WasmInterpreter::GlobalTearDown() {
8607 // TODO(paolosev@microsoft.com): Support multithreading.
8608
8609#ifdef DRUMBRAKE_ENABLE_PROFILING
8610 PrintAndClearProfilingData();
8611#endif // DRUMBRAKE_ENABLE_PROFILING
8612
8613 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
8614 WasmBytecodeGenerator::PrintBytecodeCompressionStats();
8615 }
8616
8617 WasmInterpreterThread::Terminate();
8618}
8619
8620// static
8621void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PrintBytecodeCompressionStats() {
8622 printf("Total bytecode size: %zu bytes.\n", total_bytecode_size_);
8623 size_t space_saved_in_bytes = 2 * emitted_short_slot_offset_count_ +
8624 4 * emitted_short_memory_offset_count_;
8625 double saved_pct = (total_bytecode_size_ + space_saved_in_bytes == 0)
8626 ? .0
8627 : 100.0 * space_saved_in_bytes /
8628 (total_bytecode_size_ + space_saved_in_bytes);
8629 printf("Bytes saved: %zu (%.1f%%).\n", space_saved_in_bytes, saved_pct);
8630}
8631
8632void WasmBytecodeGenerator::InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(const FunctionSig* sig,
8633 bool is_indirect_call) {
8634 size_t stack_index;
8635 if (is_indirect_call) {
8636 // Subtract one to discard the function index on the top of the stack.
8637 DCHECK_LE(sig->parameter_count(), stack_.size() - 1);
8638 stack_index = stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count() - 1;
8639 } else {
8640 DCHECK_LE(sig->parameter_count(), stack_.size());
8641 stack_index = stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count();
8642 }
8643
8644 bool fast_path = sig->parameter_count() > 1 && sig->parameter_count() < 32 &&
8645 !WasmBytecode::HasRefOrSimdArgs(sig);
8646 if (fast_path) {
8647 if (sig->parameter_count() == 2) {
8648 const ValueType type0 = sig->GetParam(0);
8649 const ValueKind kind0 = type0.kind();
8650 ValueType type1 = sig->GetParam(1);
8651 const ValueKind kind1 = type1.kind();
8652 uint32_t to = CreateSlot(type0);
8653 CreateSlot(type1);
8654
8655 uint32_t copyslot32_two_args_func_id =
8656 ((kind0 == kI64 || kind0 == kF64) ? 0x01 : 0x00) |
8657 ((kind1 == kI64 || kind1 == kF64) ? 0x02 : 0x00);
8658 static const InstructionHandler kCopySlot32TwoArgFuncs[4] = {
8659 k_s2s_CopySlot_ll, k_s2s_CopySlot_lq, k_s2s_CopySlot_ql,
8660 k_s2s_CopySlot_qq};
8661
8662 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER() {
8663 EmitFnId(kCopySlot32TwoArgFuncs[copyslot32_two_args_func_id]);
8664 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to].slot_offset);
8665 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
8666 stack_index++;
8667 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
8668 stack_index++;
8669 }
8670 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
8671 } else {
8672 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(s2s_CopySlotMulti) {
8673 EmitI32Const(static_cast<uint32_t>(sig->parameter_count()));
8674
8675 uint32_t arg_size_mask = 0;
8676 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
8677 const ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(index);
8678 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
8679 if (kind == kI64 || kind == kF64) {
8680 arg_size_mask |= (1 << index);
8681 }
8682 }
8683 EmitI32Const(arg_size_mask);
8684
8685 uint32_t to = 0;
8686 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
8687 const ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(index);
8688 to = CreateSlot(value_type);
8689 if (index == 0) {
8690 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[to].slot_offset);
8691 }
8692 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
8693 stack_index++;
8694 }
8695 }
8696 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
8697 }
8698 } else {
8699 // Slow path.
8700 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count(); index++) {
8701 ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(index);
8702 uint32_t to = CreateSlot(value_type);
8703 EmitCopySlot(value_type, stack_[stack_index], to);
8704 stack_index++;
8705 }
8706 }
8707}
8708
8709// static
8710void WasmInterpreter::NotifyIsolateDisposal(Isolate* isolate) {
8711 WasmInterpreterThread::NotifyIsolateDisposal(isolate);
8712}
8713
8714// Checks if {obj} is a subtype of type, thus checking will always
8715// succeed.
8716bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(ValueType obj_type,
8717 HeapType type) const {
8718 return IsSubtypeOf(obj_type, ValueType::RefNull(type), module_);
8719}
8720
8721// Returns true if type checking will always fail, either because the types
8722// are unrelated or because the target_type is one of the null sentinels and
8723// conversion to null does not succeed.
8724bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::TypeCheckAlwaysFails(ValueType obj_type,
8725 HeapType expected_type,
8726 bool null_succeeds) const {
8727 bool types_unrelated =
8728 !IsSubtypeOf(ValueType::Ref(expected_type), obj_type, module_) &&
8729 !IsSubtypeOf(obj_type, ValueType::RefNull(expected_type), module_);
8730 // (Comment copied from function-body-decoder-impl.h).
8731 // For "unrelated" types the check can still succeed for the null value on
8732 // instructions treating null as a successful check.
8733 // TODO(12868): For string views, this implementation anticipates that
8734 // https://github.com/WebAssembly/stringref/issues/40 will be resolved
8735 // by making the views standalone types.
8736 return (types_unrelated &&
8737 (!null_succeeds || !obj_type.is_nullable() ||
8738 obj_type.is_string_view() || expected_type.is_string_view())) ||
8739 (!null_succeeds &&
8740 (expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNone ||
8741 expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoFunc ||
8742 expected_type.representation() == HeapType::kNoExtern));
8743}
