9251#endif // DEBUG
9252
9253RegMode WasmBytecodeGenerator::EncodeInstruction(const WasmInstruction& instr,
9254 RegMode curr_reg_mode,
9255 RegMode next_reg_mode) {
9256 if (!v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
9257 DCHECK_EQ(handler_size_, InstrHandlerSize::Large);
9258 return DoEncodeInstruction(instr, curr_reg_mode, next_reg_mode);
9259 }
9260
9261 size_t current_instr_code_offset = code_.size();
9262 size_t current_slots_size = slots_.size();
9263 current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
9264 handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Small;
9265 stack_.clear_history();
9266
9267 RegMode reg_mode = DoEncodeInstruction(instr, curr_reg_mode, next_reg_mode);
9268 if (current_instr_encoding_failed_) {
9269 DCHECK(!HasSideEffects(instr.opcode));
9270 code_.resize(current_instr_code_offset);
9271 slots_.resize(current_slots_size);
9272 stack_.rollback();
9273 current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
9274 handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Large;
9275 reg_mode = DoEncodeInstruction(instr, curr_reg_mode, next_reg_mode);
9276 DCHECK(!current_instr_encoding_failed_);
9277 }
9278
9279 return reg_mode;
9280}
9281
9282RegMode WasmBytecodeGenerator::DoEncodeInstruction(const WasmInstruction& instr,
9283 RegMode curr_reg_mode,
9284 RegMode next_reg_mode) {
9285 DCHECK(curr_reg_mode != RegMode::kAnyReg);
9286
9287#ifdef DEBUG
9288 was_current_instruction_reachable_ = is_instruction_reachable_;
9289#endif // DEBUG
9290 if (!is_instruction_reachable_) {
9291 if (instr.opcode == kExprBlock || instr.opcode == kExprLoop ||
9292 instr.opcode == kExprIf || instr.opcode == kExprTry) {
9293 unreachable_block_count_++;
9294 } else if (instr.opcode == kExprEnd || instr.opcode == kExprDelegate) {
9295 DCHECK_GT(unreachable_block_count_, 0);
9296 if (0 == --unreachable_block_count_) {
9297 is_instruction_reachable_ = true;
9298 }
9299 } else if (instr.opcode == kExprElse || instr.opcode == kExprCatch ||
9300 instr.opcode == kExprCatchAll) {
9301 if (1 == unreachable_block_count_) {
9302 is_instruction_reachable_ = true;
9303 unreachable_block_count_ = 0;
9304 }
9305 }
9306 }
9307 if (!is_instruction_reachable_) return RegMode::kNoReg;
9308
9309 ValueKind top_stack_slot_type = GetTopStackType(curr_reg_mode);
9310
9311 OperatorMode mode = kS2S;
9312 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_register_optimization) {
9313 switch (next_reg_mode) {
9314 case RegMode::kNoReg:
9315 if (curr_reg_mode != RegMode::kNoReg) {
9316 mode = kR2S;
9317 }
9318 break;
9319 case RegMode::kAnyReg:
9320 default: // kI32Reg|kI64Reg|kF32Reg|kF64Reg
9321 if (curr_reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
9322 if (ToRegisterIsAllowed(instr)) {
9323 mode = kS2R;
9324 } else {
9325 mode = kS2S;
9326 }
9327 } else {
9328 if (ToRegisterIsAllowed(instr)) {
9329 mode = kR2R;
9330 } else {
9331 mode = kR2S;
9332 }
9333 }
9334 break;
9335 }
9336 }
9337
9338#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
9339 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_bytecode_generator) {
9340 printf("PRE @%-3u: %-24s: %3s %-7s -> %-7s\n", instr.pc,
9341 wasm::WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(static_cast<WasmOpcode>(instr.opcode)),
9342 GetOperatorModeString(mode), GetRegModeString(curr_reg_mode),
9343 GetRegModeString(next_reg_mode));
9344 }
9345
9346 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
9347 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_TraceInstruction);
9348 EmitI32Const(instr.pc);
9349 EmitI32Const(instr.opcode);
9350 EmitI32Const(static_cast<int>(curr_reg_mode));
9351 }
9352#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
9353
9354 switch (instr.opcode) {
9355 case kExprUnreachable: {
9356 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Unreachable, instr.pc);
9357 SetUnreachableMode();
9358 break;
9359 }
9360 case kExprNop:
9361 break;
9362 case kExprBlock:
9363 case kExprLoop: {
9364 PreserveArgsAndLocals();
9365 BeginBlock(instr.opcode, instr.optional.block);
9366 break;
9367 }
9368 case kExprTry: {
9369 PreserveArgsAndLocals();
9370 int parent_or_matching_try_block_index = GetCurrentTryBlockIndex(true);
9371 int ancestor_try_block_index = GetCurrentTryBlockIndex(false);
9372 int try_block_index = BeginBlock(instr.opcode, instr.optional.block);
9373 eh_data_.AddTryBlock(try_block_index, parent_or_matching_try_block_index,
9374 ancestor_try_block_index);
9375 break;
9376 }
9377 case kExprIf: {
9378 PreserveArgsAndLocals();
9379 if (mode == kR2S) {
9380 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_If);
9381 } else {
9382 DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9383 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_If);
9384 I32Pop(); // cond
9385 }
9386 BeginBlock(instr.opcode, instr.optional.block);
9387 EmitIfElseBranchOffset();
9388 break;
9389 }
9390 case kExprElse: {
9391 DCHECK_GT(current_block_index_, 0);
9392 DCHECK(blocks_[current_block_index_].IsIf());
9393 BeginElseBlock(current_block_index_, false);
9394 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Else);
9395 EmitIfElseBranchOffset(); // Jumps to the end of the 'else' block.
9396 break;
9397 }
9398 case kExprCatch:
9399 case kExprCatchAll: {
9400 DCHECK_GT(current_block_index_, 0);
9401
9402 int try_block_index = eh_data_.GetCurrentTryBlockIndex();
9403 DCHECK_GT(try_block_index, 0);
9404
9405 EndBlock(instr.opcode); // End previous try or catch.
9406
9407 stack_.resize(blocks_[try_block_index].stack_size_);
9408 int32_t catch_block_index =
9409 BeginBlock(instr.opcode, blocks_[try_block_index].signature_);
9410
9411 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Catch);
9412 EmitTryCatchBranchOffset(); // Jumps to the end of the try/catch blocks.
9413
9414 uint32_t first_param_slot_index = UINT_MAX;
9415 uint32_t first_ref_param_slot_index = UINT_MAX;
9416 if (instr.opcode == kExprCatch) {
9417 // Exception arguments are pushed into the stack.
9418 const WasmTag& tag = module_->tags[instr.optional.index];
9419 const FunctionSig* sig = tag.sig;
9420 for (size_t i = 0; i < sig->parameter_count(); ++i) {
9421 const ValueType value_type = sig->GetParam(i);
9422 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
9423 switch (kind) {
9424 case kI32:
9425 case kI64:
9426 case kF32:
9427 case kF64:
9428 case kS128:
9429 case kRef:
9430 case kRefNull: {
9431 uint32_t slot_index = CreateSlot(value_type);
9432 if (first_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX) {
9433 first_param_slot_index = slot_index;
9434 }
9435 if ((kind == kRefNull || kind == kRef) &&
9436 first_ref_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX) {
9437 first_ref_param_slot_index = slot_index;
9438 }
9439 PushSlot(slot_index);
9440 slots_[slot_index].value_type = value_type;
9441 break;
9442 }
9443 default:
9444 UNREACHABLE();
9445 }
9446 }
9447 }
9448
9449 blocks_[catch_block_index].first_block_index_ =
9450 blocks_[try_block_index].first_block_index_;
9451
9452 if (instr.opcode == kExprCatch) {
9453 eh_data_.AddCatchBlock(
9454 current_block_index_, instr.optional.index,
9455 first_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX
9456 ? 0
9457 : slots_[first_param_slot_index].slot_offset,
9458 first_ref_param_slot_index == UINT_MAX
9459 ? 0
9460 : slots_[first_ref_param_slot_index].ref_stack_index,
9461 static_cast<int>(code_.size()));
9462 } else { // kExprCatchAll
9463 eh_data_.AddCatchBlock(current_block_index_,
9464 WasmEHData::kCatchAllTagIndex, 0, 0,
9465 static_cast<int>(code_.size()));
9466 }
9467
9468 break;
9469 }
9470 case kExprDelegate: {
9471 int32_t target_block_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth + 1);
9472 DCHECK_LT(target_block_index, blocks_.size());
9473 int32_t delegated_try_block_index = WasmEHData::kDelegateToCallerIndex;
9474 if (target_block_index > 0) {
9475 const BlockData& target_block = blocks_[target_block_index];
9476 delegated_try_block_index = target_block.IsTry()
9477 ? target_block_index
9478 : target_block.parent_try_block_index_;
9479 }
9480 eh_data_.AddDelegatedBlock(delegated_try_block_index);
9481 EndBlock(kExprDelegate);
9482 break;
9483 }
9484 case kExprThrow: {
9485 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Throw);
9486 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
9487
9488 // Exception arguments are popped from the stack (in reverse order!)
9489 const WasmTag& tag = module_->tags[instr.optional.index];
9490 const WasmTagSig* sig = tag.sig;
9491 DCHECK_GE(stack_.size(), sig->parameter_count());
9492 size_t stack_index = stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count();
9493 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->parameter_count();
9494 index++, stack_index++) {
9495 ValueKind kind = sig->GetParam(index).kind();
9496 DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(kind, slots_[stack_[stack_index]].kind()));
9497 switch (kind) {
9498 case kI32:
9499 case kI64:
9500 case kF32:
9501 case kF64:
9502 case kS128: {
9503 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[stack_index]].slot_offset);
9504 break;
9505 }
9506 case kRef:
9507 case kRefNull: {
9508 uint32_t ref_index = slots_[stack_[stack_index]].ref_stack_index;
9509 Emit(&ref_index, sizeof(uint32_t));
9510 break;
9511 }
9512 default:
9513 UNREACHABLE();
9514 }
9515 }
9516
9517 stack_.resize(stack_.size() - sig->parameter_count());
9518 eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
9519 CurrentCodePos());
9520 SetUnreachableMode();
9521 break;
9522 }
9523 case kExprRethrow: {
9524 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Rethrow);
9525 int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9526 DCHECK(blocks_[target_branch_index].IsCatch() ||
9527 blocks_[target_branch_index].IsCatchAll());
9528 Emit(&target_branch_index, sizeof(int32_t));
9529 eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
9530 CurrentCodePos());
9531 SetUnreachableMode();
9532 break;
9533 }
9534 case kExprEnd: {
9535 // If there is an 'if...end' statement without an 'else' branch, create
9536 // a dummy else branch used to store results.
9537 if (blocks_[current_block_index_].IsIf()) {
9538 uint32_t if_block_index = current_block_index_;
9539 DCHECK(!blocks_[if_block_index].HasElseBranch());
9540 uint32_t params_count = ParamsCount(blocks_[if_block_index]);
9541 if (params_count > 0) {
9542 BeginElseBlock(if_block_index, true);
9543 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Else);
9544 EmitIfElseBranchOffset(); // Jumps to the end of the 'else' block.
9545 }
9546 }
9547
9548 if (EndBlock(kExprEnd) < 0) {
9549 Return();
9550 }
9551 break;
9552 }
9553 case kExprBr: {
9554 int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9555 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBr);
9556
9557 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9558 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9559 SetUnreachableMode();
9560 break;
9561 }
9562 case kExprBrIf: {
9563 int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9564 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9565 blocks_[target_branch_index];
9566 if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9567 if (mode == kR2S) {
9568 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BranchIf);
9569 } else {
9570 DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9571 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchIf);
9572 I32Pop(); // condition
9573 }
9574 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9575 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9576 } else {
9577 if (mode == kR2S) {
9578 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BranchIfWithParams);
9579 } else {
9580 DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9581 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchIfWithParams);
9582 I32Pop(); // condition
9583 }
9584
9585 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9586 const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9587 Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9588
9589 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9590
9591 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9592 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9593
9594 // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9595 int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9596 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9597 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9598 delta);
9599 }
9600 break;
9601 }
9602 case kExprBrOnNull: {
9603 DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9604 int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9605 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9606 blocks_[target_branch_index];
9607 if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9608 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9609 ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9610 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9611 // Remove nullability.
9612 if (value_type.kind() == kRefNull) {
9613 value_type = ValueType::Ref(value_type.heap_type());
9614 }
9615 RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9616 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9617 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9618 } else {
9619 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNullWithParams);
9620 ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9621 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9622 // Remove nullability.
9623 if (value_type.kind() == kRefNull) {
9624 value_type = ValueType::Ref(value_type.heap_type());
9625 }
9626 RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9627
9628 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9629 const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9630 Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9631
9632 uint32_t stack_top = stack_.back();
9633 RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9634
9635 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9636
9637 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9638 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9639
9640 stack_.push_back(stack_top); // re-push non-null ref on top of stack
9641
9642 // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9643 int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9644 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9645 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9646 delta);
9647 }
9648 break;
9649 }
9650 case kExprBrOnNonNull: {
9651 DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9652 int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(instr.optional.depth);
9653 const WasmBytecodeGenerator::BlockData& target_block_data =
9654 blocks_[target_branch_index];
9655 if (HasVoidSignature(target_block_data)) {
9656 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNonNull);
9657 ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9658 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9659 RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9660 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is true.
9661 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9662
9663 RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9664 } else {
9665 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNonNullWithParams);
9666 ValueType value_type = RefPop(); // pop condition
9667 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9668 RefPush(value_type); // re-push condition value
9669
9670 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9671 const uint32_t if_false_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9672 Emit(&if_false_code_offset, sizeof(if_false_code_offset));
9673
9674 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrIf);
9675
9676 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9677 EmitBranchOffset(instr.optional.depth);
9678
9679 // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9680 int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - if_false_code_offset;
9681 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9682 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + if_false_code_offset),
9683 delta);
9684
9685 RefPop(false); // Drop the null reference.
9686 }
9687 break;
9688 }
9689 case kExprBrOnCast: {
9690 const BranchOnCastData& br_on_cast_data = instr.optional.br_on_cast_data;
9691 const int32_t target_branch_index =
9692 GetTargetBranch(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9693 bool null_succeeds = br_on_cast_data.res_is_null;
9694 const ValueType target_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
9695 ModuleTypeIndex({br_on_cast_data.target_type}),
9696 null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
9697
9698 const ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
9699 DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
9700
9701 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions can
9702 // only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
9703 if (V8_UNLIKELY(
9704 TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type.heap_type()))) {
9705 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9706 // The branch will still not be taken on null if not {null_succeeds}.
9707 if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
9708 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9709 RefPop(); // pop condition
9710 EmitRefValueType(obj_type.raw_bit_field());
9711 RefPush(target_type); // re-push condition value with a new HeapType.
9712 EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9713 } else {
9714 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9715 EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9716 }
9717 } else if (V8_LIKELY(!TypeCheckAlwaysFails(
9718 obj_type, target_type.heap_type(), null_succeeds))) {
9719 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnCast);
9720 EmitI32Const(null_succeeds);
9721 HeapType br_on_cast_data_target_type(
9722 ModuleTypeIndex({br_on_cast_data.target_type}));
9723 EmitI32Const(br_on_cast_data_target_type.is_index()
9724 ? br_on_cast_data_target_type.representation()
9725 : target_type.heap_type().representation());
9726 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
9727 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9728 RefPush(value_type);
9729 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9730 const uint32_t no_branch_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9731 Emit(&no_branch_code_offset, sizeof(no_branch_code_offset));
9732 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9733 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9734 EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9735 // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9736 int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - no_branch_code_offset;
9737 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9738 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + no_branch_code_offset),
9739 delta);
9740 }
9741 break;
9742 }
9743 case kExprBrOnCastFail: {
9744 const BranchOnCastData& br_on_cast_data = instr.optional.br_on_cast_data;
9745 int32_t target_branch_index =
9746 GetTargetBranch(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9747 bool null_succeeds = br_on_cast_data.res_is_null;
9748 HeapType br_on_cast_data_target_type(
9749 ModuleTypeIndex({br_on_cast_data.target_type}));
9750 const ValueType target_type =
9751 ValueType::RefMaybeNull(br_on_cast_data_target_type,
9752 null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
9753
9754 const ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
9755 DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
9756
9757 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions can
9758 // only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
9759 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type.heap_type(),
9760 null_succeeds))) {
9761 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9762 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9763 EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9764 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(
9765 obj_type, target_type.heap_type()))) {
9766 // The branch can still be taken on null.
9767 if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
9768 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index,
9769 kExprBrOnCast);
9770 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnNull);
9771 RefPop(); // pop condition
9772 EmitRefValueType(obj_type.raw_bit_field());
9773 RefPush(target_type); // re-push condition value with a new HeapType.
9774 EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9775 } else {
9776 // Fallthrough.
9777 }
9778 } else {
9779 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BranchOnCastFail);
9780 EmitI32Const(null_succeeds);
9781 EmitI32Const(br_on_cast_data_target_type.is_index()
9782 ? br_on_cast_data_target_type.representation()
9783 : target_type.heap_type().representation());
9784 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
9785 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
9786 RefPush(value_type);
9787 // Emit code offset to branch to if the condition is not true.
9788 const uint32_t no_branch_code_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9789 Emit(&no_branch_code_offset, sizeof(no_branch_code_offset));
9790 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrOnCast);
9791 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9792 EmitBranchOffset(br_on_cast_data.label_depth);
9793 // Patch the 'if-false' offset with the correct jump offset.
9794 int32_t delta = CurrentCodePos() - no_branch_code_offset;
9795 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9796 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + no_branch_code_offset),
9797 delta);
9798 }
9799 break;
9800 }
9801 case kExprBrTable: {
9802 if (mode == kR2S) {
9803 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_BrTable);
9804 } else {
9805 DCHECK_EQ(mode, kS2S);
9806 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_BrTable);
9807 I32Pop(); // branch label
9808 }
9809
9810 // We emit the following bytecode for a br_table instruction:
9811 // s2s_BrTable handler id
9812 // (uint32) labels_count
9813 // (uint32) offset branch 0
9814 // (uint32) offset branch 1
9815 // ...
9816 // (uint32) offset branch labels_count - 1
9817 // (uint32) offset branch labels_count (default branch)
9818 // { Branch 0 slots }
9819 // { Branch 1 slots }
9820 // ...
9821 // { Branch labels_count slots }
9822 //
9823 // Where each {Branch i slots} contains the slots to execute a Branch
9824 // instruction:
9825 // { CopySlots for branch results, if present }
9826 // s2s_Branch handler id
9827 // (uint32) branch_offset (to be patched later)
9828 //
9829 const uint32_t labels_count = instr.optional.br_table.table_count;
9830 EmitI32Const(labels_count);
9831 uint32_t labels_offset_start = CurrentCodePos();
9832 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= labels_count; i++) {
9833 // Here we don't know what will be the offset of this branch yet, so we
9834 // pass the current bytecode position as offset. This value will be
9835 // overwritten in the next loop.
9836 const uint32_t label_offset = CurrentCodePos();
9837 Emit(&label_offset, sizeof(label_offset));
9838 }
9839 for (uint32_t i = 0; i <= labels_count; i++) {
9840 uint32_t label =
9841 br_table_labels_[instr.optional.br_table.labels_index + i];
9842 int32_t target_branch_index = GetTargetBranch(label);
9843 uint32_t branch_code_start = CurrentCodePos();
9844 StoreBlockParamsAndResultsIntoSlots(target_branch_index, kExprBrTable);
9845
9846 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Branch);
9847 EmitBranchTableOffset(label, CurrentCodePos());
9848
9849 // Patch the branch offset with the correct jump offset.
9850 uint32_t label_offset = labels_offset_start + i * sizeof(uint32_t);
9851 int32_t delta = branch_code_start - label_offset;
9852 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
9853 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + label_offset), delta);
9854 }
9855 SetUnreachableMode();
9856 break;
9857 }
9858 case kExprReturn: {
9859 Return();
9860 SetUnreachableMode();
9861 break;
9862 }
9863 case kExprCallFunction:
9864 case kExprReturnCall: {
9865 uint32_t function_index = instr.optional.index;
9866 const FunctionSig* sig = GetFunctionSignature(function_index);
9867
9868 // Layout of a frame:
9869 // ------------------
9870 // stack slot #N-1 â€¾\
9871 // ... |
9872 // stack slot #0 _/
9873 // local #L-1 â€¾\
9874 // ... |
9875 // local #0 _/
9876 // const #C-1 â€¾\
9877 // ... |
9878 // const #0 _/
9879 // param #P-1 â€¾\
9880 // ... |
9881 // param #0 _/
9882 // return #R-1 â€¾\
9883 // ... |
9884 // return #0 _/
9885 // ------------------
9886
9887 const bool is_imported = (module_->functions[function_index].imported);
9888 const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCall);
9889 uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
9890 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
9891
9892 std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
9893 rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
9894 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
9895 rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
9896 : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
9897 }
9898
9899 InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, false);
9900
9901 if (is_imported) {
9902 if (is_tail_call) {
9903 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallImportedFunction, instr.pc);
9904 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9905 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9906 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
9907 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
9908 } else {
9909 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallImportedFunction, instr.pc);
9910 }
9911 } else {
9912 if (is_tail_call) {
9913 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCall, instr.pc);
9914 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9915 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
9916 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
9917 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
9918 } else {
9919 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallFunction, instr.pc);
9920 }
9921 }
9922 EmitI32Const(function_index);
9923 EmitStackIndex(static_cast<uint32_t>(stack_.size()));
9924 EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
9925 EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
9926
9927 // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
9928 for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
9929 Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
9930 }
9931
9932#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
9933 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
9934 EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
9935 ? 0
9936 : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
9937 }
9938#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
9939
9940 if (!is_tail_call) {
9941 eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
9942 CurrentCodePos());
9943 }
9944
9945 // Function results are pushed to the stack.
9946 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
9947 const ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
9948 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
9949 switch (kind) {
9950 case kI32:
9951 case kI64:
9952 case kF32:
9953 case kF64:
9954 case kS128:
9955 case kRef:
9956 case kRefNull:
9957 PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
9958 SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
9959 break;
9960 default:
9961 UNREACHABLE();
9962 }
9963 }
9964
9965 // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
9966 // unreachable.
9967 if (is_tail_call) {
9968 SetUnreachableMode();
9969 }
9970
9971 return RegMode::kNoReg;
9972 }
9973 case kExprCallIndirect:
9974 case kExprReturnCallIndirect: {
9975 const FunctionSig* sig = module_->signature(
9976 ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.indirect_call.sig_index}));
9977
9978 const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCallIndirect);
9979 uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
9980 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
9981
9982 // Reserve space for return values.
9983 std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
9984 rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
9985 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
9986 rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
9987 : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
9988 }
9989
9990 InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, true);
9991
9992 bool is_table64 =
9993 module_->tables[instr.optional.indirect_call.table_index]
9994 .is_table64();
9995
9996 if (is_tail_call) {
9997 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallIndirect,
9998 s2s_ReturnCallIndirect64, is_table64,
9999 instr.pc);
10000 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10001 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10002 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
10003 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
10004 } else {
10005 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallIndirect, s2s_CallIndirect64,
10006 is_table64, instr.pc);
10007 }
10008
10009 // Pops the index of the function to call.
10010 is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
10011
10012 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.indirect_call.table_index);
10013 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.indirect_call.sig_index);
10014
10015 EmitStackIndex(stack_size());
10016 EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
10017 EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
10018
10019 // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
10020 for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
10021 Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10022 }
10023
10024#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10025 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10026 EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10027 ? 0
10028 : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10029 }
10030#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10031
10032 if (!is_tail_call) {
10033 eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10034 CurrentCodePos());
10035 }
10036
10037 // Function result is pushed to the stack.
10038 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10039 ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10040 switch (value_type.kind()) {
10041 case kI32:
10042 case kI64:
10043 case kF32:
10044 case kF64:
10045 case kS128:
10046 case kRef:
10047 case kRefNull:
10048 PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10049 SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10050 break;
10051 default:
10052 UNREACHABLE();
10053 }
10054 }
10055
10056 // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10057 // unreachable.
10058 if (is_tail_call) {
10059 SetUnreachableMode();
10060 }
10061
10062 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10063 }
10064
10065 case kExprCallRef:
10066 case kExprReturnCallRef: {
10067 const FunctionSig* sig =
10068 module_->signature(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index}));
10069 const bool is_tail_call = (instr.opcode == kExprReturnCallRef);
10070 uint32_t slot_offset = GetStackFrameSize() * kSlotSize;
10071 uint32_t ref_stack_fp_offset = ref_slots_count_;
10072
10073 // Reserve space for return values.
10074 std::vector<uint32_t> rets_slots;
10075 rets_slots.resize(sig->return_count());
10076 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10077 rets_slots[index] = is_tail_call ? static_cast<uint32_t>(index)
10078 : CreateSlot(sig->GetReturn(index));
10079 }
10080
10081 InitSlotsForFunctionArgs(sig, true);
10082
10083 if (is_tail_call) {
10084 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ReturnCallRef, instr.pc);
10085 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::RetsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10086 EmitSlotOffset(WasmBytecode::ArgsSizeInSlots(sig) * kSlotSize);
10087 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefRetsCount(sig));
10088 EmitI32Const(WasmBytecode::RefArgsCount(sig));
10089 } else {
10090 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_CallRef, instr.pc);
10091 }
10092
10093 // Pops the function to call.
10094 RefPop();
10095
10096 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index); // Signature index.
10097 EmitStackIndex(stack_size());
10098 EmitSlotOffset(slot_offset);
10099 EmitRefStackIndex(ref_stack_fp_offset);
10100
10101 // Function arguments are popped from the stack.
10102 for (size_t index = sig->parameter_count(); index > 0; index--) {
10103 Pop(sig->GetParam(index - 1).kind(), false);
10104 }
10105
10106#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10107 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_execution) {
10108 EmitSlotOffset(rets_slots.empty()
10109 ? 0
10110 : slots_[rets_slots[0]].slot_offset * kSlotSize);
10111 }
10112#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
10113
10114 if (!is_tail_call) {
10115 eh_data_.RecordPotentialExceptionThrowingInstruction(instr.opcode,
10116 CurrentCodePos());
10117 }
10118
10119 // Function result is pushed to the stack.
10120 for (size_t index = 0; index < sig->return_count(); index++) {
10121 const ValueType value_type = sig->GetReturn(index);
10122 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10123 switch (kind) {
10124 case kI32:
10125 case kI64:
10126 case kF32:
10127 case kF64:
10128 case kS128:
10129 case kRef:
10130 case kRefNull:
10131 PushSlot(rets_slots[index]);
10132 SetSlotType(stack_top_index(), value_type);
10133 break;
10134 default:
10135 UNREACHABLE();
10136 }
10137 }
10138
10139 // If this is a tail call, the following instructions in this block are
10140 // unreachable.
10141 if (is_tail_call) {
10142 SetUnreachableMode();
10143 }
10144
10145 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10146 }
10147
10148 case kExprDrop: {
10149 switch (top_stack_slot_type) {
10150 case kI32:
10151 switch (mode) {
10152 case kR2R:
10153 case kS2R:
10154 UNREACHABLE();
10155 case kR2S:
10156 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I32Drop);
10157 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10158 case kS2S:
10159 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32Drop);
10160 I32Pop();
10161 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10162 }
10163 break;
10164 case kI64:
10165 switch (mode) {
10166 case kR2R:
10167 case kS2R:
10168 UNREACHABLE();
10169 case kR2S:
10170 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I64Drop);
10171 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10172 case kS2S:
10173 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64Drop);
10174 I64Pop();
10175 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10176 }
10177 break;
10178 case kF32:
10179 switch (mode) {
10180 case kR2R:
10181 case kS2R:
10182 UNREACHABLE();
10183 case kR2S:
10184 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F32Drop);
10185 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10186 case kS2S:
10187 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32Drop);
10188 F32Pop();
10189 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10190 }
10191 break;
10192 case kF64:
10193 switch (mode) {
10194 case kR2R:
10195 case kS2R:
10196 UNREACHABLE();
10197 case kR2S:
10198 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F64Drop);
10199 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10200 case kS2S:
10201 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64Drop);
10202 F64Pop();
10203 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10204 }
10205 break;
10206 case kS128:
10207 switch (mode) {
10208 case kR2R:
10209 case kR2S:
10210 case kS2R:
10211 UNREACHABLE();
10212 case kS2S:
10213 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128Drop);
10214 S128Pop();
10215 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10216 }
10217 break;
10218 case kRef:
10219 case kRefNull:
10220 switch (mode) {
10221 case kR2R:
10222 case kS2R:
10223 UNREACHABLE();
10224 case kR2S:
10225 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_RefDrop);
10226 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10227 case kS2S:
10228 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefDrop);
10229 RefPop();
10230 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10231 }
10232 break;
10233 default:
10234 UNREACHABLE();
10235 }
10236 break;
10237 }
10238 case kExprSelect:
10239 case kExprSelectWithType: {
10240 DCHECK_GE(stack_size(), 2);
10241 switch (slots_[stack_[stack_size() - 2]].kind()) {
10242 case kI32:
10243 switch (mode) {
10244 case kR2R:
10245 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_I32Select);
10246 I32Pop(); // val2
10247 I32Pop(); // val1
10248 return RegMode::kI32Reg;
10249 case kR2S:
10250 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I32Select);
10251 I32Pop(); // val2
10252 I32Pop(); // val1
10253 I32Push(); // result
10254 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10255 case kS2R:
10256 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I32Select);
10257 I32Pop(); // condition
10258 I32Pop(); // val2
10259 I32Pop(); // val1
10260 return RegMode::kI32Reg;
10261 case kS2S:
10262 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32Select);
10263 I32Pop(); // condition
10264 I32Pop(); // val2
10265 I32Pop(); // val1
10266 I32Push(); // result
10267 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10268 }
10269 break;
10270 case kI64:
10271 switch (mode) {
10272 case kR2R:
10273 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_I64Select);
10274 I64Pop(); // val2
10275 I64Pop(); // val1
10276 return RegMode::kI64Reg;
10277 case kR2S:
10278 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I64Select);
10279 I64Pop(); // val2
10280 I64Pop(); // val1
10281 I64Push(); // result
10282 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10283 case kS2R:
10284 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I64Select);
10285 I32Pop(); // condition
10286 I64Pop(); // val2
10287 I64Pop(); // val1
10288 return RegMode::kI64Reg;
10289 case kS2S:
10290 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64Select);
10291 I32Pop(); // condition
10292 I64Pop();
10293 I64Pop();
10294 I64Push();
10295 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10296 }
10297 break;
10298 case kF32:
10299 switch (mode) {
10300 case kR2R:
10301 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_F32Select);
10302 F32Pop(); // val2
10303 F32Pop(); // val1
10304 return RegMode::kF32Reg;
10305 case kR2S:
10306 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F32Select);
10307 F32Pop(); // val2
10308 F32Pop(); // val1
10309 F32Push(); // result
10310 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10311 case kS2R:
10312 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F32Select);
10313 I32Pop(); // condition
10314 F32Pop(); // val2
10315 F32Pop(); // val1
10316 return RegMode::kF32Reg;
10317 case kS2S:
10318 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32Select);
10319 I32Pop(); // condition
10320 F32Pop();
10321 F32Pop();
10322 F32Push();
10323 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10324 }
10325 break;
10326 case kF64:
10327 switch (mode) {
10328 case kR2R:
10329 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2r_F64Select);
10330 F64Pop(); // val2
10331 F64Pop(); // val1
10332 return RegMode::kF64Reg;
10333 case kR2S:
10334 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F64Select);
10335 F64Pop(); // val2
10336 F64Pop(); // val1
10337 F64Push(); // result
10338 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10339 case kS2R:
10340 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F64Select);
10341 I32Pop(); // condition
10342 F64Pop(); // val2
10343 F64Pop(); // val1
10344 return RegMode::kF64Reg;
10345 case kS2S:
10346 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64Select);
10347 I32Pop(); // condition
10348 F64Pop();
10349 F64Pop();
10350 F64Push();
10351 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10352 }
10353 break;
10354 case kS128:
10355 switch (mode) {
10356 case kR2R:
10357 case kS2R:
10358 UNREACHABLE();
10359 case kR2S:
10360 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_S128Select);
10361 S128Pop();
10362 S128Pop();
10363 S128Push();
10364 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10365 case kS2S:
10366 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128Select);
10367 I32Pop(); // condition
10368 S128Pop();
10369 S128Pop();
10370 S128Push();
10371 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10372 }
10373 break;
10374 case kRef:
10375 case kRefNull:
10376 switch (mode) {
10377 case kR2R:
10378 case kS2R:
10379 UNREACHABLE();
10380 case kR2S: {
10381 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_RefSelect);
10382 RefPop(); // val2
10383 ValueType type = RefPop(); // val1
10384 RefPush(type); // result
10385 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10386 }
10387 case kS2S: {
10388 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefSelect);
10389 I32Pop(); // condition
10390 RefPop();
10391 ValueType type = RefPop();
10392 RefPush(type);
10393 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10394 }
10395 }
10396 break;
10397 default:
10398 UNREACHABLE();
10399 }
10400 break;
10401 }
10402
10403 case kExprLocalGet: {
10404 switch (slots_[stack_[instr.optional.index]].kind()) {
10405 case kI32:
10406 case kI64:
10407 case kF32:
10408 case kF64:
10409 case kS128:
10410 case kRef:
10411 case kRefNull:
10412 switch (mode) {
10413 case kR2R:
10414 case kR2S:
10415 case kS2R:
10416 UNREACHABLE();
10417 case kS2S:
10418 PushCopySlot(instr.optional.index);
10419 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10420 }
10421 break;
10422 default:
10423 UNREACHABLE();
10424 }
10425 break;
10426 }
10427 case kExprLocalSet: {
10428 DCHECK_LE(instr.optional.index, stack_size());
10429 // Validation ensures that the target slot type must be the same as the
10430 // stack top slot type.
10431 const ValueType value_type =
10432 slots_[stack_[instr.optional.index]].value_type;
10433 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10434 DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(kind, top_stack_slot_type));
10435 switch (kind) {
10436 case kI32:
10437 case kI64:
10438 case kF32:
10439 case kF64:
10440 switch (mode) {
10441 case kR2R:
10442 case kS2R:
10443 UNREACHABLE();
10444 case kR2S:
10445 CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, false, true);
10446 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10447 case kS2S:
10448 CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, false, false);
10449 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10450 }
10451 break;
10452 case kS128:
10453 switch (mode) {
10454 case kR2R:
10455 case kR2S:
10456 case kS2R:
10457 UNREACHABLE();
10458 case kS2S:
10459 CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, false, false);
10460 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10461 }
10462 break;
10463 case kRef:
10464 case kRefNull:
10465 switch (mode) {
10466 case kR2R:
10467 case kR2S:
10468 case kS2R:
10469 UNREACHABLE();
10470 case kS2S:
10471 CopyToSlotAndPop(slots_[stack_.back()].value_type,
10472 instr.optional.index, false, false);
10473 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10474 }
10475 break;
10476 default:
10477 UNREACHABLE();
10478 }
10479 break;
10480 }
10481 case kExprLocalTee: {
10482 DCHECK_LE(instr.optional.index, stack_size());
10483 // Validation ensures that the target slot type must be the same as the
10484 // stack top slot type.
10485 const ValueType value_type =
10486 slots_[stack_[instr.optional.index]].value_type;
10487 const ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
10488 DCHECK(CheckEqualKind(kind, top_stack_slot_type));
10489 switch (kind) {
10490 case kI32:
10491 case kI64:
10492 case kF32:
10493 case kF64:
10494 switch (mode) {
10495 case kR2R:
10496 CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, true, true);
10497 return GetRegMode(value_type.kind());
10498 case kR2S:
10499 UNREACHABLE();
10500 case kS2R:
10501 UNREACHABLE();
10502 case kS2S:
10503 CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, true, false);
10504 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10505 }
10506 break;
10507 case kS128:
10508 switch (mode) {
10509 case kR2R:
10510 case kR2S:
10511 case kS2R:
10512 UNREACHABLE();
10513 case kS2S:
10514 CopyToSlotAndPop(value_type, instr.optional.index, true, false);
10515 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10516 }
10517 break;
10518 case kRef:
10519 case kRefNull:
10520 switch (mode) {
10521 case kR2R:
10522 case kR2S:
10523 case kS2R:
10524 UNREACHABLE();
10525 case kS2S:
10526 CopyToSlotAndPop(slots_[stack_.back()].value_type,
10527 instr.optional.index, true, false);
10528 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10529 }
10530 break;
10531 default:
10532 UNREACHABLE();
10533 }
10534 break;
10535 }
10536 case kExprGlobalGet: {
10537 switch (GetGlobalType(instr.optional.index)) {
10538 case kI32:
10539 switch (mode) {
10540 case kR2R:
10541 case kR2S:
10542 UNREACHABLE();
10543 case kS2R:
10544 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I32GlobalGet);
10545 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10546 return RegMode::kI32Reg;
10547 case kS2S:
10548 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32GlobalGet);
10549 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10550 I32Push();
10551 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10552 }
10553 break;
10554 case kI64:
10555 switch (mode) {
10556 case kR2R:
10557 case kR2S:
10558 UNREACHABLE();
10559 case kS2R:
10560 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_I64GlobalGet);
10561 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10562 return RegMode::kI64Reg;
10563 case kS2S:
10564 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64GlobalGet);
10565 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10566 I64Push();
10567 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10568 }
10569 break;
10570 case kF32:
10571 switch (mode) {
10572 case kR2R:
10573 case kR2S:
10574 UNREACHABLE();
10575 case kS2R:
10576 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F32GlobalGet);
10577 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10578 return RegMode::kF32Reg;
10579 case kS2S:
10580 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32GlobalGet);
10581 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10582 F32Push();
10583 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10584 }
10585 break;
10586 case kF64:
10587 switch (mode) {
10588 case kR2R:
10589 case kR2S:
10590 UNREACHABLE();
10591 case kS2R:
10592 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_F64GlobalGet);
10593 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10594 return RegMode::kF64Reg;
10595 case kS2S:
10596 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64GlobalGet);
10597 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10598 F64Push();
10599 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10600 }
10601 break;
10602 case kS128:
10603 switch (mode) {
10604 case kR2R:
10605 case kR2S:
10606 case kS2R:
10607 UNREACHABLE();
10608 case kS2S:
10609 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128GlobalGet);
10610 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10611 S128Push();
10612 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10613 }
10614 break;
10615 case kRef:
10616 case kRefNull:
10617 switch (mode) {
10618 case kR2R:
10619 case kR2S:
10620 case kS2R:
10621 UNREACHABLE();
10622 case kS2S:
10623 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefGlobalGet);
10624 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10625 RefPush(module_->globals[instr.optional.index].type);
10626 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10627 }
10628 break;
10629 default:
10630 UNREACHABLE();
10631 }
10632 break;
10633 }
10634 case kExprGlobalSet: {
10635 switch (top_stack_slot_type) {
10636 case kI32:
10637 switch (mode) {
10638 case kR2R:
10639 case kS2R:
10640 UNREACHABLE();
10641 case kR2S:
10642 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I32GlobalSet);
10643 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10644 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10645 case kS2S:
10646 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I32GlobalSet);
10647 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10648 I32Pop();
10649 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10650 }
10651 break;
10652 case kI64:
10653 switch (mode) {
10654 case kR2R:
10655 case kS2R:
10656 UNREACHABLE();
10657 case kR2S:
10658 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_I64GlobalSet);
10659 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10660 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10661 case kS2S:
10662 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_I64GlobalSet);
10663 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10664 I64Pop();
10665 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10666 }
10667 break;
10668 case kF32:
10669 switch (mode) {
10670 case kR2R:
10671 case kS2R:
10672 UNREACHABLE();
10673 case kR2S:
10674 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F32GlobalSet);
10675 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10676 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10677 case kS2S:
10678 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F32GlobalSet);
10679 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10680 F32Pop();
10681 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10682 }
10683 break;
10684 case kF64:
10685 switch (mode) {
10686 case kR2R:
10687 case kS2R:
10688 UNREACHABLE();
10689 case kR2S:
10690 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(r2s_F64GlobalSet);
10691 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10692 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10693 case kS2S:
10694 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_F64GlobalSet);
10695 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10696 F64Pop();
10697 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10698 }
10699 break;
10700 case kS128:
10701 switch (mode) {
10702 case kR2R:
10703 case kR2S:
10704 case kS2R:
10705 UNREACHABLE();
10706 case kS2S:
10707 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_S128GlobalSet);
10708 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10709 S128Pop();
10710 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10711 }
10712 break;
10713 case kRef:
10714 case kRefNull:
10715 switch (mode) {
10716 case kR2R:
10717 case kR2S:
10718 case kS2R:
10719 UNREACHABLE();
10720 case kS2S:
10721 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefGlobalSet);
10722 EmitGlobalIndex(instr.optional.index);
10723 RefPop();
10724 return RegMode::kNoReg;
10725 }
10726 break;
10727 default:
10728 UNREACHABLE();
10729 }
10730 break;
10731 }
10732
10733 case kExprTableGet: {
10734 bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
10735 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableGet, s2s_Table64Get, is_table64,
10736 instr.pc);
10737 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
10738 is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
10739 RefPush(module_->tables[instr.optional.index].type);
10740 break;
10741 }
10742
10743 case kExprTableSet: {
10744 bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
10745 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableSet, s2s_Table64Set, is_table64,
10746 instr.pc);
10747 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
10748 RefPop();
10749 is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
10750 break;
10751 }

10753#define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
10754 case kExpr##name: { \
10755 switch (mode) { \
10756 case kR2R: \
10757 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2r_##name, r2r_##name##_Idx64, \
10758 is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10759 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10760 return RegMode::k##type##Reg; \
10761 case kR2S: \
10762 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_##name, r2s_##name##_Idx64, \
10763 is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10764 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10765 type##Push(); \
10766 return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10767 case kS2R: \
10768 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2r_##name, s2r_##name##_Idx64, \
10769 is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10770 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10771 MemIndexPop(); \
10772 return RegMode::k##type##Reg; \
10773 case kS2S: \
10774 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, s2s_##name##_Idx64, \
10775 is_memory64_, instr.pc); \
10776 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset); \
10777 MemIndexPop(); \
10778 type##Push(); \
10779 return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10780 } \
10781 break; \
10782 }
10783 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8S, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
10784 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);
10785 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16S, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
10786 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);
10787 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8S, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
10788 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
10789 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
10790 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
10791 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
10792 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);
10793 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
10794 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
10795 LOAD_CASE(F32LoadMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
10796 LOAD_CASE(F64LoadMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);

10893#define EXECUTE_BINOP(name, ctype, reg, op, type) \

10899 return RegMode::kI32Reg; \

10902 type##Pop(); \
10903 I32Push(); \
10904 return RegMode::kNoReg; \
10905 case kS2R: \
10906 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2r_##name); \
10907 type##Pop(); \
10908 type##Pop(); \
10909 return RegMode::kI32Reg; \

10912 type##Pop(); \

10915 return RegMode::kNoReg; \

11025 return RegMode::kNoReg; \
11026 } \
11027 break; \
11028 }

11112 case kExprRefNull: {
11113 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefNull);
11114 ValueType value_type =
11115 ValueType::RefNull(HeapType(instr.optional.ref_type));
11116 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11117 RefPush(value_type);
11118 break;
11119 }
11120
11121 case kExprRefIsNull:
11122 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefIsNull);
11123 RefPop();
11124 I32Push();
11125 break;
11126
11127 case kExprRefFunc: {
11128 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefFunc);
11129 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11130 ValueType value_type =
11131 ValueType::Ref(module_->functions[instr.optional.index].sig_index);
11132 RefPush(value_type);
11133 break;
11134 }
11135
11136 case kExprRefEq:
11137 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefEq);
11138 RefPop();
11139 RefPop();
11140 I32Push();
11141 break;
11142
11143 case kExprRefAsNonNull: {
11144 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefAsNonNull, instr.pc);
11145 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11146 RefPush(value_type);
11147 break;
11148 }
11149
11150 case kExprStructNew: {
11151 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_StructNew);
11152 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11153 // Pops args
11154 const StructType* struct_type = module_->struct_type(
11155 ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.struct_index}));
11156 for (uint32_t i = struct_type->field_count(); i > 0;) {
11157 i--;
11158 ValueKind kind = struct_type->field(i).kind();
11159 Pop(kind);
11160 }
11161
11162 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index})));
11163 break;
11164 }
11165
11166 case kExprStructNewDefault: {
11167 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_StructNewDefault);
11168 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11169 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index})));
11170 break;
11171 }
11172
11173 case kExprStructGet:
11174 case kExprStructGetS:
11175 case kExprStructGetU: {
11176 bool is_signed = (instr.opcode == wasm::kExprStructGetS);
11177 const StructType* struct_type = module_->struct_type(
11178 ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.struct_index}));
11179 uint32_t field_index = instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.field_index;
11180 ValueType value_type = struct_type->field(field_index);
11181 ValueKind kind = value_type.kind();
11182 int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field_index);
11183 switch (kind) {
11184 case kI8:
11185 if (is_signed) {
11186 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8SStructGet, instr.pc);
11187 } else {
11188 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8UStructGet, instr.pc);
11189 }
11190 RefPop();
11191 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11192 I32Push();
11193 break;
11194 case kI16:
11195 if (is_signed) {
11196 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16SStructGet, instr.pc);
11197 } else {
11198 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16UStructGet, instr.pc);
11199 }
11200 RefPop();
11201 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11202 I32Push();
11203 break;
11204 case kI32:
11205 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32StructGet, instr.pc);
11206 RefPop();
11207 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11208 I32Push();
11209 break;
11210 case kI64:
11211 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64StructGet, instr.pc);
11212 RefPop();
11213 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11214 I64Push();
11215 break;
11216 case kF32:
11217 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32StructGet, instr.pc);
11218 RefPop();
11219 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11220 F32Push();
11221 break;
11222 case kF64:
11223 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64StructGet, instr.pc);
11224 RefPop();
11225 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11226 F64Push();
11227 break;
11228 case kS128:
11229 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128StructGet, instr.pc);
11230 RefPop();
11231 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11232 S128Push();
11233 break;
11234 case kRef:
11235 case kRefNull:
11236 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefStructGet, instr.pc);
11237 RefPop();
11238 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11239 RefPush(value_type);
11240 break;
11241 default:
11242 UNREACHABLE();
11243 }
11244 break;
11245 }
11246
11247 case kExprStructSet: {
11248 const StructType* struct_type = module_->struct_type(
11249 ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.struct_index}));
11250 uint32_t field_index = instr.optional.gc_field_immediate.field_index;
11251 int offset = StructFieldOffset(struct_type, field_index);
11252 ValueKind kind = struct_type->field(field_index).kind();
11253 switch (kind) {
11254 case kI8:
11255 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8StructSet, instr.pc);
11256 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11257 I32Pop();
11258 break;
11259 case kI16:
11260 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16StructSet, instr.pc);
11261 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11262 I32Pop();
11263 break;
11264 case kI32:
11265 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32StructSet, instr.pc);
11266 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11267 I32Pop();
11268 break;
11269 case kI64:
11270 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64StructSet, instr.pc);
11271 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11272 I64Pop();
11273 break;
11274 case kF32:
11275 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32StructSet, instr.pc);
11276 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11277 F32Pop();
11278 break;
11279 case kF64:
11280 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64StructSet, instr.pc);
11281 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11282 F64Pop();
11283 break;
11284 case kS128:
11285 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128StructSet, instr.pc);
11286 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11287 S128Pop();
11288 break;
11289 case kRef:
11290 case kRefNull:
11291 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefStructSet, instr.pc);
11292 EmitStructFieldOffset(offset);
11293 RefPop();
11294 break;
11295 default:
11296 UNREACHABLE();
11297 }
11298 RefPop(); // The object to set the field to.
11299 break;
11300 }
11301
11302 case kExprArrayNew: {
11303 uint32_t array_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_fixed.array_index;
11304 const ArrayType* array_type =
11305 module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}));
11306 ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type();
11307 ValueKind kind = element_type.kind();
11308
11309 // Pop a single value to be used to initialize the array.
11310 switch (kind) {
11311 case kI8:
11312 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11313 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11314 I32Pop(); // Array length.
11315 I32Pop(); // Initialization value.
11316 break;
11317 case kI16:
11318 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11319 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11320 I32Pop();
11321 I32Pop();
11322 break;
11323 case kI32:
11324 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11325 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11326 I32Pop();
11327 I32Pop();
11328 break;
11329 case kI64:
11330 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11331 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11332 I32Pop();
11333 I64Pop();
11334 break;
11335 case kF32:
11336 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11337 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11338 I32Pop();
11339 F32Pop();
11340 break;
11341 case kF64:
11342 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11343 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11344 I32Pop();
11345 F64Pop();
11346 break;
11347 case kS128:
11348 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128ArrayNew, instr.pc);
11349 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11350 I32Pop();
11351 S128Pop();
11352 break;
11353 case kRef:
11354 case kRefNull:
11355 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefArrayNew, instr.pc);
11356 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11357 I32Pop();
11358 RefPop();
11359 break;
11360 default:
11361 UNREACHABLE();
11362 }
11363 // Push the new array.
11364 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index})));
11365 break;
11366 }
11367
11368 case kExprArrayNewFixed: {
11369 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayNewFixed, instr.pc);
11370 uint32_t length = instr.optional.gc_array_new_fixed.length;
11371 uint32_t array_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_fixed.array_index;
11372 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11373 EmitI32Const(length);
11374 const ArrayType* array_type =
11375 module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index}));
11376 ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type();
11377 ValueKind kind = element_type.kind();
11378 // Pop values to initialize the array.
11379 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
11380 switch (kind) {
11381 case kI8:
11382 case kI16:
11383 case kI32:
11384 I32Pop();
11385 break;
11386 case kI64:
11387 I64Pop();
11388 break;
11389 case kF32:
11390 F32Pop();
11391 break;
11392 case kF64:
11393 F64Pop();
11394 break;
11395 case kS128:
11396 S128Pop();
11397 break;
11398 case kRef:
11399 case kRefNull:
11400 RefPop();
11401 break;
11402 default:
11403 UNREACHABLE();
11404 }
11405 }
11406 // Push the new array.
11407 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index})));
11408 break;
11409 }
11410
11411 case kExprArrayNewDefault: {
11412 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayNewDefault, instr.pc);
11413 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11414 I32Pop();
11415 // Push the new array.
11416 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index})));
11417 break;
11418 }
11419
11420 case kExprArrayNewData: {
11421 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayNewData, instr.pc);
11422 uint32_t array_index =
11423 instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.array_index;
11424 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11425 uint32_t data_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.data_index;
11426 EmitI32Const(data_index);
11427 I32Pop();
11428 I32Pop();
11429 // Push the new array.
11430 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index})));
11431 break;
11432 }
11433
11434 case kExprArrayNewElem: {
11435 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayNewElem, instr.pc);
11436 uint32_t array_index =
11437 instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.array_index;
11438 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11439 uint32_t data_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.data_index;
11440 EmitI32Const(data_index);
11441 I32Pop();
11442 I32Pop();
11443 // Push the new array.
11444 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(ModuleTypeIndex({array_index})));
11445 break;
11446 }
11447
11448 case kExprArrayInitData: {
11449 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayInitData, instr.pc);
11450 uint32_t array_index =
11451 instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.array_index;
11452 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11453 uint32_t data_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.data_index;
11454 EmitI32Const(data_index);
11455 I32Pop(); // size
11456 I32Pop(); // src offset
11457 I32Pop(); // dest offset
11458 RefPop(); // array to initialize
11459 break;
11460 }
11461
11462 case kExprArrayInitElem: {
11463 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayInitElem, instr.pc);
11464 uint32_t array_index =
11465 instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.array_index;
11466 EmitI32Const(array_index);
11467 uint32_t data_index = instr.optional.gc_array_new_or_init_data.data_index;
11468 EmitI32Const(data_index);
11469 I32Pop(); // size
11470 I32Pop(); // src offset
11471 I32Pop(); // dest offset
11472 RefPop(); // array to initialize
11473 break;
11474 }
11475
11476 case kExprArrayLen: {
11477 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayLen, instr.pc);
11478 RefPop();
11479 I32Push();
11480 break;
11481 }
11482
11483 case kExprArrayCopy: {
11484 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_ArrayCopy, instr.pc);
11485 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_array_copy.dest_array_index);
11486 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_array_copy.src_array_index);
11487 I32Pop(); // size
11488 I32Pop(); // src offset
11489 RefPop(); // src array
11490 I32Pop(); // dest offset
11491 RefPop(); // dest array
11492 break;
11493 }
11494
11495 case kExprArrayGet:
11496 case kExprArrayGetS:
11497 case kExprArrayGetU: {
11498 bool is_signed = (instr.opcode == wasm::kExprArrayGetS);
11499 const ArrayType* array_type =
11500 module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index}));
11501 ValueType element_type = array_type->element_type();
11502 ValueKind kind = element_type.kind();
11503 switch (kind) {
11504 case kI8:
11505 if (is_signed) {
11506 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8SArrayGet, instr.pc);
11507 } else {
11508 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8UArrayGet, instr.pc);
11509 }
11510 I32Pop();
11511 RefPop();
11512 I32Push();
11513 break;
11514 case kI16:
11515 if (is_signed) {
11516 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16SArrayGet, instr.pc);
11517 } else {
11518 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16UArrayGet, instr.pc);
11519 }
11520 I32Pop();
11521 RefPop();
11522 I32Push();
11523 break;
11524 case kI32:
11525 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32ArrayGet, instr.pc);
11526 I32Pop();
11527 RefPop();
11528 I32Push();
11529 break;
11530 case kI64:
11531 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64ArrayGet, instr.pc);
11532 I32Pop();
11533 RefPop();
11534 I64Push();
11535 break;
11536 case kF32:
11537 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32ArrayGet, instr.pc);
11538 I32Pop();
11539 RefPop();
11540 F32Push();
11541 break;
11542 case kF64:
11543 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64ArrayGet, instr.pc);
11544 I32Pop();
11545 RefPop();
11546 F64Push();
11547 break;
11548 case kS128:
11549 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128ArrayGet, instr.pc);
11550 I32Pop();
11551 RefPop();
11552 S128Push();
11553 break;
11554 case kRef:
11555 case kRefNull:
11556 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefArrayGet, instr.pc);
11557 I32Pop();
11558 RefPop();
11559 RefPush(element_type);
11560 break;
11561 default:
11562 UNREACHABLE();
11563 }
11564 break;
11565 }
11566
11567 case kExprArraySet: {
11568 const ArrayType* array_type =
11569 module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index}));
11570 ValueKind kind = array_type->element_type().kind();
11571 switch (kind) {
11572 case kI8:
11573 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8ArraySet, instr.pc);
11574 I32Pop();
11575 I32Pop();
11576 RefPop();
11577 break;
11578 case kI16:
11579 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16ArraySet, instr.pc);
11580 I32Pop();
11581 I32Pop();
11582 RefPop();
11583 break;
11584 case kI32:
11585 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32ArraySet, instr.pc);
11586 I32Pop();
11587 I32Pop();
11588 RefPop();
11589 break;
11590 case kI64:
11591 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64ArraySet, instr.pc);
11592 I64Pop();
11593 I32Pop();
11594 RefPop();
11595 break;
11596 case kF32:
11597 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32ArraySet, instr.pc);
11598 F32Pop();
11599 I32Pop();
11600 RefPop();
11601 break;
11602 case kF64:
11603 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64ArraySet, instr.pc);
11604 F64Pop();
11605 I32Pop();
11606 RefPop();
11607 break;
11608 case kS128:
11609 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128ArraySet, instr.pc);
11610 S128Pop();
11611 I32Pop();
11612 RefPop();
11613 break;
11614 case kRef:
11615 case kRefNull:
11616 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefArraySet, instr.pc);
11617 RefPop();
11618 I32Pop();
11619 RefPop();
11620 break;
11621 default:
11622 UNREACHABLE();
11623 }
11624 break;
11625 }
11626
11627 case kExprArrayFill: {
11628 const ArrayType* array_type =
11629 module_->array_type(ModuleTypeIndex({instr.optional.index}));
11630 ValueKind kind = array_type->element_type().kind();
11631 switch (kind) {
11632 case kI8:
11633 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I8ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11634 I32Pop(); // The size of the filled slice.
11635 I32Pop(); // The value with which to fill the array.
11636 I32Pop(); // The offset at which to begin filling.
11637 RefPop(); // The array to fill.
11638 break;
11639 case kI16:
11640 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I16ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11641 I32Pop();
11642 I32Pop();
11643 I32Pop();
11644 RefPop();
11645 break;
11646 case kI32:
11647 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11648 I32Pop();
11649 I32Pop();
11650 I32Pop();
11651 RefPop();
11652 break;
11653 case kI64:
11654 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11655 I32Pop();
11656 I64Pop();
11657 I32Pop();
11658 RefPop();
11659 break;
11660 case kF32:
11661 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11662 I32Pop();
11663 F32Pop();
11664 I32Pop();
11665 RefPop();
11666 break;
11667 case kF64:
11668 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11669 I32Pop();
11670 F64Pop();
11671 I32Pop();
11672 RefPop();
11673 break;
11674 case kS128:
11675 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_S128ArrayFill, instr.pc);
11676 I32Pop();
11677 S128Pop();
11678 I32Pop();
11679 RefPop();
11680 break;
11681 case kRef:
11682 case kRefNull:
11683 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefArrayFill, instr.pc);
11684 I32Pop();
11685 RefPop();
11686 I32Pop();
11687 RefPop();
11688 break;
11689 default:
11690 UNREACHABLE();
11691 }
11692 break;
11693 }
11694
11695 case kExprRefI31: {
11696 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefI31);
11697 I32Pop();
11698 RefPush(ValueType::Ref(HeapType::kI31));
11699 break;
11700 }
11701
11702 case kExprI31GetS: {
11703 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I31GetS, instr.pc);
11704 RefPop();
11705 I32Push();
11706 break;
11707 }
11708
11709 case kExprI31GetU: {
11710 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I31GetU, instr.pc);
11711 RefPop();
11712 I32Push();
11713 break;
11714 }
11715
11716 case kExprRefCast:
11717 case kExprRefCastNull: {
11718 bool null_succeeds = (instr.opcode == kExprRefCastNull);
11719 HeapType target_type = instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.type();
11720 ValueType resulting_value_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11721 target_type, null_succeeds ? kNullable : kNonNullable);
11722
11723 ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
11724 DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
11725
11726 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
11727 // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
11728 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type))) {
11729 if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
11730 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AssertNotNullTypecheck, instr.pc);
11731 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11732 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11733 RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11734 } else {
11735 // Just forward the ref object.
11736 }
11737 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type,
11738 null_succeeds))) {
11739 // Unrelated types. The only way this will not trap is if the object
11740 // is null.
11741 if (obj_type.is_nullable() && null_succeeds) {
11742 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AssertNullTypecheck, instr.pc);
11743 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11744 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11745 RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11746 } else {
11747 // In this case we just trap.
11748 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TrapIllegalCast, instr.pc);
11749 }
11750 } else {
11751 if (instr.opcode == kExprRefCast) {
11752 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefCast, instr.pc);
11753 } else {
11754 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_RefCastNull, instr.pc);
11755 }
11756 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.type_representation);
11757 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11758 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11759 RefPush(resulting_value_type);
11760 }
11761 break;
11762 }
11763
11764 case kExprRefTest:
11765 case kExprRefTestNull: {
11766 bool null_succeeds = (instr.opcode == kExprRefTestNull);
11767 HeapType target_type = instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.type();
11768
11769 ValueType obj_type = slots_[stack_.back()].value_type;
11770 DCHECK(obj_type.is_object_reference());
11771
11772 // This logic ensures that code generation can assume that functions
11773 // can only be cast to function types, and data objects to data types.
11774 if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysSucceeds(obj_type, target_type))) {
11775 // Type checking can still fail for null.
11776 if (obj_type.is_nullable() && !null_succeeds) {
11777 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefIsNonNull);
11778 RefPop();
11779 I32Push(); // bool
11780 } else {
11781 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestSucceeds);
11782 RefPop();
11783 I32Push(); // bool=true
11784 }
11785 } else if (V8_UNLIKELY(TypeCheckAlwaysFails(obj_type, target_type,
11786 null_succeeds))) {
11787 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestFails);
11788 RefPop();
11789 I32Push(); // bool=false
11790 } else {
11791 if (instr.opcode == kExprRefTest) {
11792 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTest);
11793 } else {
11794 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_RefTestNull);
11795 }
11796 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.gc_heap_type_immediate.type_representation);
11797 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11798 EmitRefValueType(value_type.raw_bit_field());
11799 I32Push(); // bool
11800 }
11801 break;
11802 }
11803
11804 case kExprAnyConvertExtern: {
11805 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AnyConvertExtern, instr.pc);
11806 ValueType extern_val = RefPop();
11807 ValueType intern_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11808 HeapType::kAny, Nullability(extern_val.is_nullable()));
11809 RefPush(intern_type);
11810 break;
11811 }
11812
11813 case kExprExternConvertAny: {
11814 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_ExternConvertAny);
11815 ValueType value_type = RefPop();
11816 ValueType extern_type = ValueType::RefMaybeNull(
11817 HeapType::kExtern, Nullability(value_type.is_nullable()));
11818 RefPush(extern_type);
11819 break;
11820 }
11821
11822 case kExprMemoryInit:
11823 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_MemoryInit, s2s_Memory64Init,
11824 is_memory64_, instr.pc);
11825 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11826 I32Pop();
11827 I32Pop();
11828 MemIndexPop();
11829 break;
11830
11831 case kExprDataDrop:
11832 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_DataDrop);
11833 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11834 break;
11835
11836 case kExprMemoryCopy:
11837 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_MemoryCopy, s2s_Memory64Copy,
11838 is_memory64_, instr.pc);
11839 MemIndexPop();
11840 MemIndexPop();
11841 MemIndexPop();
11842 break;
11843
11844 case kExprMemoryFill:
11845 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_MemoryFill, s2s_Memory64Fill,
11846 is_memory64_, instr.pc);
11847 MemIndexPop();
11848 I32Pop();
11849 MemIndexPop();
11850 break;
11851
11852 case kExprTableInit: {
11853 bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11854 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableInit, s2s_Table64Init,
11855 is_table64, instr.pc);
11856
11857 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_init.table_index);
11858 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_init.element_segment_index);
11859 I32Pop();
11860 I32Pop();
11861 is_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11862 } break;
11863
11864 case kExprElemDrop:
11865 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_ElemDrop);
11866 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11867 break;
11868
11869 case kExprTableCopy: {
11870 bool is_src_table64 =
11871 module_->tables[instr.optional.table_copy.src_table_index]
11872 .is_table64();
11873 bool is_dst_table64 =
11874 module_->tables[instr.optional.table_copy.dst_table_index]
11875 .is_table64();
11876
11877 if (is_src_table64) {
11878 if (is_dst_table64) {
11879 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Copy_64_64_64, instr.pc);
11880 } else {
11881 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Copy_32_64_32, instr.pc);
11882 }
11883 } else {
11884 if (is_dst_table64) {
11885 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Copy_64_32_32, instr.pc);
11886 } else {
11887 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableCopy, instr.pc);
11888 }
11889 }
11890 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_copy.dst_table_index);
11891 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.table_copy.src_table_index);
11892 is_dst_table64&& is_src_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11893 is_src_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11894 is_dst_table64 ? I64Pop() : I32Pop();
11895 } break;
11896
11897 case kExprTableGrow: {
11898 bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11899 if (is_table64) {
11900 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Table64Grow);
11901 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11902 I64Pop();
11903 RefPop();
11904 I64Push();
11905 } else {
11906 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_TableGrow);
11907 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11908 I32Pop();
11909 RefPop();
11910 I32Push();
11911 }
11912 } break;
11913
11914 case kExprTableSize: {
11915 bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11916 if (is_table64) {
11917 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_Table64Size);
11918 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11919 I64Push();
11920 } else {
11921 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_TableSize);
11922 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11923 I32Push();
11924 }
11925 } break;
11926
11927 case kExprTableFill: {
11928 bool is_table64 = module_->tables[instr.optional.index].is_table64();
11929 if (is_table64) {
11930 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_Table64Fill, instr.pc);
11931 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11932 I64Pop();
11933 RefPop();
11934 I64Pop();
11935 } else {
11936 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_TableFill, instr.pc);
11937 EmitI32Const(instr.optional.index);
11938 I32Pop();
11939 RefPop();
11940 I32Pop();
11941 }
11942 } break;
11943
11944 case kExprAtomicNotify:
11945 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_AtomicNotify, instr.pc);
11946 I32Pop(); // val
11947 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset);
11948 I32Pop(); // memory index
11949 I32Push();
11950 break;
11951
11952 case kExprI32AtomicWait:
11953 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32AtomicWait, instr.pc);
11954 I64Pop(); // timeout
11955 I32Pop(); // val
11956 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset);
11957 I32Pop(); // memory index
11958 I32Push();
11959 break;
11960
11961 case kExprI64AtomicWait:
11962 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64AtomicWait, instr.pc);
11963 I64Pop(); // timeout
11964 I64Pop(); // val
11965 EmitMemoryOffset(instr.optional.offset);
11966 I32Pop(); // memory index
11967 I32Push();
11968 break;
11969
11970 case kExprAtomicFence:
11971 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER(s2s_AtomicFence);
11972 break;
11973
11974#define ATOMIC_BINOP(name, Type, ctype, type, op_ctype, op_type, operation) \
11975 case kExpr##name: { \
11976 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, s2s_##name##_Idx64, \

12646 wasm_code_->start[instr.pc],
12647 WasmOpcodes::OpcodeName(
