12654
12655bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::EncodeSuperInstruction(
12656 RegMode& reg_mode, const WasmInstruction& curr_instr,
12657 const WasmInstruction& next_instr) {
12658 if (!v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode) {
12659 DCHECK_EQ(handler_size_, InstrHandlerSize::Large);
12660 return DoEncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr);
12661 }
12662
12663 size_t current_instr_code_offset = code_.size();
12664 size_t current_slots_size = slots_.size();
12665 current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
12666 handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Small;
12667 stack_.clear_history();
12668
12669 bool result = DoEncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr);
12670 if (result && current_instr_encoding_failed_) {
12671 code_.resize(current_instr_code_offset);
12672 slots_.resize(current_slots_size);
12673 stack_.rollback();
12674 current_instr_encoding_failed_ = false;
12675 handler_size_ = InstrHandlerSize::Large;
12676 result = DoEncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr);
12677 DCHECK(!current_instr_encoding_failed_);
12678 }
12679
12680 return result;
12681}
12682
12683bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::DoEncodeSuperInstruction(
12684 RegMode& reg_mode, const WasmInstruction& curr_instr,
12685 const WasmInstruction& next_instr) {
12686 if (curr_instr.orig >= kExprI32LoadMem &&
12687 curr_instr.orig <= kExprI64LoadMem32U &&
12688 next_instr.orig == kExprLocalSet) {
12689 // Do not optimize if we are updating a shared slot.
12690 uint32_t to_stack_index = next_instr.optional.index;
12691 if (HasSharedSlot(to_stack_index)) return false;
12692
12693 switch (curr_instr.orig) {
12694// The implementation of r2s_LoadMem_LocalSet is identical to the
12695// implementation of r2s_LoadMem, so we can reuse the same builtin.
12696#define LOAD_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
12697 case kExpr##name: { \
12698 if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) { \
12699 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name##_LocalSet, \
12700 s2s_##name##_LocalSet_Idx64, \
12701 is_memory64_, curr_instr.pc); \
12702 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset); \
12703 MemIndexPop(); \
12704 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[to_stack_index]].slot_offset); \
12705 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg; \
12706 } else { \
12707 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_##name, r2s_##name##_Idx64, \
12708 is_memory64_, curr_instr.pc); \
12709 EmitMemoryOffset(static_cast<uint64_t>(curr_instr.optional.offset)); \
12710 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[to_stack_index]].slot_offset); \
12711 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg; \
12712 } \
12713 return true; \
12714 }
12715 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8S, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
12716 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem8U, int32_t, uint8_t, kWord8, I32);
12717 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16S, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
12718 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem16U, int32_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I32);
12719 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8S, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
12720 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem8U, int64_t, uint8_t, kWord16, I64);
12721 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16S, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
12722 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem16U, int64_t, uint16_t, kWord16, I64);
12723 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32S, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
12724 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem32U, int64_t, uint32_t, kWord32, I64);
12725 LOAD_CASE(I32LoadMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
12726 LOAD_CASE(I64LoadMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
12727 LOAD_CASE(F32LoadMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
12728 LOAD_CASE(F64LoadMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
12729#undef LOAD_CASE
12730
12731 default:
12732 return false;
12733 }
12734 } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprI32LoadMem &&
12735 next_instr.orig == kExprI32StoreMem) {
12736 if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12737 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I32LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12738 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset); // load_offset
12739 I32Pop(); // load_index
12740 } else {
12741 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_I32LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12742 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset); // load_offset
12743 }
12744 EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset); // store_offset
12745 I32Pop(); // store_index
12746 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12747 return true;
12748 } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprI64LoadMem &&
12749 next_instr.orig == kExprI64StoreMem) {
12750 if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12751 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_I64LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12752 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12753 I32Pop();
12754 } else {
12755 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_I64LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12756 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12757 }
12758 EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset);
12759 I32Pop();
12760 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12761 return true;
12762 } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprF32LoadMem &&
12763 next_instr.orig == kExprF32StoreMem) {
12764 if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12765 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F32LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12766 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12767 I32Pop();
12768 } else {
12769 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_F32LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12770 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12771 }
12772 EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset);
12773 I32Pop();
12774 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12775 return true;
12776 } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprF64LoadMem &&
12777 next_instr.orig == kExprF64StoreMem) {
12778 if (reg_mode == RegMode::kNoReg) {
12779 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_F64LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12780 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12781 I32Pop();
12782 } else {
12783 EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(r2s_F64LoadStoreMem, curr_instr.pc);
12784 EmitMemoryOffset(curr_instr.optional.offset);
12785 }
12786 EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset);
12787 I32Pop();
12788 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12789 return true;
12790 } else if (curr_instr.orig >= kExprI32Const &&
12791 curr_instr.orig <= kExprF32Const &&
12792 next_instr.orig == kExprLocalSet) {
12793 uint32_t to_stack_index = next_instr.optional.index;
12794 switch (curr_instr.orig) {
12795 case kExprI32Const: {
12796 uint32_t from_slot_index =
12797 CreateConstSlot<int32_t>(curr_instr.optional.i32);
12798 CopyToSlot(kWasmI32, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12799 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12800 return true;
12801 }
12802 case kExprI64Const: {
12803 uint32_t from_slot_index =
12804 CreateConstSlot<int64_t>(curr_instr.optional.i64);
12805 CopyToSlot(kWasmI64, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12806 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12807 return true;
12808 }
12809 case kExprF32Const: {
12810 uint32_t from_slot_index =
12811 CreateConstSlot<float>(curr_instr.optional.f32);
12812 CopyToSlot(kWasmF32, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12813 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12814 return true;
12815 }
12816 case kExprF64Const: {
12817 uint32_t from_slot_index =
12818 CreateConstSlot<double>(curr_instr.optional.f64);
12819 CopyToSlot(kWasmF64, from_slot_index, to_stack_index, false);
12820 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12821 return true;
12822 }
12823 default:
12824 return false;
12825 }
12826 } else if (curr_instr.orig == kExprLocalGet &&
12827 next_instr.orig >= kExprI32StoreMem &&
12828 next_instr.orig <= kExprI64StoreMem32) {
12829 switch (next_instr.orig) {
12830// The implementation of r2s_LocalGet_StoreMem is identical to the
12831// implementation of r2s_StoreMem, so we can reuse the same builtin.
12832#define STORE_CASE(name, ctype, mtype, rep, type) \
12833 case kExpr##name: { \
12834 EMIT_MEM64_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_PC(s2s_##name, s2s_##name##_Idx64, \
12835 is_memory64_, curr_instr.pc); \
12836 EmitSlotOffset(slots_[stack_[curr_instr.optional.index]].slot_offset); \
12837 EmitMemoryOffset(next_instr.optional.offset); \
12838 MemIndexPop(); \
12839 reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg; \
12840 return true; \
12841 }
12842 STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem8, int32_t, int8_t, kWord8, I32);
12843 STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem16, int32_t, int16_t, kWord16, I32);
12844 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem8, int64_t, int8_t, kWord8, I64);
12845 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem16, int64_t, int16_t, kWord16, I64);
12846 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem32, int64_t, int32_t, kWord32, I64);
12847 STORE_CASE(I32StoreMem, int32_t, int32_t, kWord32, I32);
12848 STORE_CASE(I64StoreMem, int64_t, int64_t, kWord64, I64);
12849 STORE_CASE(F32StoreMem, Float32, uint32_t, kFloat32, F32);
12850 STORE_CASE(F64StoreMem, Float64, uint64_t, kFloat64, F64);
12851#undef STORE_CASE
12852
12853 default:
12854 return false;
12855 }
12856 }
12857
12858 return false;
12859}
12860
12861std::unique_ptr<WasmBytecode> WasmBytecodeGenerator::GenerateBytecode() {
12862#ifdef V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
12863 if (v8_flags.trace_drumbrake_bytecode_generator) {
12864 printf("\nGenerate bytecode for function: %d\n", function_index_);
12865 }
12866#endif // V8_ENABLE_DRUMBRAKE_TRACING
12867
12868 uint32_t const_slots = ScanConstInstructions();
12869 const_slots_values_.resize(const_slots * kSlotSize);
12870
12871 pc_t pc = wasm_code_->locals.encoded_size;
12872 RegMode reg_mode = RegMode::kNoReg;
12873
12874 Decoder decoder(wasm_code_->start, wasm_code_->end);
12875
12876 current_block_index_ = -1;
12877
12878 // Init stack_ with return values, args and local types.
12879
12880 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < return_count_; index++) {
12881 CreateSlot(wasm_code_->function->sig->GetReturn(index));
12882 }
12883
12884 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < args_count_; index++) {
12885 _PushSlot(wasm_code_->function->sig->GetParam(index));
12886 }
12887
12888 // Reserve space for const slots
12889 slot_offset_ += const_slots;
12890
12891 for (uint32_t index = 0; index < wasm_code_->locals.num_locals; index++) {
12892 _PushSlot(wasm_code_->locals.local_types[index]);
12893 }
12894
12895 current_block_index_ =
12896 BeginBlock(kExprBlock, {wasm_code_->function->sig_index, kBottom});
12897
12898 WasmInstruction curr_instr;
12899 WasmInstruction next_instr;
12900
12901 pc_t limit = wasm_code_->end - wasm_code_->start;
12902 while (pc < limit) {
12903 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(wasm_code_->start);
12904
12905 if (!curr_instr) {
12906 curr_instr = DecodeInstruction(pc, decoder);
12907 if (curr_instr) pc += curr_instr.length;
12908 }
12909 if (!curr_instr) break;
12910 DCHECK(!next_instr);
12911 next_instr = DecodeInstruction(pc, decoder);
12912 if (next_instr) pc += next_instr.length;
12913
12914 if (next_instr) {
12915 if (v8_flags.drumbrake_super_instructions && is_instruction_reachable_ &&
12916 EncodeSuperInstruction(reg_mode, curr_instr, next_instr)) {
12917 curr_instr = {};
12918 next_instr = {};
12919 } else {
12920 reg_mode =
12921 EncodeInstruction(curr_instr, reg_mode, next_instr.InputRegMode());
12922 curr_instr = next_instr;
12923 next_instr = {};
12924 }
12925 } else {
12926 reg_mode = EncodeInstruction(curr_instr, reg_mode, RegMode::kNoReg);
12927 curr_instr = {};
12928 }
12929
12930 if (pc == limit && curr_instr) {
12931 reg_mode = EncodeInstruction(curr_instr, reg_mode, RegMode::kNoReg);
12932 }
12933 }
12934
12935 PatchLoopBeginInstructions();
12936 PatchBranchOffsets();
12937
12938 total_bytecode_size_ += code_.size();
12939
12940 return std::make_unique<WasmBytecode>(
12941 function_index_, code_.data(), code_.size(), slot_offset_,
12942 module_->functions[function_index_].sig, wasm_code_, blocks_.size(),
12943 const_slots_values_.data(), const_slots_values_.size(), ref_slots_count_,
12944 std::move(eh_data_), std::move(code_pc_map_));
12945}
12946
12947int32_t WasmBytecodeGenerator::BeginBlock(
12948 WasmOpcode opcode, const WasmInstruction::Optional::Block signature) {
12949 int32_t block_index = static_cast<int32_t>(blocks_.size());
12950 uint32_t stack_size = this->stack_size();
12951
12952 uint32_t first_block_index = 0;
12953 size_t rets_slots_count = 0;
12954 size_t params_slots_count = 0;
12955 if (block_index > 0 && (opcode != kExprElse && opcode != kExprCatch &&
12956 opcode != kExprCatchAll)) {
12957 first_block_index = ReserveBlockSlots(opcode, signature, &rets_slots_count,
12958 &params_slots_count);
12959 }
12960
12961 uint32_t parent_block_index = current_block_index_;
12962 if (opcode == kExprCatch || opcode == kExprCatchAll) {
12963 parent_block_index =
12964 blocks_[eh_data_.GetCurrentTryBlockIndex()].parent_block_index_;
12965 }
12966
12967 blocks_.emplace_back(opcode, CurrentCodePos(), parent_block_index, stack_size,
12968 signature, first_block_index, rets_slots_count,
12969 params_slots_count, eh_data_.GetCurrentTryBlockIndex());
12970 current_block_index_ = block_index;
12971
12972 if (opcode == kExprIf && params_slots_count > 0) {
12973 DCHECK_GE(stack_size, params_slots_count);
12974 blocks_.back().SaveParams(&stack_[stack_size - params_slots_count],
12975 params_slots_count);
12976 }
12977
12978 if (opcode == kExprLoop) {
12979 StoreBlockParamsIntoSlots(current_block_index_, true);
12980 loop_begin_code_offsets_.push_back(CurrentCodePos());
12981 blocks_[current_block_index_].begin_code_offset_ = CurrentCodePos();
12982 last_instr_offset_ = kInvalidCodeOffset;
12983
12984 START_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER_WITH_ID(s2s_OnLoopBegin) {}
12985 END_EMIT_INSTR_HANDLER()
12986 }
12987 return current_block_index_;
12988}
12989
12990int WasmBytecodeGenerator::GetCurrentTryBlockIndex(
12991 bool return_matching_try_for_catch_blocks) const {
12992 DCHECK_GE(current_block_index_, 0);
12993 int index = current_block_index_;
12994 while (index >= 0) {
12995 const auto& block = blocks_[index];
12996 if (block.IsTry()) return index;
12997 if (return_matching_try_for_catch_blocks &&
12998 (block.IsCatch() || block.IsCatchAll())) {
12999 return block.parent_try_block_index_;
13000 }
13001 index = blocks_[index].parent_block_index_;
13002 }
13003 return -1;
13004}
13005
13006void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PatchLoopBeginInstructions() {
13007 if (ref_slots_count_ == 0) {
13008 for (size_t i = 0; i < loop_begin_code_offsets_.size(); i++) {
13009 base::WriteUnalignedValue<InstructionHandler>(
13010 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + loop_begin_code_offsets_[i]),
13011 k_s2s_OnLoopBeginNoRefSlots);
13012 }
13013 }
13014}
13015
13016void WasmBytecodeGenerator::PatchBranchOffsets() {
13017 static const uint32_t kElseBlockStartOffset =
13018 sizeof(InstructionHandler) + sizeof(uint32_t);
13019
13020 for (int block_index = 0; block_index < static_cast<int>(blocks_.size());
13021 block_index++) {
13022 const BlockData block_data = blocks_[block_index];
13023 for (size_t i = 0; i < block_data.branch_code_offsets_.size(); i++) {
13024 uint32_t current_code_offset = block_data.branch_code_offsets_[i];
13025 uint32_t target_offset = block_data.end_code_offset_;
13026 if (block_data.IsLoop()) {
13027 target_offset = block_data.begin_code_offset_;
13028 } else if (block_data.IsIf() && block_data.if_else_block_index_ >= 0 &&
13029 current_code_offset == block_data.begin_code_offset_) {
13030 // Jumps to the 'else' branch.
13031 target_offset =
13032 blocks_[block_data.if_else_block_index_].begin_code_offset_ +
13033 kElseBlockStartOffset;
13034 } else if ((block_data.IsCatch() || block_data.IsCatchAll()) &&
13035 current_code_offset == block_data.begin_code_offset_ +
13036 sizeof(InstructionHandler)) {
13037 // Jumps to the end of a sequence of 'try'/'catch' branches.
13038 target_offset = static_cast<uint32_t>(
13039 eh_data_.GetEndInstructionOffsetFor(block_index));
13040 }
13041
13042 int32_t delta = target_offset - current_code_offset;
13043 base::WriteUnalignedValue<uint32_t>(
13044 reinterpret_cast<Address>(code_.data() + current_code_offset), delta);
13045 }
13046 }
13047}
13048
13049bool WasmBytecodeGenerator::TryCompactInstructionHandler(
13050 InstructionHandler func_id) {
13051 if (last_instr_offset_ == kInvalidCodeOffset) return false;
13052 InstructionHandler* prev_instr_addr =
13053 reinterpret_cast<InstructionHandler*>(code_.data() + last_instr_offset_);
13054 InstructionHandler prev_instr_handler = *prev_instr_addr;
13055 if (func_id == k_s2s_CopySlot32 && prev_instr_handler == k_s2s_CopySlot32) {
13056 // Tranforms:
13057 // [CopySlot32: InstrId][from: slot_offset_t][to: slot_offset_t]
13058 // into:
13059 // [CopySlot32x2: InstrId][from0: slot_offset_t][to0: slot_offset_t][from1:
13060 // slot_offset_t][to1: slot_offset_t]
13061 DCHECK(handler_size_ == InstrHandlerSize::Large ||
13062 v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode);
13063 base::WriteUnalignedValue<InstructionHandler>(
13064 reinterpret_cast<Address>(prev_instr_addr), k_s2s_CopySlot32x2);
13065 return true;
13066 } else if (func_id == k_s2s_CopySlot64 &&
13067 prev_instr_handler == k_s2s_CopySlot64) {
13068 DCHECK(handler_size_ == InstrHandlerSize::Large ||
13069 v8_flags.drumbrake_compact_bytecode);
13070 base::WriteUnalignedValue<InstructionHandler>(
13071 reinterpret_cast<Address>(prev_instr_addr), k_s2s_CopySlot64x2);
13072 return true;
13073 }
13074 return false;
13075}
13076
13077ClearThreadInWasmScope::ClearThreadInWasmScope(Isolate* isolate)
13078 : isolate_(isolate) {
13079 DCHECK_IMPLIES(trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled(),
13080 trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm());
13081 trap_handler::ClearThreadInWasm();
13082}
13083
13084ClearThreadInWasmScope ::~ClearThreadInWasmScope() {
13085 DCHECK_IMPLIES(trap_handler::IsTrapHandlerEnabled(),
13086 !trap_handler::IsThreadInWasm());
13087 if (!isolate_->has_exception()) {
13088 trap_handler::SetThreadInWasm();
13089 }
13090 // Otherwise we only want to set the flag if the exception is caught in
13091 // wasm. This is handled by the unwinder.
13092}
